BODY: story your father s preyanuj had gone on a holiday for one month and when he returns he turned the key in the lock and opens the door to his horror he finds someone staring at him and then suddenly there was a loud crack of thunder he saw that one boy who looked exactly the same as anuj jumped out of the balcony before we move further let us start from the beginning anuj is a college student who is the second boy of his college in calcutta he stayed in the hostel of that college he had a small vacation of durga puja so he went to his home to spend some time with his loved ones and end his boredom but unfortunately his father who was the professor of anuj s college died of a strange disease that could not be cured by any medicines or therapy he was already not mentally peaceful and this incident happened when he returned to the hostel he turned the key to his room it was a stormy night there was a load shedding so he took a torch in his hand his roommate and his best friend rony who was the first boy the college didn t come yet so he had to stay alone for some days when he entered the room he saw a boy who looked like him jumped out of the balcony he was horrified he didn t enter his room rather he rushed to the security guard anand but when anand examined the room balcony he saw everything was at their places then anuj calmed down his mind and entered the room he thought it was his hallucination after his mournful holidays he always had suffocation in that room after that incident he couldn t sleep he was losing his concentration on studies and was gradually attacked by insomnia so he asked his hostel s superintendent ajay to shift his room ajay said yes that s a big problem but you should try to overcome it there is one room vacant but you know that it is locked by your father before his death and it should not be opened as instructed by him but anuj refused to listen he asked ajay to give him the keys and took his belongings to that room the slowly settled in that room and could now sleep peacefully one hectic day he came to his room and threw his body on the bed and slowly went to sleep he had a dreadful dream and woke up he saw all his belongings scattered here and there he closed his eyes and thought maybe he himself had done it and now he will have to keep the things at their proper places he didn t want to get up he wished if rony was there when anuj opened his eyes and saw two human feet in front of him he stood up and what he saw was really horrifying a boy was hanging from the fan seeing this his voice choked he couldn t keep himself standing and fainted when he opened his eyes he saw he was in the hospital ajay was the first man to meet him he said see what happened to you i told you not to stay in that room anuj asked why that incident took place with him why he saw all this and why his father forbidden anyone to stay in that room ajay said your father wanted you to be the first student of this college so he made rony stay here for some days and he was promised that he get extra holidays but who knew his holidays will be forever your father murdered rony and hanged him in that room so that everyone thinks that he committed suicide saying so he broke into tears anuj didn t say a single word he called the police and the police arrested ajay anuj s face became red with anger and grief with tears he asked his friend to forgive him and prayed so that his soul rest in peace after recovering he decided to leave the hostel his things were shifted so he went to the room to see if anything is left or not soon he found a note on the table it said anuj your father got the punishment for his wrong deed now you have to focus on your aim and proceed towards it remember your father did this to see you as a topper don t disrespect his wish this will let your father s soul stay peacefully and mine too take care farewell your father s prey ronyayantika rakshit

movie series supply kora bondho koreche thale ekhon h2s er kaj ta kimovie sharing 6ara aar kono kaj thakte parena apnar moton lokeder bola je apnader supply dite amra apatoto okkhom h2s is a community nowi want to join private grouppupa k k dekhechen indrasis acharya er chobiit s one of the most saddest thing that h2s has stopped sharing movies and series the quality which h2s provided to us was one of the finest quality in telegram and tbh i really miss those contents because there are many channels in telegram but the uniqueness which i found in h2s is rare and i m unable to find the same in other channels but anyways thankyou h2s for providing such great content i really wish you start uploading these great movies again thankyou another one bites the dust banned e x reviewname the shape of water 2019 director guillermo del toroimdb rating 7 3 10my rating 7 10the movie starts with elisa a mute girl she lives in her humble apartment takes care of her artist neighbor before going to the marine research corp where she works as a sweeper her life isn t much colorful just like any other lower middle class working girl director paid enough effort to portray it but everything changes one day when a new asset arrives into the facility a humanoid green merman like creature from amazon our protagonist gets curious tries to communicate with the new creature feeds it and it turns out that the creature is actually intelligent enough to respond and communicate the mute unaccepted unloved elisa founds her resemblance to the creature than the humans who just treat it as a disposable lab rat a unnatural friendship starts to grow they fall in love elisa finds a meaning to her life on the other hand director of the facility decides to kill and disect the oragnism to learn more and from here everything escalates fast a russian undercover scientist elisa and her co worker zelda and elisa s artist neighbor gets into a dangerous play of extracting the creature to release it into the sea and finally in a series of jawdropping events they almost does it just before elisa and her creature gets shot following their russian alley it looks like a sad classic ending to a different kind of love story but here comes the signature of del toro he doesn t end the movie there he shows us the revival of the god like amazonian creature who gets up heals his wounds and get the revenge for elisa s death and then we re shown an alternate ending where he takes dead elisa to water and elisa starts to breathe again narrator on the background says if you ask i would say i remember a poem for elisa i didn t know the shape of you so i imgined you all around me that s the shape of water i don t know what del toro tried to show but i felt that absurd ending quite valuable for the movie it s just a ode to an unfulfilled love we know elisa dies but we wish she would be alive to live happily with her man that s where director wins the game he created a open ending that feels like a surreal fable that looks like a flat statement but questions us about it s reality and left enough opportunity for us to interpret it another one bites the dust banned reason fake id both apple and google are part of the global surveillance program that implies that these companies have to among other things implement backdoors into their mobile operating systems these backdoors usually disguised as security bugs allow us agencies to access information on any smartphone in the world the problem with such backdoors is that they are never exclusive to just one party anybody can exploit them so if a us security agency can hack an ios or android phone any other organization that uncovers the backdoors can do the same unsurprisingly this is exactly what has been taking place an israeli company called nso group has been selling access to the spying tools that allowed third parties to hack tens of thousands of phones since at least 2018 i have been aware that one of my phone numbers was included in a list of potential targets of such surveillance tools although a source from the nso group denies it personally i wasn t worried since 2011 when i was still living in russia i ve got used to assuming that all my phones were compromised anyone who gains access to my private data will be utterly disappointed they will have to go through thousands of concept designs for telegram features and millions of messages related to our product development process they won t find any important information there however these surveillance tools are also used against people far more prominent than me for example they were employed to spy on 14 heads of state the existence of backdoors in crucial infrastructure and software creates a huge challenge for humanity that s why i have been calling upon the governments of the world to start acting against the apple google duopoly in the smartphone market and to force them to open their closed ecosystems and allow for more competition so far even though the current market monopolization increases costs and impedes privacy and freedom of speech of billions government officials have been very slow to act i hope the news that they themselves have been targeted by these surveillance tools will prompt politicians to change their minds

BODY: story your father s preyanuj had gone on a holiday for one month and when he returns he turned the key in the lock and opens the door to his horror he finds someone staring at him and then suddenly there was a loud crack of thunder he saw that one boy who looked exactly the same as anuj jumped out of the balcony before we move further let us start from the beginning anuj is a college student who is the second boy of his college in calcutta he stayed in the hostel of that college he had a small vacation of durga puja so he went to his home to spend some time with his loved ones and end his boredom but unfortunately his father who was the professor of anuj s college died of a strange disease that could not be cured by any medicines or therapy he was already not mentally peaceful and this incident happened when he returned to the hostel he turned the key to his room it was a stormy night there was a load shedding so he took a torch in his hand his roommate and his best friend rony who was the first boy the college didn t come yet so he had to stay alone for some days when he entered the room he saw a boy who looked like him jumped out of the balcony he was horrified he didn t enter his room rather he rushed to the security guard anand but when anand examined the room balcony he saw everything was at their places then anuj calmed down his mind and entered the room he thought it was his hallucination after his mournful holidays he always had suffocation in that room after that incident he couldn t sleep he was losing his concentration on studies and was gradually attacked by insomnia so he asked his hostel s superintendent ajay to shift his room ajay said yes that s a big problem but you should try to overcome it there is one room vacant but you know that it is locked by your father before his death and it should not be opened as instructed by him but anuj refused to listen he asked ajay to give him the keys and took his belongings to that room the slowly settled in that room and could now sleep peacefully one hectic day he came to his room and threw his body on the bed and slowly went to sleep he had a dreadful dream and woke up he saw all his belongings scattered here and there he closed his eyes and thought maybe he himself had done it and now he will have to keep the things at their proper places he didn t want to get up he wished if rony was there when anuj opened his eyes and saw two human feet in front of him he stood up and what he saw was really horrifying a boy was hanging from the fan seeing this his voice choked he couldn t keep himself standing and fainted when he opened his eyes he saw he was in the hospital ajay was the first man to meet him he said see what happened to you i told you not to stay in that room anuj asked why that incident took place with him why he saw all this and why his father forbidden anyone to stay in that room ajay said your father wanted you to be the first student of this college so he made rony stay here for some days and he was promised that he get extra holidays but who knew his holidays will be forever your father murdered rony and hanged him in that room so that everyone thinks that he committed suicide saying so he broke into tears anuj didn t say a single word he called the police and the police arrested ajay anuj s face became red with anger and grief with tears he asked his friend to forgive him and prayed so that his soul rest in peace after recovering he decided to leave the hostel his things were shifted so he went to the room to see if anything is left or not soon he found a note on the table it said anuj your father got the punishment for his wrong deed now you have to focus on your aim and proceed towards it remember your father did this to see you as a slumping and lazily browsing through your bookshelf for a quick read a chetan bhagat book serves almost similar flavour what a smaranjit book is meant for in terms of bengali however this time he tries his hand with somewhat he loves to call fun thriller needless to say proving himself wrong in my opinion if not in mass opinion the story unfolds a rajasthani man keshav rajpurohit to fall in one sided love with a kashmiri muslim girl called zara lone the mystery sets in when one night in room 105 keshav finds her dead then the hunt for murderer begins with a juxtaposed outcome the pages are quite full with desi dialogues with a pinch of vulgar swear words random in bhagat ji novels nowadays kashmir sensitive topics terorism hint and army thing are clearly added for more promotional hype than storytelling or for the sake of plot twist i honestly think bhagat misuses his potential by writing his pieces only eying to make these spicey plot for upcoming bollywood masala flicks this one too not devoid of stock characters randomised taken for granted girl characters cheap punchlines and predictable ending thrill part is wasted while comedy part still manages to stand seriously mystery and even danger by the end of each episode i ve been on the edge of my seat i crave more i really do wish that they released all the episodes together but i will not allow that to tarnish the greatness of this show after having such a long break between marvel content this is exactly what i needed to kickstart my love for the franchise again can t wait for more episodes reaction thriller er blending ta osadharon review movie i watched dc s aquaman today and to be honest this movie doesn t deserve to be treated like this by the critics especially aquaman is dc s one of the beautiful and finest creation and above all this movie has proved what dceu can give common movie lovers this movie is outstanding most common thing in the movie was the tone of the movie as it should be dark in story but the story telling is beautifully managed and exceed all our expectation and visuals were simply jaw dropping as a story aquaman is run of the mill mixing bits of national treasure thor black panther ormwasright and green lantern in a good way into an entertaining stew but the devil is in the details and the screen is filled with delightful details easter eggs and visual gags from beginning to end save for a reference to steppenwolf this is an entirely self contained movie and even the mid credit cookie is entirely in the service of this specific franchise it is colorful funny swashbuckling ly violent big screen entertainment with a simple story providing a framework for charming characters and top notch spectacle the third act soars accordingly delivering the promised absurdist lord of the rings but underwater action and by that time we like the characters enough to give a damn momoa s arc as aquaman is solid and includes some especially thoughtful intelligent self awareness and self criticism nicole kidman s atlanna is a wonderfully developed role and the one with the strongest emotional presentation she packs so much into a relatively small number of scenes but it s such a full story and kidman brings it all to life perfectly yahya abdul mateen ii as black manta is aquaman s most hated enemy and the film really sets up their conflict perfectly giving manta a singular understandable drive also he s simply one of the coolest looking villains in comics and now he s become one of the absolutely coolest looking villains in movies patrick wilson s ocean master has a few different motives and goals and it all works well even though i d like to have seen more passionate emphasis on his sense of righteousness regarding the threat posed by the surface world dolph lundgren plays king nereus and willem dafoe plays nuidis vulko both actors delivering smart restrained performances as dignified royalty who must choose sides in an increasingly brutal and complicated conflict aquaman is more similar to wonder woman than it is to batman v superman or man of steel so yeah i got my aquaman movie i mean i got my aquaman movie the one that lived in my heart the one i yearned to see yet never really believed would ever be made aquaman is an amazing achievement in superhero cinema filled with pulse pounding action and dazzling visual effects it s indiana jones black panther avatar and pirates of the caribbean rolled into one blockbuster ball of holiday cinema thanks a lot to happy2share and mystic phoenix for sharing this BODY: review movie spoilerfreetenet don t try to understand it feel it year 2020writer director christopher nolan cinematography hoyte van hoyetemamusic ludwig g ranssoncast john david washington robert pattinson elizabeth debicki kenneth branagh dimple kapadia michael caine and many more this quoted line is from the most awaited movie of christopher nolan tenet this one line was said by a character named laura for the lead character and the audience who were just about experience the absurdness of the film and yes at first i watched the movie at one go without giving a pause just to take that experience and the second time i rewatched few parts of the movie in order to understand it and i would say i tried my best to understand the movie though that is kind of impossible yet i developed my own perception of the entire film the plot is based on an unnamed guy who is referred as the protagonist played by j d washington is recruited by a secret organisation in his afterlife which is engaged in cold war with an unknown enemy he is advised by his senior to go after andrei sator played by kenneth branagh a russian arms dealer who is involved with some rare kind of ammunition that moves backwards through his journey he is assisted by neil robert pattinson and sator s wife katharine elizabeth debicki the first positive point in this movie is the writing probably in every nolan s movie we get an overview of something absurd or beyond our imagination thing is taking place without knowing its source or the cause of why its happening like in inception we never get to know what the whole dream machine is about but we see a detailed procedure of how they get involved in each others dream in interstellar we see the lead character communicating with his daughter through the 5 dimension world but we never get an overview how this is happening but in tenet he gave the explanation of the absurdities occurring though not all but he explains the exact reason behind time reversal concept and the pincher movement but he didn t explain the concept of afterlife and the actual purpose of satore moreover the whole story being told through the perspective of the protagonist gives rise to several mysteries especially the involvement of neil remains a mystery but the ones who have watched the movie closely will know who this neil really is second great thing about this movie is the cinematography the whole time reversal action sequences is a delight to watch in the very beginning when the lead character is at the verge of being killed we see two trains passing simultaneously one in forward and the other one in backward direction which was a hint what is going to happen in the film in many of the action movies when we watch car flipping we watch it on pov shot or through distorted shots but here nolan uses a steady wide angle shot in a whole car flip scene which i must say is very very rare the editing of the movie is abrupt in few cases that is another good thing regarding this film now the negatives i personally didn t find any negatives regarding the film but there are few concepts regarding the movie which you should be familiar with not the time reversal concept but the whole occurrence of the pincher movement is the main key factor if you are the ones who hasn t seen a sci fi thriller or doesn t know about nolan s filmography or style please don t watch this film at first go for his previous films first in order to understand this one and if you want to develop a complete perception regarding this you need to watch each and every minute details and still if you cant you can refer to different blogs there is nothing shame in referring to a blog in order to understand this movie i personally referred to some them in order to find answers to my queries to me this movie another masterpiece by nolan and yes do watch it on a big screen in full hd otherwise you wont be able to experience the stunning visuals and slow motions throughout the film

BODY: review movie spoilerfreedisciple indian film winning the golden lion at venice film festival after 19 years year 2020writer director chaitanya tamhaneproducer vivek gombarcinematography michal soboci skimusic aneesh pradhancast aditya modak sushmita bhave ashwini kulkarni kiran yadnyopavit arun dravid and many more there are few films which can show you the reality of your boring life in a very interesting manner this film is one of them this film won the golden lion award for the best screenplay and the best film critics choice at the prestigious venice film festival which is considered as the oldest and the most prestigious among all other film festivals last film from india which won this award was mira nair aposs monsoon wedding long back in 2000 the plot revolves around a guy named sharad nerulkar who is very passionate and wants to make a career in indian classical music the film focuses more on his journey dilemma struggle regarding various instances in his life the plot may seem very much simple and yet it manages to entangle you in the story due to magnificent cinematography movement of the camera zooming into the lead character as he sings will show how much determination he has for his dreams this shot has been used time and time again in the movie second thing which will attract you is the slow motion shots as our lead character is riding a bike and is listening to the tap recordings of maai this particular camera work shows how much blindly and passionately he listens and follows maai aposs philosophy this particular one shot is trump card of the whole film the frames taken are exceptional and will enhance your visual experience after the cinematography the other positive point is the metaphorical writing in many of the shows and films we get an overview of the traditions regarding classical music but here we get that but not that much and there is a reason for it in the whole movie classical music has been used as a metaphor to anything that we are dedicated to so it is basically a life oriented movie and music has been used only as a metaphor thats why if you closely listen to maai aposs philosophy regarding music they are actually techniques of leading life and lastly the most important point is the sound designing in the whole movie you will get a perfect blend of digentic and non digentic sound the tanpura starts immediately when our lead character is listening to maai aposs philosophy and rest of the part you will hear normal and sounds now the negatives i didn apost find any negatives throughout the movie but this film more about visual storytelling and very less dialogues so if you are not into that then this movie is not for you according to me this movie is more than a masterpiece and i will request each and every individual to watch this film

BODY: press release21 10 2020in 1922 a bengali freedom fighter satindranath sen started a hunger strike movement in the barisal prison of the erstwhile undivided bengal in protest against the oppression of the british jailor he demanded that the political prisoners had to be treated separately from the ordinary prisoners satindranath s 61 day long hunger strike was the first historic movement in the colonial india which demanded the status of political prisoners in 1929 jatindranath das also started a hunger strike in the lahore central jail with the same demand his heroic strike ended in 13th september 1929 when he breathed his last after 63 days of fasting but history repeats itself and we see this when even after 73years of independence political prisoners like prof g n saibaba has had to go for the same hunger strike to protest against the ill treatment of the nagpur jail authority according to his family and the committee set up for his defence release saibaba is being denied of the books letters sent regularly by his family citing covid 19 outbreak he is also being denied of regular newspapers and phone calls to either his family or the lawyer not only that his family complained that the jail authority has not even provided the medical assistance prescribed by his doctor at the same time even after repeated request saibaba who is a 90 percent disabled wheelchair bound person has not been provided with a permanent trained helper equipped to deal with his medical needs as prescribed by the doctors at the government medical college nagpur on the other hand revolutionary poet vara vara rao who is at his 80s and is severely ill has fallen prey to the continuous negligence of the taloja jail hospital authority his family has complained that v v has been denied of necessary medical tests due to his critical condition he is presently kept on urinary catheterization but his family complained that since his urinary bag has not been changed for long he has got infected also because of the continuous neglect of his neurological problems he is totally in an incoherent state and talked about the deadbody of his wife kept in the morgue when she is very much alive we think these incidents cannot be seen simply as negligence but are a part of the cruel vindictive attitude of the indian state towards its political prisoners which can only have resemblance to our colonial past it is utterly shameful that even after the india government being a signatory of the international mandela rules the jail authorities regularly flout the basic rights of the political prisoners of our country so quite obviously political prisoners like saibaba has to take resort to a hunger strike to fight the oppressive rules of the present day indian state we see his fight for the dignity of the political prisoners as the ones which follows the legacy of our beloved freedom fighters so we stand in complete solidarity with prof saibaba and demand immidiate provision of all the necessary items as well as requisite medical assistance to him so that his life as a political prisoner is not threatened crpp w b

BODY: mann kasturi of masaan indian ocean a translation it is hard to do a fair translation of the pithy use of words in this brilliantly produced song mann refers to the heart or soul while kasturi is a musk deer known for its strong perfumed smell the core of the message is this metaphor of the heart as a musk deer the deer keeps looking for the source of the fragrance without realizing that it originates from its own body from within itself another allegory to be mindful of is that of the river ganges which passes through some of the oldest cities of india intersecting lives across many languages and religions rivers are of central importance to all civilizations both ancient and contemporary they have been an immense source of inspiration to people objects of mythic fables a muse for poets and artists across cultures the ganges has a sacrosanct status for those who live around it the originator of life the washer of sins the carrier of death the poetry of this song is imbued with many facets of the human condition growing up growing old finding meaning finding hope shifting perspective and achieving enlightenment managing to self reflect on the medium of poetry itself the escalation of words mirrors the steps of strings culminating in a whirling dervish of a crescendo i hope you find this composition as helpful as i do here are the lyrics and interpretations adapted from here intro paat na paaya meetha paani x2or chhor ki doori re even the purest of sweet river waters cannotbridge the gap between one side of the river to the other mann kasturi re jagg dastoori re x2the heart is a musk deer such is the order of things in life baat hui na poori re which is a conversation without closure mann kasturi re jagg dastoori re baat hui na poori re first verse khoje apni gandh na paawe chaadar ka paiband na paawe x2 the deer looks for its own essence but does not find it cannot decipher the pattern of patchwork on the sheet of existence bikhe bikhre chhand sa tehle dohon mein yeh bandh na paawe wanders around like a broken verse unable to be weaved into poetry naache hoke phirki lattoo x2dances like a spinning topkhoje apni ghoori re searching for its axis of rotation chorus mann kasturi re jagg dastoori re x2baat hui na poori re mann kasturi re jagg dastoori re baat hui na poori re second verse umar ki ginti haath na aayi the mystery of growing old cannot be understood purkhon ne ye baat bataayi the elders have advised us that ulta karke dekh sake toh ambar bhi hai gehri khaayi if you were to turn it upside down the sky too is a bottomless pit rekhaaon ke paar nazar ko jisne phainka andhe mann se whoever sees beyond the bounded dimensions of space with an unbiased heart satrangi bazaar ka khola darwaaza phir bin jatan ke opens the gate to a seven colored world without any efforts at all phir toh jhooma paagul hoke x2sar pe daal phitoori re and then he dances without any care with sheer ecstasy in his head chorus mann kasturi re jagg dastoori re baat hui na poori re x3 outro paat na paaya mann kasturi re meetha paani jagg dastoori re baat hui na baat hui na baat hui na baat hui na poori re mann kasturi paat na paaya jagg dastoori meetha paani baat hui na re poori re sahil loomba medium

BODY: a huge number of players have been given the moniker of the next messi 14 hours ago auttymore than a dozen players have been dubbed the next messi over the years but none have ever reached the heights scaled by barcelona and argentina star lionel messi not even close arsenal are the latest club to be linked with the latest next messi iranian star sardar azmoun who is a star in russia for zenit st petersburg while last summer manchester united were said to be monitoring trabzonspor teenager abdulkadir omur the turkish messi but we all know the type and the hype that follows as soon as any young player comes through who is small quick and able to beat a man off the dribble he s dubbed the next messi double points if he s left footed the world map has almost been filled in with different next messis from around the globe from peru to south africa and japan to iran two dozen countries have produced their own version of the little genius even scotland had one while england have two here s how they got on the english messi patrick robertsburst on to the scene as a teenager at fulham and after some impressive performances as a teenager man city splashed 12million on him he barely got into the city side before a long loan spell at celtic although he won seven trophies under brendan rodgers roberts had a number of injury issues and did not hit the heights expected of him another loan spell to girona last season didn t really work out while stints at norwich and middlesbrough this term have been uninspiring mini messi fran kirbyone of the players most deserving of the tag the england and chelsea star is one of the biggest stars in the women s game kirby who stands at just 5ft 2in is a former pfa and fwa player of the year and has been a vital player in all of the lionesses recent success in december 2018 kirby was voted the 13th best player in the world in an extensive newspaper poll scottish messi ryan gauldgauld was 17 when he made his debut for dundee united and began tearing it up in scotland helping the terrors reach the scottish cup final in 2014 after being shortlisted for young player of the year gauld was snapped up by portuguese giants sporting lisbon but gauld only made two league appearances for sporting all in 2014 and early 2015 and went on four unsuccessful loan spells he s now at portuguese second tier side farense swiss messi xherdan shaqirithe messi comparisons are definitely a step too far but shaqiri now at liverpool is quite obviously a talent good enough for most teams in the world he has played at some of the biggest clubs in the world and scored at two world cups and the european championship injuries have limited his impact this season behind mohamed salah in the pecking order at the reds egyptian messi mohamed salahspeaking of whom there was a time when salah being compared to messi would have been impossible to imagine namely at chelsea now thriving at liverpool the egyptian king isn t quite at messi s level but he s pretty close this was a tag from when the forward was still at basel and in all honesty it s quite fair salah is now one of the best players in the world and will soon have players being dubbed the next salah catalan messi gerard deulofeucertainly has enough natural talent to earn comparisons to one of the best ever but the winger now at watford does not have the consistency or work rate to compare himself to messi deulofeu has struggled in two spells at barca but was instrumental to the hornets getting to the fa cup final in 2019 german messi marko marinarrived at chelsea in 2012 with a massive reputation but like so many other blues youngsters never got a fair chance at stamford bridge was sent on four loan spells in three seasons and managed just six premier league games in west london marin has since won trophies in greece spain and serbia croatian messi alen halilovicanother barcelona graduate the diminutive

BODY: story your father s preyanuj had gone on a holiday for one month and when he returns he turned the key in the lock and opens the door to his horror he finds someone staring at him and then suddenly there was a loud crack of thunder he saw that one boy who looked exactly the same as anuj jumped out of the balcony before we move further let us start from the beginning anuj is a college student who is the second boy of his college in calcutta he stayed in the hostel of that college he had a small vacation of durga puja so he went to his home to spend some time with his loved ones and end his boredom but unfortunately his father who was the professor of anuj s college died of a strange disease that could not be cured by any medicines or therapy he was already not mentally peaceful and this incident happened when he returned to the hostel he turned the key to his room it was a stormy night there was a load shedding so he took a torch in his hand his roommate and his best friend rony who was the first boy the college didn t come yet so he had to stay alone for some days when he entered the room he saw a boy who looked like him jumped out of the balcony he was horrified he didn t enter his room rather he rushed to the security guard anand but when anand examined the room balcony he saw everything was at their places then anuj calmed down his mind and entered the room he thought it was his hallucination after his mournful holidays he always had suffocation in that room after that incident he couldn t sleep he was losing his concentration on studies and was gradually attacked by insomnia so he asked his hostel s superintendent ajay to shift his room ajay said yes that s a big problem but you should try to overcome it there is one room vacant but you know that it is locked by your father before his death and it should not be opened as instructed by him but anuj refused to listen he asked ajay to give him the keys and took his belongings to that room the slowly settled in that room and could now sleep peacefully one hectic day he came to his room and threw his body on the bed and slowly went to sleep he had a dreadful dream and woke up he saw all his belongings scattered here and there he closed his eyes and thought maybe he himself had done it and now he will have to keep the things at their proper places he didn t want to get up he wished if rony was there when anuj opened his eyes and saw two human feet in front of him he stood up and what he saw was really horrifying a boy was hanging from the fan seeing this his voice choked he couldn t keep himself standing and fainted when he opened his eyes he saw he was in the hospital ajay was the first man to meet him he said see what happened to you i told you not to stay in that room anuj asked why that incident took place with him why he saw all this and why his father forbidden anyone to stay in that room ajay said your father wanted you to be the first student of this college so he made rony stay here for some days and he was promised that he get extra holidays but who knew his holidays will be forever your father murdered rony and hanged him in that room so that everyone thinks that he committed suicide saying so he broke into tears anuj didn t say a single word he called the police and the police arrested ajay anuj s face became red with anger and grief with tears he asked his friend to forgive him and prayed so that his soul rest in peace after recovering he decided to leave the hostel his things were shifted so he went to the room to see if anything is left or not soon he found a note on the table it said anuj your father got the punishment for his wrong deed now you have to focus on your aim and proceed towards it remember your father did this to see you as a topper don t disrespect his wish this will let your father s soul stay peacefully and mine too take care farewell your father s prey ronyayantika rakshit

BODY: press release21 10 2020in 1922 a bengali freedom fighter satindranath sen started a hunger strike movement in the barisal prison of the erstwhile undivided bengal in protest against the oppression of the british jailor he demanded that the political prisoners had to be treated separately from the ordinary prisoners satindranath aposs 61 day long hunger strike was the first historic movement in the colonial india which demanded the status of political prisoners in 1929 jatindranath das also started a hunger strike in the lahore central jail with the same demand his heroic strike ended in 13th september 1929 when he breathed his last after 63 days of fasting but history repeats itself and we see this when even after 73years of independence political prisoners like prof g n saibaba has had to go for the same hunger strike to protest against the ill treatment of the nagpur jail authority according to his family and the committee set up for his defence release saibaba is being denied of the books letters sent regularly by his family citing covid 19 outbreak he is also being denied of regular newspapers and phone calls to either his family or the lawyer not only that his family complained that the jail authority has not even provided the medical assistance prescribed by his doctor at the same time even after repeated request saibaba who is a 90 percent disabled wheelchair bound person has not been provided with a permanent trained helper equipped to deal with his medical needs as prescribed by the doctors at the government medical college nagpur on the other hand revolutionary poet vara vara rao who is at his 80s and is severely ill has fallen prey to the continuous negligence of the taloja jail hospital authority his family has complained that v v has been denied of necessary medical tests due to his critical condition he is presently kept on urinary catheterization but his family complained that since his urinary bag has not been changed for long he has got infected also because of the continuous neglect of his neurological problems he is totally in an incoherent state and talked about the deadbody of his wife kept in the morgue when she is very much alive we think these incidents cannot be seen simply as negligence but are a part of the cruel vindictive attitude of the indian state towards its political prisoners which can only have resemblance to our colonial past it is utterly shameful that even after the india government being a signatory of the international mandela rules the jail authorities regularly flout the basic rights of the political prisoners of our country so quite obviously political prisoners like saibaba has to take resort to a hunger strike to fight the oppressive rules of the present day indian state we see his fight for the dignity of the political prisoners as the ones which follows the legacy of our beloved freedom fighters so we stand in complete solidarity with prof saibaba and demand immidiate provision of all the necessary items as well as requisite medical assistance to him so that his life as a political prisoner is not threatened crpp w b

indigenously developed anti hail guns what are anti hail guns an anti hail gun is a machine that generates shock waves to disrupt the growth of hailstones in clouds according to its makers it comprises a tall fixed structure somewhat resembling an inverted tower several metres high with a long and narrow cone opening towards the sky the gun is fired by feeding an explosive mixture of acetylene gas and air into its lower chamber which releases a shock wave waves that travel faster than the speed of sound such as those produced by supersonic aircraft these shock waves supposedly stop water droplets in clouds from turning into hailstones so that they fall simply as raindrops answer this pyq in the comment box q during a thunderstorm the thunder in the skies is produced by themeeting of cumulonimbus clouds in the skylightning that separates the nimbus cloudsviolent upward movement of air and water particlesselect the correct option using the codes given below a 1 only b 2 and 3 only c 1 and 3 only d none of the abovehow do they prevent a hailstorm it is this hail formation process that the shock waves from anti hail guns try to disrupt in a radius of 500 meters so that the water droplets fall down before they can be lifted by the updrafts the machine is repeatedly fired every few seconds during an approaching thunderstorm however the effectiveness of anti hail guns has remained a contentious issue how do hailstorms occur hail is produced by cumulonimbus clouds which are generally large and dark and may cause thunder and lightning in such clouds winds can blow up the water droplets to heights where they freeze into ice the frozen droplets begin to fall but are soon pushed back up by the winds and more droplets freeze onto them resulting in multiple layers of ice on the hailstones this fall and rise is repeated several times till the hailstones become too heavy and fall down

soboci skimusic aneesh pradhancast aditya modak sushmita bhave ashwini kulkarni kiran yadnyopavit arun dravid and many more there are few films which can show you the reality of your boring life in a very interesting manner this film is one of them this film won the golden lion award for the best screenplay and the best film critics choice at the prestigious venice film festival which is considered as the oldest and the most prestigious among all other film festivals last film from india which won this award was mira nair s monsoon wedding long back in 2000 the plot revolves around a guy named sharad nerulkar who is very passionate and wants to make a career in indian classical music the film focuses more on his journey dilemma struggle regarding various instances in his life the plot may seem very much simple and yet it manages to entangle you in the story due to magnificent cinematography movement of the camera zooming into the lead character as he sings will show how much determination he has for his dreams this shot has been used time and time again in the movie second thing which will attract you is the slow motion shots as our lead character is riding a bike and is listening to the tap recordings of maai this particular camera work shows how much blindly and passionately he listens and follows maai s philosophy this particular one shot is trump card of the whole film the frames taken are exceptional and will enhance your visual experience after the cinematography the other positive point is the metaphorical writing in many of the shows and films we get an overview of the traditions regarding classical music but here we get that but not that much and there is a reason for it in the whole movie classical music has been used as a metaphor to anything that we are dedicated to so it is basically a life oriented movie and music has been used only as a metaphor thats why if you closely listen to maai s philosophy regarding music they are actually techniques of leading life and lastly the most important point is the sound designing in the whole movie you will get a perfect blend of digentic and non digentic sound the tanpura starts immediately when our lead character is listening to maai s philosophy and rest of the part you will hear normal and sounds now the negatives i didn t find any negatives throughout the movie but this film more individual to watch this film

android phone and there is no way to protect your device from it it doesn t matter which apps you use because the system is breached on a deeper level according to the snowden revelations from 2013 both apple and google are part of the global surveillance program that implies that these companies have to among other things implement backdoors into their mobile operating systems these backdoors usually disguised as security bugs allow us agencies to access information on any smartphone in the world the problem with such backdoors is that they are never exclusive to just one party anybody can exploit them so if a us security agency can hack an ios or android phone any other organization that uncovers the backdoors can do the same unsurprisingly this is exactly what has been taking place an israeli company called nso group has been selling access to the spying tools that allowed third parties to hack tens of thousands of phones since at least 2018 i have been aware that one of my phone numbers was included in a list of potential targets of such surveillance tools although a source from the nso group denies it personally i wasn t worried since 2011 when i was still living in russia i ve got used to assuming that all my phones were compromised anyone who gains access to my private data will be utterly disappointed they will have to go through thousands of concept designs for telegram features and millions of messages related to our product development process they won t find any important information there however these surveillance tools are also used against people far more prominent than me for example they were employed to spy on 14 heads of state the existence of backdoors in crucial infrastructure and software creates a huge challenge for humanity that s why i have been calling upon the governments of the world to start acting against the apple google duopoly in the smartphone market and to force them to open their closed ecosystems and allow for more originates from its own body from within itself another allegory to be mindful of is that of the river ganges which passes through some of the oldest cities of india intersecting lives across many languages and religions rivers are of central importance to all civilizations both ancient and contemporary they have been an immense source of inspiration to people objects of mythic fables a muse for poets and artists across cultures the ganges has a sacrosanct status for those who live around it the originator of life the washer of sins the carrier of death the poetry of this song is imbued with many facets of the human condition growing up growing old finding meaning finding hope shifting perspective and achieving enlightenment managing to self reflect on the medium of poetry itself the escalation of words mirrors the steps of strings culminating in a whirling dervish of a crescendo i hope you find this composition as helpful as i do here are the lyrics and interpretations adapted BODY: review nospoiler book the girl in room 105 an unlove storyauthor chetan bhagatpublisher westland ltd genre fictionpublishing year 2018language englishisbn 978 1542040464pages 304when you re slumping and lazily browsing through your bookshelf for a quick read a chetan bhagat book serves almost similar flavour what a smaranjit book is meant for in terms of bengali however this time he tries his hand with somewhat he loves to call fun thriller needless to say proving himself wrong in my opinion if not in mass opinion the story unfolds a rajasthani man keshav rajpurohit to fall in one sided love with a kashmiri muslim girl called zara lone the mystery sets in when one night in room 105 keshav finds her dead then the hunt for murderer begins with a juxtaposed outcome the pages are quite full with desi dialogues with a pinch of vulgar swear words random in bhagat ji novels nowadays kashmir sensitive topics terorism hint and army thing are clearly added for more promotional hype than storytelling or for the sake of plot twist i honestly think bhagat misuses his potential by writing his pieces only eying to make these spicey plot for upcoming bollywood masala flicks this one too not devoid of stock characters randomised taken for granted girl characters cheap punchlines and predictable ending thrill part is wasted while comedy part still manages to stand seriously would love something more credible coming out from him in future time alternative choice to consider rahasya samagra by shirshendu mukhopadhyaytumbaad dekhechi nirvana inn tao dekhechi ebar fobiya ta dekhte hobe review reaction review review review movie h2s team review wanda vision just finished the first 2 episodes and i can t wait for more i will never be tired from seeing elizabeth olsen and paul bettany on screen together they have a fantastic chemistry that brings their characters to life kathryn hahn also does her role well wandavision is weird and wonderful there is a strong sense of mystery and even danger by the end of each episode i ve been on the edge of my seat i crave more i really do wish that they released all the episodes together but i will not allow that to tarnish the greatness of this show after having such a long break between marvel content this is exactly what i needed to kickstart my love for the franchise again can t wait for more episodes reaction wandavision na dekhe thakle akhuni dekhun jodi apni marvel fan hon marvel fan non kintu marvel er cinema gulo dakha taholeo dekhun because mcu is going to explode puro universe ta ke onno matray niye gachhe beshi kotha bolle spoiler dewa hoye jabe tobe ajker episode tar por uttejona aro bere galo marvel er ei bold move experimentation korar amar darun lagchhe ar sitcom er sathe sci fi mystery thriller er blending ta osadharon review movie i watched dc s aquaman today and to be honest this movie doesn t deserve to be treated like this by the critics especially aquaman is dc s one of the beautiful and finest creation and above all this movie has proved what dceu can give common movie lovers this movie is outstanding most common thing in the movie was the tone of the movie as it should be dark in story but the story telling is beautifully managed and exceed all our expectation and visuals were simply jaw dropping as a story aquaman is run of the mill mixing bits of national treasure thor black panther ormwasright and green lantern in a good way into an entertaining stew but the devil is in the details and the screen is filled with delightful details easter eggs and visual gags from beginning to end save for a reference to steppenwolf this is an entirely self contained movie and even the mid credit cookie is entirely in the service of this specific franchise it is colorful funny swashbuckling ly violent big screen entertainment with a simple story providing a framework for charming characters and top notch spectacle the third act soars accordingly delivering the promised absurdist lord of the rings but underwater action and by that time we like the characters enough to give a damn momoa s arc as aquaman is solid and includes some especially thoughtful intelligent self awareness and self criticism nicole kidman s atlanna is a wonderfully developed role and the one with the strongest emotional presentation she packs so much into a relatively small number of scenes but it s such a full story and kidman brings it all to life perfectly yahya abdul mateen ii as black manta is aquaman s most hated enemy and the film really sets up their conflict perfectly giving manta a singular understandable drive also he s simply one of the coolest looking villains in comics and now he s become one of the absolutely coolest looking villains in movies patrick wilson s ocean master has a few different motives and goals and it all works well even though i d like to have seen more passionate emphasis on his sense of righteousness regarding the threat posed by the surface world dolph lundgren plays king nereus and willem dafoe plays nuidis vulko both actors delivering smart restrained performances as dignified royalty who must choose sides in an increasingly brutal and complicated conflict aquaman is more similar to wonder woman than it is to batman v superman or man of steel so yeah i got my aquaman movie i mean i got my aquaman movie the one that lived in my heart the one i yearned to see yet never really believed would ever be made aquaman is an amazing achievement in superhero cinema filled with pulse pounding action and dazzling visual effects it s indiana jones black panther avatar and pirates of the caribbean rolled into one blockbuster ball of holiday cinema thanks a lot to happy2share and mystic phoenix for sharing this movie with me my rating for this movie would be9 8 10 for character development and supporting characters 10 10 for fantastic visual effects and great imaginations9 2 10 for story and sub plotsoverall BODY: story words speak louder than actionswe have often heard people saying that actions speak louder than words but words can in some cases speak louder than actions this story tells us that we can also say the latter in mexico city there lived a boy named ethan he had an indian origin and had traveled almost every place in the world due to his father s transferrable job he was a very jolly and happy boy he was strong in both academics and athletics his mother had her own home business of bakery and he grew up watching his father go to work every morning before anyone woke up and returned after everyone slept he only knew that his father did a very reputed job on sundays he loved to spend time with his father playing games or by going on a small trip with the family life for him was very much similar every day except the fact that he met a lot of new people almost every year as he grew up he had many friends too they wanted to know about him and what his father and mother did and every time he ended saying that he did not know his father s occupation properly he felt very ashamed of himself and it was then he was determined to ask his father about it likewise he asked his father about his job his father replied that he worked in a call center despite getting the answer ethan was not satisfied with it he knew that at call centers there were shifts but one stay in one place for a long time moreover his job was transferrable that means talking to different peoples in different countries almost every year is impossible but he had no other option than to believe the same now ethan became mature and they shifted to pennsylvania the day was similar to another day but that day his father didn t come back home to the work he and his mother were extremely worried they informed the local police and filed a missing diary as well they hoped that he would return soon but days passed by and he did not return even after a week ethan and his mother searched him like mad persons then ethan decided to search for everything very minutely so he asked for the cctv footage and found his father in a very remote part of pennsylvania when they went there his father was not there ethan and his mother lost all their hopes as they also couldn t find any clues after three weeks and two days later his father came and without answering their questions he told them that now they had to go to india as soon as possible they followed his words went to the place where they actually belonged to when they reached india he revealed the biggest secret of his life he was actually a secret agent from the indian government he went to different countries to accomplish small missions but this time they had to deal with the biggest criminal of all time dudley he also told them that the mission was really hard and it took them two weeks to identify dudley s actual location but they succeeded in their mission both of the listeners were shocked they could not believe their ears they understood why some people say words speak louder than actions instead of saying actions speak louder than words ayantika rakshitbesh laglo golpo ta jai hind

BODY: story words speak louder than actionswe have often heard people saying that actions speak louder than words but words can in some cases speak louder than actions this story tells us that we can also say the latter in mexico city there lived a boy named ethan he had an indian origin and had traveled almost every place in the world due to his father s transferrable job he was a very jolly and happy boy he was strong in both academics and athletics his mother had her own home business of bakery and he grew up watching his father go to work every morning before anyone woke up and returned after everyone slept he only knew that his father did a very reputed job on sundays he loved to spend time with his father playing games or by going on a small trip with the family life for him was very much similar every day except the fact that he met a lot of new people almost every year as he grew up he had many friends too they wanted to know about him and what his father and mother did and every time he ended saying that he did not know his father s occupation properly he felt very ashamed of himself and it was then he was determined to ask his father about it likewise he asked his father about his job his father replied that he worked in a call center despite getting the answer ethan was not satisfied with it he knew that at call centers there were shifts but one stay in one place for a long time moreover his job was transferrable that means talking to different peoples in different countries almost every year is impossible but he had no other option than to believe the same now ethan became mature and they shifted to pennsylvania the day was similar to another day but that day his father didn t come back home to the work he and his mother were extremely worried they informed the local police and filed a missing diary as well they hoped that he would return soon but days passed by and he did not return even after a week ethan and his mother searched him like mad persons then ethan decided to search for everything very minutely so he asked for the cctv footage and found his father in a very remote part of pennsylvania when they went there his father was not there ethan and his mother lost all their hopes as they also couldn t find any clues after three weeks and two days later his father came and without answering their questions he told them that now they had to go to india as soon as possible they followed his words went to the place where they actually belonged to when they reached india he revealed the biggest secret of his life he was actually a secret agent from the indian government he went to different countries to accomplish small missions but this time they had to deal with the biggest criminal of all time dudley he also told them that the mission was really hard and it took them two weeks to identify dudley s actual location but they succeeded in their mission both of the listeners were shocked they could not believe their ears they understood why some people say words speak louder than actions instead of saying actions speak louder than words ayantika rakshit

BODY: review movie spoilerfreetenet don t try to understand it feel it year 2020writer director christopher nolan cinematography hoyte van hoyetemamusic ludwig g ranssoncast john david washington robert pattinson elizabeth debicki kenneth branagh dimple kapadia michael caine and many more this quoted line is from the most awaited movie of christopher nolan tenet this one line was said by a character named laura for the lead character and the audience who were just about experience the absurdness of the film and yes at first i watched the movie at one go without giving a pause just to take that experience and the second time i rewatched few parts of the movie in order to understand it and i would say i tried my best to understand the movie though that is kind of impossible yet i developed my own perception of the entire film the plot is based on an unnamed guy who is referred as the protagonist played by j d washington is recruited by a secret organisation in his afterlife which is engaged in cold war with an unknown enemy he is advised by his senior to go after andrei sator played by kenneth branagh a russian arms dealer who is involved with some rare kind of ammunition that moves backwards through his journey he is assisted by neil robert pattinson and sator s wife katharine elizabeth debicki the first positive point in this movie is the writing probably in every nolan s movie we get an overview of something absurd or beyond our imagination thing is taking place without knowing its source or the cause of why its happening like in inception we never get to know what the whole dream machine is about but we see a detailed procedure of how they get involved in each others dream in interstellar we see the lead character communicating with his daughter through the 5 dimension world but we never get an overview how this is happening but in tenet he gave the explanation of the absurdities occurring though not all but he explains the exact reason behind time reversal concept and the pincher movement but he didn t explain the concept of afterlife and the actual purpose of satore moreover the whole story being told through the perspective of the protagonist gives rise to several mysteries especially the involvement of neil remains a mystery but the ones who have watched the movie closely will know who this neil really is second great thing about this movie is the cinematography the whole time reversal action sequences is a delight to watch in the very beginning when the lead character is at the verge of being killed we see two trains passing simultaneously one in forward and the other one in backward direction which was a hint what is going to happen in the film in many of the action movies when we watch car flipping we watch it on pov shot or through distorted shots but here nolan uses a steady wide angle shot in a whole car flip scene which i must say is very very rare the editing of the movie is abrupt in few cases that is another good thing regarding this film now the negatives i personally didn t find any negatives regarding the film but there are few concepts regarding the movie which you should be familiar with not the time reversal concept but the whole occurrence of the pincher movement is the main key factor if you are the ones who hasn t seen a sci fi thriller or doesn t know about nolan s filmography or style please don t watch this film at first go for his previous films first in order to understand this one and if you want to develop a complete perception regarding this you need to watch each and every minute details and still if you cant you can refer to different blogs there is nothing shame in referring to a blog in order to understand this movie i personally referred to some them in order to find answers to my queries to me this movie another masterpiece by nolan and yes do watch it on a big screen in full hd otherwise you wont be able to experience the stunning visuals and slow motions throughout the film

BODY: as telegram approaches 500 million active users many of you are asking the question who is going to pay to support this growth after all more users mean more expenses for traffic and servers a project of our size needs at least a few hundred million dollars per year to keep going for most of telegram s history i paid for the expenses of the company from my personal savings however with its current growth telegram is on track to reach billions of users and to require appropriate funding when a tech project reaches this scale typically there are two options start earning money to cover the costs or sell the company hence the question which path will telegram take i d like to make a few points to clarify our plan 1 we are not going to sell the company like the founders of whatsapp the world needs telegram to stay independent as a place where users are respected and high quality service is ensured telegram must continue to serve the world as an example of a tech company that strives for perfection and integrity and as the sad examples of our predecessors show that is impossible if you become part of a corporation 2 telegram is here to stay for a long time we began developing our apps for our personal use over 8 years ago and have come a long way since then in the process telegram changed the way people communicate in several aspects encryption functionality simplicity design speed this journey has just started there s much more we can and will bring to the world 3 in order to make points 1 and 2 possible telegram will begin to generate revenue starting next year we will do it in accordance with our values and the pledges we have made over the last 7 years thanks to our current scale we will be able to do it in a non intrusive way most users will hardly notice any change 4 all the features that are currently free will stay free we will add some new features for business teams or power users some of these features will require more resources and will be paid for by these premium users regular users will be able to keep enjoying telegram for free forever 5 all parts of telegram devoted to messaging will remain ad free we think that displaying ads in private 1 to 1 chats or group chats is a bad idea communication between people should be free of advertising of any sort 6 in addition to its messaging component telegram has a social networking dimension our massive public one to many channels can have millions of subscribers each and are more like twitter feeds in many markets the owners of such channels display ads to earn money sometimes using third party ad platforms the ads they post look like regular messages and are often intrusive we will fix this by introducing our own ad platform for public one to many channels one that is user friendly respects privacy and allows us to cover the costs of servers and traffic 7 if telegram starts earning money the community should also benefit for example if we monetize large public one to many channels via the ad platform the owners of these channels will receive free traffic in proportion to their size or if telegram introduces premium stickers with additional expressive features the artists who make stickers of this new type will also get a part of the profit we want millions of telegram based creators and small businesses to thrive enriching the experience of all our users this is the telegram way it will allow us to keep innovating and keep growing for decades to come we will be able to launch countless new features and welcome billions of new users while doing that we will remain independent and stay true to our values redefining how a tech company should operate

BODY: reviewbook karna s wife the outcast s queenauthor kavita kanewhile mahabharata itself is an intriguing read i have to admit that the character of karna has always been the most intriguing one while on one hand we feel attached to him and his journey and on the other hand we can t help questioning him well this is just the book while making a journey through the pages we live with karna we get to understand him in a much deeper level and most importantly we get to put up the questions uruvi though a fictional character actually represents us she is karna s conscience keeper but i personally feel she represents us readers throughout the book there had been so many instances where i felt uruvi was able to read my mind and was putting forward all the questions and seeking justification for all the injustice rendered to karna there is a beautiful instance in the book where uruvi seeks justification from bhishma pitamah about the injustice he had subjected karna to for years even after knowing that he was the rightful heir of kuru clan to which bhishma replied that he had no right in claiming him as his grandson until his mother kunti recongnized him as his son in front of the society especially when the society can question her character but this yet again gives rise to the question how long shall you stay indifferent is it actually right to silently give rise to kurukshetra we also see uruvi questioning karna about his blind friendship and oath of loyalty towards duryodhana while their friendship had grown only stronger over the years yet it was this very friendship which caused the demise of karna even though he proved his loyalty till the end but could he really be a great friend what is friendship if not stopping them going to the wrong path and then again we get to a point where uruvi herself is questioned about her judgements towards karna how could she judge him when she hadn t been through a lifetime of humiliation and abandonment and a constant search of acceptance and dignity when once questioned by uruvi why do you want to fight arjuna what do you want to prove that you are a great warrior to which karna replies no a loser who wants to fight for his dignity he knew he was going towards his death a death whose dentiny was determined by the curses abandonment humiliations and his daanveerta a man with his flaws and strenghts this book is a perfect read for those who want to see the insight of karna you will feel your existence throughout the journey because uruvi isn t fictional it s the reader s voice please do give this book a try you sure will enjoy it

BODY: i had left calcutta in 1976 never went back to settle down for various reasons yes when i left calcutta it was dreadful i had to waste one year to get into college in madras because my final school result were delayed by 6 months but emotionally i love my calcutta many says calcutta has much less oppertunity than other metro i worked with abp and hence i really never lost roots and kept visiting i always saw changes during my visits since last few years many malls new restaurants huge gated community but still whenever i see paiteins in bangalore or hyderabad or madras they complain about inadequacy my friends in calcutta keeps asking about schools and colleges in south i wonder why is it other side of river always green or something else i always wanted to go back to calcutta to settle down but my kids prevented it then one of childhood friend who had settled in canada spoken bitterly about calcutta he wanted to come back but was harassed and now looking to purchase property in south then i understood one point those of us who prefer the city are always emotionally attached to it but i all practical purpose our dear state had gone back or self destroyed since 1967 what we look at the infrastructure progress which otherwise is happening everywhere and except real estate and other developments which is natural keeping with the time we lost the practical development politics is calcutta never grew from 1970 chaos every state mechinary is corrupt south is the most but they are preferred destination simply because they had been working despite being the machinery being corrupt in calcutta it is not only machinery but willingness to take it forward also got corrupted i cry in my inner sense when someone innocently ask me what actor dev got to do with davos meeting or why is that they go on rampages still in hospitals or in universities or why is that nandigram happened if we really love bengal we need to address this there are people who started business and doing well in calcutta but compare the percentage and it is only trading and service i love to settle down there as i am now retired but not before that as city of joy has long way to go to become city of opportunity like once the glorified villages like hyderabad and bangalore has become now

BODY: review movie spoilerfreedisciple indian film winning the golden lion at venice film festival after 19 years year 2020writer director chaitanya tamhaneproducer vivek gombarcinematography michal soboci skimusic aneesh pradhancast aditya modak sushmita bhave ashwini kulkarni kiran yadnyopavit arun dravid and many more there are few films which can show you the reality of your boring life in a very interesting manner this film is one of them this film won the golden lion award for the best screenplay and the best film critics choice at the prestigious venice film festival which is considered as the oldest and the most prestigious among all other film festivals last film from india which won this award was mira nair aposs monsoon wedding long back in 2000 the plot revolves around a guy named sharad nerulkar who is very passionate and wants to make a career in indian classical music the film focuses more on his journey dilemma struggle regarding various instances in his life the plot may seem very much simple and yet it manages to entangle you in the story due to magnificent cinematography movement of the camera zooming into the lead character as he sings will show how much determination he has for his dreams this shot has been used time and time again in the movie second thing which will attract you is the slow motion shots as our lead character is riding a bike and is listening to the tap recordings of maai this particular camera work shows how much blindly and passionately he listens and follows maai aposs philosophy this particular one shot is trump card of the whole film the frames taken are exceptional and will enhance your visual experience after the cinematography the other positive point is the metaphorical writing in many of the shows and films we get an overview of the traditions regarding classical music but here we get that but not that much and there is a reason for it in the whole movie classical music has been used as a metaphor to anything that we are dedicated to so it is basically a life oriented movie and music has been used only as a metaphor thats why if you closely listen to maai aposs philosophy regarding music they are actually techniques of leading life and lastly the most important point is the sound designing in the whole movie you will get a perfect blend of digentic and non digentic sound the tanpura starts immediately when our lead character is listening to maai aposs philosophy and rest of the part you will hear normal and sounds now the negatives i didn apost find any negatives throughout the movie but this film more about visual storytelling and very less dialogues so if you are not into that then this movie is not for you according to me this movie is more than a masterpiece and i will request each and every individual to watch this film

BODY: guidelinefor the first timers in prelims first attempt is the golden attempt my favourite line some of the things which i would like to share with you1 fear of forgetting everything is quite normal even for senior players don t worry about this 2 fear of not able to see any questions from what you have read till now is classic first attempt trap it happens because you are new to the preparation and your coverage of syllabus is definitely less than senior players but trust me around 60 70 questions will come from what you have read till now rest you will be able to solve with your knowledge of solving mock test 3 confusion between two options it is also faced by all whether first attempt or last pin pointed knowledge is the key here where you have pin pointed knowledge even about any single option don t change it for anything if you are confused then please try the elimination method elimination method doesn t mean some god level trick which you have learned on some youtube or telegram channel upsc is hundred steps ahead of those tricks it s the mix of wide knowledge which you have acquired during this process and basic human instinct for this i want all of you to go through previous year questions 4 chronology of revision first is the basic books then current affairs from wherever you have done it and then previous year questions and lastly test series most of the questions you will find from the basic text books then current affairs and then test series and pyq please don t rely only and only on test papers many test series will claim 70 80 90 questions
