BODY: storyher last visit one day my grandmother was sharing some of my great grandfather s experiences about some paranormal activities one of them seemed really horrifying and mysterious ghost story i don t know whether it was a real story or not but it is really interesting i will share the story with you all my great grandfather s name is manishankar mukhopadhaya but everyone in the village used to call him mani in short he was known for his bravery in his village this story revolves around 1878 when bengal witnessed a massive flood at earlier times kirtans and bhajans devotional songs used to be sung in the zamindar s resident that lasted for 7 8 days one night of the 4th day a woman who was called sarada told the landlady that she would return home as her son is alone at home and he had to leave for work tomorrow at dawn so the landlady gave sarada a plate where all kinds of bengali food were there it is often believed that if someone carries any non veg food with them at night alone then ghosts with capture them still sarada went towards home she didn t take the usual road but she unconsciously took the other way now let s come to another scene it is about my great grandfather at his time child marriage was very prevalent at those times people were not aware of the outcomes of child marriage so considering child marriage as a ritual my great grandfather married a girl of 12 years soon she was pregnant and the delivery date came after 10 months 10 days but unfortunately while delivering she and also the child who was to be born passed away so my great grandfather had to fulfill the last rites for her so that her soul can rest in peace it was that day when sarada was returning home it was also the last day of my great grandfather maintaining his wife s last rites in older times as there was no arrangement for defecating in a covered place people had to go to fields so that night he went to the fields and that time was the time when bengal faced a massive threat to life due to the disastrous flood that place was at a higher level so it didn t face any problem the only ankle dipped water level was present there during the flood he went to the place where water was present after finishing his work when he was about to head towards home he heard something he turned and saw that something was disturbing the tranquility of the standing paddy crops he thought it was some animal but the humming sound that came from didn t seem like an animal so he decided to check what it was he followed the direction in which the crops were moving the humming sound was making the eerier but whenever he headed towards the moving object in no time it changed its direction it was happening again and again so he showed his bravery and ran to block the way of the moving object suddenly the moving object stopped and stood up it was a human figure suddenly with the dim light of the moon he recognized the person and yelled the name of sarada she was all wet and was half undressed then great grandfather properly put her sari and asked what had happened suddenly sarada caught hold of him and told amake bachao baba amake bachao baba save me son save me son my great grandfather asked what had happened but she continuously asked him to save her from what from whom all remained unknown forever he took her home and handed her over to her son on asking what had happened her son just got a reply to take care of her as it was too late to explain to him great grandfather reached home and his mother enquired about him being late he told that on his way he met his friend confused that what on earth his friend was doing late night told great grandfather to wash his feet in the pond he went there and while he was washing his feet in the water he saw one girl in bengali attire was standing on the opposite side of the pond and was watching him he shouted who s there but she ran away at home when great grandfather was about to sleep and was trying to sleep

BODY: a huge number of players have been given the moniker of the next messi 14 hours ago auttymore than a dozen players have been dubbed the next messi over the years but none have ever reached the heights scaled by barcelona and argentina star lionel messi not even close arsenal are the latest club to be linked with the latest next messi iranian star sardar azmoun who is a star in russia for zenit st petersburg while last summer manchester united were said to be monitoring trabzonspor teenager abdulkadir omur the turkish messi but we all know the type and the hype that follows as soon as any young player comes through who is small quick and able to beat a man off the dribble he s dubbed the next messi double points if he s left footed the world map has almost been filled in with different next messis from around the globe from peru to south africa and japan to iran two dozen countries have produced their own version of the little genius even scotland had one while england have two here s how they got on the english messi patrick robertsburst on to the scene as a teenager at fulham and after some impressive performances as a teenager man city splashed 12million on him he barely got into the city side before a long loan spell at celtic although he won seven trophies under brendan rodgers roberts had a number of injury issues and did not hit the heights expected of him another loan spell to girona last season didn t really work out while stints at norwich and middlesbrough this term have been uninspiring mini messi fran kirbyone of the players most deserving of the tag the england and chelsea star is one of the biggest stars in the women s game kirby who stands at just 5ft 2in is a former pfa and fwa player of the year and has been a vital player in all of the lionesses recent success in december 2018 kirby was voted the 13th best player in the world in an extensive newspaper poll scottish messi ryan gauldgauld was 17 when he made his debut for dundee united and began tearing it up in scotland helping the terrors reach the scottish cup final in 2014 after being shortlisted for young player of the year gauld was snapped up by portuguese giants sporting lisbon but gauld only made two league appearances for sporting all in 2014 and early 2015 and went on four unsuccessful loan spells he s now at portuguese second tier side farense swiss messi xherdan shaqirithe messi comparisons are definitely a step too far but shaqiri now at liverpool is quite obviously a talent good enough for most teams in the world he has played at some of the biggest clubs in the world and scored at two world cups and the european championship injuries have limited his impact this season behind mohamed salah in the pecking order at the reds egyptian messi mohamed salahspeaking of whom there was a time when salah being compared to messi would have been impossible to imagine namely at chelsea now thriving at liverpool the egyptian king isn t quite at messi s level but he s pretty close this was a tag from when the forward was still at basel and in all honesty it s quite fair salah is now one of the best players in the world and will soon have players being dubbed the next salah catalan messi gerard deulofeucertainly has enough natural talent to earn comparisons to one of the best ever but the winger now at watford does not have the consistency or work rate to compare himself to messi deulofeu has struggled in two spells at barca but was instrumental to the hornets getting to the fa cup final in 2019 german messi marko marinarrived at chelsea in 2012 with a massive reputation but like so many other blues youngsters never got a fair chance at stamford bridge was sent on four loan spells in three seasons and managed just six premier league games in west london marin has since won trophies in greece spain and serbia croatian messi alen halilovicanother barcelona graduate the diminutive

BODY: review movie spoilerfreetenet don apost try to understand it feel it year 2020writer director christopher nolan cinematography hoyte van hoyetemamusic ludwig g ranssoncast john david washington robert pattinson elizabeth debicki kenneth branagh dimple kapadia michael caine and many more this quoted line is from the most awaited movie of christopher nolan tenet this one line was said by a character named laura for the lead character and the audience who were just about experience the absurdness of the film and yes at first i watched the movie at one go without giving a pause just to take that experience and the second time i rewatched few parts of the movie in order to understand it and i would say i tried my best to understand the movie though that is kind of impossible yet i developed my own perception of the entire film the plot is based on an unnamed guy who is referred as the protagonist played by j d washington is recruited by a secret organisation in his afterlife which is engaged in cold war with an unknown enemy he is advised by his senior to go after andrei sator played by kenneth branagh a russian arms dealer who is involved with some rare kind of ammunition that moves backwards through his journey he is assisted by neil robert pattinson and sator aposs wife katharine elizabeth debicki the first positive point in this movie is the writing probably in every nolan aposs movie we get an overview of something absurd or beyond our imagination thing is taking place without knowing its source or the cause of why its happening like in inception we never get to know what the whole dream machine is about but we see a detailed procedure of how they get involved in each others dream in interstellar we see the lead character communicating with his daughter through the 5 dimension world but we never get an overview how this is happening but in tenet he gave the explanation of the absurdities occurring though not all but he explains the exact reason behind time reversal concept and the pincher movement but he didn apost explain the concept of afterlife and the actual purpose of satore moreover the whole story being told through the perspective of the protagonist gives rise to several mysteries especially the involvement of neil remains a mystery but the ones who have watched the movie closely will know who this neil really is second great thing about this movie is the cinematography the whole time reversal action sequences is a delight to watch in the very beginning when the lead character is at the verge of being killed we see two trains passing simultaneously one in forward and the other one in backward direction which was a hint what is going to happen in the film in many of the action movies when we watch car flipping we watch it on pov shot or through distorted shots but here nolan uses a steady wide angle shot in a whole car flip scene which i must say is very very rare the editing of the movie is abrupt in few cases that is another good thing regarding this film now the negatives i personally didn apost find any negatives regarding the film but there are few concepts regarding the movie which you should be familiar with not the time reversal concept but the whole occurrence of the pincher movement is the main key factor if you are the ones who hasn apost seen a sci fi thriller or doesn apost know about nolan aposs filmography or style please don apost watch this film at first go for his previous films first in order to understand this one and if you want to develop a complete perception regarding this you need to watch each and every minute details and still if you cant you can refer to different blogs there is nothing shame in referring to a blog in order to understand this movie i personally referred to some them in order to find answers to my queries to me this movie another masterpiece by nolan and yes do watch it on a big screen in full hd otherwise you wont be able to experience the stunning visuals and slow motions throughout the film

death note and since he deplores the state of the world tests the deadly notebook by writing a criminal s name in it when the criminal dies immediately following his experiment with the death note light is greatly surprised and quickly recognizes how devastating the power that has fallen into his hands could be with this divine capability light decides to extinguish all criminals in order to build a new world where crime does not exist and people worship him as a god police however quickly discover that a serial killer is targeting criminals and consequently try to apprehend the culprit to do this the japanese investigators count on the assistance of the best detective in the world a young and eccentric man known only by the name of l verdict according to me it is one of the best ost original soundtrack though the animation is old but it is really good the series is available on youtube even on telegram in english hope you like it thank you p s the name of the episodes of the shape of water 2019 director guillermo del toroimdb rating 7 3 10my rating 7 10the movie starts with elisa a mute girl she lives in her humble apartment takes care of her artist neighbor before going to the marine research corp where she works as a sweeper her life isn t much colorful just like any other lower middle class working girl director paid enough effort to portray it but everything changes one day when a new asset arrives into the facility a humanoid green merman like creature from amazon our protagonist gets curious tries to communicate with the new creature feeds it and it turns out that the creature is actually intelligent enough to respond and communicate the mute unaccepted unloved elisa founds her resemblance to the creature than the humans who just treat it as a disposable lab rat a unnatural friendship starts to grow they fall in love elisa finds a meaning to her life on the other hand director of the facility decides to kill and disect the oragnism to learn more and from here everything escalates fast a russian undercover scientist elisa and her co worker zelda and elisa s artist neighbor gets into a dangerous play of extracting the creature to release it into the sea and finally in a series of jawdropping events they almost does it just before elisa and her creature gets shot following their russian alley it looks like a sad classic ending to a different kind of love story but here comes the signature of del toro he doesn t end the movie there he shows us the revival of the god like amazonian creature who gets up heals his wounds and get the revenge for elisa s death and then we re shown an alternate ending where he takes dead elisa to water and elisa starts to breathe again narrator on the background says if you ask i would say i remember a poem for elisa i didn t know the shape of you so i imgined you all around me that s the shape of water i don t know what del toro tried to show but i felt that absurd ending quite valuable for the movie it s just a ode to an unfulfilled love we know elisa dies but we wish she would be alive to live happily with her man that s where director wins the game he created a open ending that note light is greatly surprised and quickly recognizes how devastating the power that has fallen into his hands could be with this divine capability light decides to extinguish all criminals in order to build a new world where crime does not exist and people worship him as a god police however quickly discover that a serial killer is targeting criminals and consequently try to apprehend the culprit to do this the japanese investigators count on the assistance of the best detective in the world a young and eccentric man known only by the name of l verdict according to me it is one of the BODY: life of an artist while rehearsing a scene from no land s man nawazuddin siddiqui became slightly emotional but since he is extremely professional he quickly regained his composure later on i came to know the reason the scene i mentioned was between him and his sister whose reel name was saima he asked me if i knew his sister s name is saima too i answered negative as my script was written five years ago and i had no idea about his sister he then told me his sister saima has been suffering from cancer for eight years and he has been trying everything he could to help her in this battle so whenever he had scenes phone conversations with saima he was feeling extremely emotional i didn t know how to respond to this strange connection i forgot this quickly as i had other things to deal with two days ago while we were shooting a scene he received a call we had no idea what was going on he completed the scene brilliantly after we packed up i came to know he lost his sister while we were shooting that scene i have recently developed some idea about this man s attachment to his family as someone who is strongly connected to family i could completely understand how he was feeling i didn t know how to deal with this situation but he knew while coordinating everything back home he continued his shoot and made sure our new york shoot is completed he will fly home today maybe he will be standing silently in front of her grave maybe they will speak thousand words in silence maybe fiction and reality will merge into each other nolandsmanfilm

BODY: review movie spoilerfreedisciple indian film winning the golden lion at venice film festival after 19 years year 2020writer director chaitanya tamhaneproducer vivek gombarcinematography michal soboci skimusic aneesh pradhancast aditya modak sushmita bhave ashwini kulkarni kiran yadnyopavit arun dravid and many more there are few films which can show you the reality of your boring life in a very interesting manner this film is one of them this film won the golden lion award for the best screenplay and the best film critics choice at the prestigious venice film festival which is considered as the oldest and the most prestigious among all other film festivals last film from india which won this award was mira nair s monsoon wedding long back in 2000 the plot revolves around a guy named sharad nerulkar who is very passionate and wants to make a career in indian classical music the film focuses more on his journey dilemma struggle regarding various instances in his life the plot may seem very much simple and yet it manages to entangle you in the story due to magnificent cinematography movement of the camera zooming into the lead character as he sings will show how much determination he has for his dreams this shot has been used time and time again in the movie second thing which will attract you is the slow motion shots as our lead character is riding a bike and is listening to the tap recordings of maai this particular camera work shows how much blindly and passionately he listens and follows maai s philosophy this particular one shot is trump card of the whole film the frames taken are exceptional and will enhance your visual experience after the cinematography the other positive point is the metaphorical writing in many of the shows and films we get an overview of the traditions regarding classical music but here we get that but not that much and there is a reason for it in the whole movie classical music has been used as a metaphor to anything that we are dedicated to so it is basically a life oriented movie and music has been used only as a metaphor thats why if you closely listen to maai s philosophy regarding music they are actually techniques of leading life and lastly the most important point is the sound designing in the whole movie you will get a perfect blend of digentic and non digentic sound the tanpura starts immediately when our lead character is listening to maai s philosophy and rest of the part you will hear normal and sounds now the negatives i didn t find any negatives throughout the movie but this film more about visual storytelling and very less dialogues so if you are not into that then this movie is not for you according to me this movie is more than a masterpiece and i will request each and every individual to watch this film

he abuses will surely make you laugh xd and the movie also contains funny scenes and dialogues the other co actors also gave their best the storyline is also very good as in the movie a judge s daughter is killed mysteriously and manoj bajpayee as an acp officer investigates the mystery the suspense in the end is the best part of the movie and you will surely be shocked it is a must watch one time movie the only thing i didn t liked is the runtime of the movie as it is too long straight 2 hr and 16 min which for the movies nowadays is a long itme it s a mystery packed a must watch movie i willl give 7 10 sardar ka grandson movie review before i start my review please expect some unrealistic things in this movie arjun kapoor is settled in los angeles and is staying as a live in with rakulpreet singh due to some reasons they have some differences and she leaves the house arjun kapoor gets a call from his dad that his grandmother played by neena gupta is unwell in amritsar and wants her last wish of visiting her home in lahore to be fulfilled now will arjun kapoor be able to live up to her expectations and what all hurdles will he face is something you have to watch out for arjun kapoor has played his role well but needs to improve upon his comic and emotional timings where he gets a bit loud rakulpreet singh is good and has done a good job john abraham and aditi rao hydari are in brief roles and are decent kumud mishra returns after a long time in a negative role and has done good the main focus is neena gupta who has played her path well but she doesn t look 90 years even after she getting an old womans make up which too is not up to the mark the movie overall is a time pass one time watch with some things being unbelievable my rating 2 5 stars streaming on netflix run time 2 hrs 19 min reaction reviewsandeep aur pinky faraarso guys i was waiting for sandeep aur pinky faraar to come on a streaming platform for a long time now it s available on amazon prime i watched it yesterday and this is how i feel about the movie a lot of people will see arjun kapoor on the poster and will simply avoid the film but this film will break the stereotypes in your mind as this is the best work of parineeti chopra as far as i have seen watching jaydeep ahlawat act is just a delight to eyes raghubir yadav and neena gupta pradhan ji and his wife from panchayat are always brilliant arjun kapoor too has done a good job but the best part about the film is the script dibakar banerjee and varun grover came together to write this and the result is worth your time this film exposes the indian society on several fronts but it never feels like it s trying to be woke the film starts as a chase thriller but halfway through you understand that it s much bigger than that in every thriller the character arc of whether the antagonist or the protagonist is fixed but this film is layered it s a social drama cum chase thriller cum dark zoned movie when i finished this movie last night there was a smile on my face the smile you generally have after watching a really good movie i don t just recommend rather request everybody to watch this movie invite link expired BODY: review movie spoilerfreeak vs ak there is some serious problm with netflix india year 2020streaming platform netflixscreenplay and direction vikramaditya motwanecinematography swapnil sonawanecast anil kapoor anurag kashyap sonam kapoor harshvardhan kapoor bony kapoor and many more i was really excited about this film when i watched the trailer since motwane is one of my favourite directors from bollywood the plot goes like this anurag kashyap wants to make a film using real life characters where sonam kapoor gets kidnapped and anil kapoor has to find her first i want to clarify a small thing i see a lot of people complaining that here anurag kashyap and anil kapoor are playing the characters which are not relevant to them actually they are playing the character in which the audience perceive them like anurag kashyap makes very dark films so naturally the many of the people may think that he himself is a sociopath where as anil kapoor is the mainstream star so the masses may think he in real life is also like that the first positive thing about this film is this approach which belongs to the metacinema genre vikramaditya motwane a man who loves to BODY: review movie spoilerfreetenet don t try to understand it feel it year 2020writer director christopher nolan cinematography hoyte van hoyetemamusic ludwig g ranssoncast john david washington robert pattinson elizabeth debicki kenneth branagh dimple kapadia michael caine and many more this quoted line is from the most awaited movie of christopher nolan tenet this one line was said by a character named laura for the lead character and the audience who were just about experience the absurdness of the film and yes at first i watched the movie at one go without giving a pause just to take that experience and the second time i rewatched few parts of the movie in order to understand it and i would say i tried my best to understand the movie though that is kind of impossible yet i developed my own perception of the entire film the plot is based on an unnamed guy who is referred as the protagonist played by j d washington is recruited by a secret organisation in his afterlife which is engaged in cold war with an unknown enemy he is advised by his senior to go after andrei sator played by kenneth branagh a russian arms dealer who is involved with some rare kind of ammunition that moves backwards through his journey he is assisted by neil robert pattinson and sator s wife katharine elizabeth debicki the first positive point in this movie is the writing probably in every nolan s movie we get an overview of something absurd or beyond our imagination thing is taking place without knowing its source or the cause of why its happening like in inception we never get to know what the whole dream machine is about but we see a detailed procedure of how they get involved in each others dream in interstellar we see the lead character communicating with his daughter through the 5 dimension world but we never get an overview how this is happening but in tenet he gave the explanation of the absurdities occurring though not all but he explains the exact reason behind time reversal concept and the pincher movement but he didn t explain the concept of afterlife and the actual purpose of satore moreover the whole story being told through the perspective of the protagonist gives rise to several mysteries especially the involvement of neil remains a mystery but the ones who have watched the movie closely will know who this neil really is second great thing about this movie is the cinematography the whole time reversal action sequences is a delight to watch in the very beginning when the lead character is at the verge of being killed we see two trains passing simultaneously one in forward and the other one in backward direction which was a hint what is going to happen in the film in many of the action movies when we watch car flipping we watch it on pov shot or through distorted shots but here nolan uses a steady wide angle shot in a whole car flip scene which i must say is very very rare the editing of the movie is abrupt in few cases that is another good thing regarding this film now the negatives i personally didn t find any negatives regarding the film but there are few concepts regarding the movie which you should be familiar with not the time reversal concept but the whole occurrence of the pincher movement is the main key factor if you are the ones who hasn t seen a sci fi thriller or doesn t know about nolan s filmography or style please don t watch this film at first go for his previous films first in order to understand this one and if you want to develop a complete perception regarding this you need to watch each and every minute details and still if you cant you can refer to different blogs there is nothing shame in referring to a blog in order to understand this movie i personally referred to some them in order to find answers to my queries to me this movie another masterpiece by nolan and yes do watch it on a big screen in full hd otherwise you wont be able to experience the stunning visuals and slow motions throughout the film

BODY: this month we have verified and promoted 17 official news sources representing ministries of health in 17 countries the constantly growing list is available in corona we did this as part of our anti covid19 initiative announced in early april while telegram is not exactly famous for cooperating with government officials we decided to make one exception globally to help spread information about the virus the current pandemic is a threat to our entire species when it ends the world will not return to normal we may witness a civilizational shift that will ripple through generations it is up to all of us to ensure that the new world about to be born is a better place than the one we re leaving behind this is a chance for people to use their time in isolation to create a better version of themselves and a chance for technology to prove its worth for humanity i believe we at telegram should do all we can not only to help contain the pandemic and combat the spread of unverified information but also to find new ways of moving forwards for this reason in addition to providing informational support we ll try to contribute to tackling the problem of education under lockdown we also have several other anti covid19 projects in the works at telegram i will announce more details in the next few days on the telegram blog stay tuned and stay safe 40 4 1 40 4 3 750 7 500

BODY: as telegram approaches 500 million active users many of you are asking the question who is going to pay to support this growth after all more users mean more expenses for traffic and servers a project of our size needs at least a few hundred million dollars per year to keep going for most of telegram s history i paid for the expenses of the company from my personal savings however with its current growth telegram is on track to reach billions of users and to require appropriate funding when a tech project reaches this scale typically there are two options start earning money to cover the costs or sell the company hence the question which path will telegram take i d like to make a few points to clarify our plan 1 we are not going to sell the company like the founders of whatsapp the world needs telegram to stay independent as a place where users are respected and high quality service is ensured telegram must continue to serve the world as an example of a tech company that strives for perfection and integrity and as the sad examples of our predecessors show that is impossible if you become part of a corporation 2 telegram is here to stay for a long time we began developing our apps for our personal use over 8 years ago and have come a long way since then in the process telegram changed the way people communicate in several aspects encryption functionality simplicity design speed this journey has just started there s much more we can and will bring to the world 3 in order to make points 1 and 2 possible telegram will begin to generate revenue starting next year we will do it in accordance with our values and the pledges we have made over the last 7 years thanks to our current scale we will be able to do it in a non intrusive way most users will hardly notice any change 4 all the features that are currently free will stay free we will add some new features for business teams or power users some of these features will require more resources and will be paid for by these premium users regular users will be able to keep enjoying telegram for free forever 5 all parts of telegram devoted to messaging will remain ad free we think that displaying ads in private 1 to 1 chats or group chats is a bad idea communication between people should be free of advertising of any sort 6 in addition to its messaging component telegram has a social networking dimension our massive public one to many channels can have millions of subscribers each and are more like twitter feeds in many markets the owners of such channels display ads to earn money sometimes using third party ad platforms the ads they post look like regular messages and are often intrusive we will fix this by introducing our own ad platform for public one to many channels one that is user friendly respects privacy and allows us to cover the costs of servers and traffic 7 if telegram starts earning money the community should also benefit for example if we monetize large public one to many channels via the ad platform the owners of these channels will receive free traffic in proportion to their size or if telegram introduces premium stickers with additional expressive features the artists who make stickers of this new type will also get a part of the profit we want millions of telegram based creators and small businesses to thrive enriching the experience of all our users this is the telegram way it will allow us to keep innovating and keep growing for decades to come we will be able to launch countless new features and welcome billions of new users while doing that we will remain independent and stay true to our values redefining how a tech company should operate

BODY: guidelinefor the first timers in prelims first attempt is the golden attempt my favourite line some of the things which i would like to share with you1 fear of forgetting everything is quite normal even for senior players don t worry about this 2 fear of not able to see any questions from what you have read till now is classic first attempt trap it happens because you are new to the preparation and your coverage of syllabus is definitely less than senior players but trust me around 60 70 questions will come from what you have read till now rest you will be able to solve with your knowledge of solving mock test 3 confusion between two options it is also faced by all whether first attempt or last pin pointed knowledge is the key here where you have pin pointed knowledge even about any single option don t change it for anything if you are confused then please try the elimination method elimination method doesn t mean some god level trick which you have learned on some youtube or telegram channel upsc is hundred steps ahead of those tricks it s the mix of wide knowledge which you have acquired during this process and basic human instinct for this i want all of you to go through previous year questions 4 chronology of revision first is the basic books then current affairs from wherever you have done it and then previous year questions and lastly test series most of the questions you will find from the basic text books then current affairs and then test series and pyq please don t rely only and only on test papers many test series will claim 70 80 90 questions but if you will check their questions you will like i am not fool test papers might help you in polity geography and history but not in other sections 5 now you must have the balanced confidence of clearing the prelims irrespective of your marks in mock or any test this is the key to get into prelims under and over confidence both can ruin your chance of prelims 6 you can t judge whether paper is simple or tough you are not having that much experience therefore please don t limit your attempt or exceed on the basis of paper attempt according to your pre decided plan 7 increase your reading speed toughness of the paper since 2018 also accompany with increased length of the papers it takes time to read full paper therefore you must solve mock test in 1 5 hrs instead of 2 hrs 8 one famous movie 3 idiots had one famous character chaturramalingam free mock in the last week is golden trap and they re using that funda of churan students how to remove competition either by increasing the performance of your team or make others feel demotivated this is what many institute do especially two big institute they resort to second option because first require efforts i know this from personal experience toppers will get 178 180 marks and you struggle for even 100 marks your marks are like 42 52 52 72 etc if you go for deep analysis then you will find questions were framed for not to get corrected avoid giving any free free mock now please depend on pyq for next week

BODY: press release21 10 2020in 1922 a bengali freedom fighter satindranath sen started a hunger strike movement in the barisal prison of the erstwhile undivided bengal in protest against the oppression of the british jailor he demanded that the political prisoners had to be treated separately from the ordinary prisoners satindranath s 61 day long hunger strike was the first historic movement in the colonial india which demanded the status of political prisoners in 1929 jatindranath das also started a hunger strike in the lahore central jail with the same demand his heroic strike ended in 13th september 1929 when he breathed his last after 63 days of fasting but history repeats itself and we see this when even after 73years of independence political prisoners like prof g n saibaba has had to go for the same hunger strike to protest against the ill treatment of the nagpur jail authority according to his family and the committee set up for his defence release saibaba is being denied of the books letters sent regularly by his family citing covid 19 outbreak he is also being denied of regular newspapers and phone calls to either his family or the lawyer not only that his family complained that the jail authority has not even provided the medical assistance prescribed by his doctor at the same time even after repeated request saibaba who is a 90 percent disabled wheelchair bound person has not been provided with a permanent trained helper equipped to deal with his medical needs as prescribed by the doctors at the government medical college nagpur on the other hand revolutionary poet vara vara rao who is at his 80s and is severely ill has fallen prey to the continuous negligence of the taloja jail hospital authority his family has complained that v v has been denied of necessary medical tests due to his critical condition he is presently kept on urinary catheterization but his family complained that since his urinary bag has not been changed for long he has got infected also because of the continuous neglect of his neurological problems he is totally in an incoherent state and talked about the deadbody of his wife kept in the morgue when she is very much alive we think these incidents cannot be seen simply as negligence but are a part of the cruel vindictive attitude of the indian state towards its political prisoners which can only have resemblance to our colonial past it is utterly shameful that even after the india government being a signatory of the international mandela rules the jail authorities regularly flout the basic rights of the political prisoners of our country so quite obviously political prisoners like saibaba has to take resort to a hunger strike to fight the oppressive rules of the present day indian state we see his fight for the dignity of the political prisoners as the ones which follows the legacy of our beloved freedom fighters so we stand in complete solidarity with prof saibaba and demand immidiate provision of all the necessary items as well as requisite medical assistance to him so that his life as a political prisoner is not threatened crpp w b

BODY: spolieralert movieexplained dracula sir movie explanationp s film ta na dekha thakle poroborti lekha gulo porben na film ta agay dekhun karon akhane onk spoilers ache ami sompurno nijer motamot ta dichchi ami film ta dekhe ki bujhlm sei byapare karur bhinno motamot thakle amr kono osubidhe nei jekono action k justify korar jonno amra ekta story ba medium er sahajjo ni jemon ekti criminal je crime korche seta k justify korar jonno tar ekta backstory thake onk somoy seta shotti hoy abar onk somoy mithye kintu ei ekta story tar kache ek dhoroner freedom of expression jeta k banglay motoprokasher sadhinota bole ai khetre o tai gota amol er story ta raktim er kache ek dhoner freedom of expression nijeke justify korar jonno ata k ami jatishwar bolbo na tar karon holo amol shome akhono beche ache jeta amra seshe a dekhlm school er mashtermoshai tai holo ashol amol shome r jatishwar tokhoni shombhob jokhon kono ekti manush mara jache se jodi nai morlo punor jonom hobe ki kore r punor jonom jodi nai hoi tahole jatishwar hobe ki kore freedom of expression ta k amra gota film jure nanan bhabe suppressed hote dekhi jmon real life a ekti sikhikito doctor konodino bolbe na ekti BODY: if you think you know about humanity you don t know humanity in 1974 yugoslavian performance artist marina abramovic dared to conduct a terrifying experiment to examine how people think many people have hailed abramovic as the grandmother of performance art after all she has been staging thought provoking interactive installations for more than 40 years indeed it can t be denied that her performances have a lasting impact in fact one of her earliest performances is still being talked about today abramovic staged a performance piece called rhythm 0 at studio morra in naples italy the premise of rhythm 0 was deceptively simple abramovic would stand still for six hours straight while the people who came to see her were urged to do whatever they wanted to her using one of 72 objects that she had placed on a table abramovic stood in the middle of the room with a notice board containing these words instructions there are 72 objects on the table that one can use on me as desired performance i am the object during this period i take full responsibility duration 6 hours 8 pm 2 am what happened in the next six hours was horrifying to say the least it began tamely someone turned her around someone thrust her arms into the air someone touched her somewhat intimately in the third hour all her clothes were cut from her with razor blades in the fourth hour the same blades began to explore her skin various minor sexual assaults were carried out on her body she was so committed to the piece that she would not have resisted rape or murder it just got worse in the last two hours abramovic s own account of what the people did to her was even more heartbreaking she recalled i felt raped they cut off the clothes they stuck me with thorns of rose in the stomach aimed the gun to my head another came apart when the six hours were over abramovic started to walk among the people they couldn t look her in the face abramovic observed that people didn t want any sort of confrontation with her they didn t want to be held accountable or judged for what they did it seemed as if they wanted to forget how they relished hurting her this work reveals something terrible about humanity it shows how fast a person can hurt you under favorable circumstances it shows that if he provides the stage the majority of normal people apparently can become truly violent that is the grammar of anarchy collected

BODY: review movie spoilerfreetenet don apost try to understand it feel it year 2020writer director christopher nolan cinematography hoyte van hoyetemamusic ludwig g ranssoncast john david washington robert pattinson elizabeth debicki kenneth branagh dimple kapadia michael caine and many more this quoted line is from the most awaited movie of christopher nolan tenet this one line was said by a character named laura for the lead character and the audience who were just about experience the absurdness of the film and yes at first i watched the movie at one go without giving a pause just to take that experience and the second time i rewatched few parts of the movie in order to understand it and i would say i tried my best to understand the movie though that is kind of impossible yet i developed my own perception of the entire film the plot is based on an unnamed guy who is referred as the protagonist played by j d washington is recruited by a secret organisation in his afterlife which is engaged in cold war with an unknown enemy he is advised by his senior to go after andrei sator played by kenneth branagh a russian arms dealer who is involved with some rare kind of ammunition that moves backwards through his journey he is assisted by neil robert pattinson and sator aposs wife katharine elizabeth debicki the first positive point in this movie is the writing probably in every nolan aposs movie we get an overview of something absurd or beyond our imagination thing is taking place without knowing its source or the cause of why its happening like in inception we never get to know what the whole dream machine is about but we see a detailed procedure of how they get involved in each others dream in interstellar we see the lead character communicating with his daughter through the 5 dimension world but we never get an overview how this is happening but in tenet he gave the explanation of the absurdities occurring though not all but he explains the exact reason behind time reversal concept and the pincher movement but he didn apost explain the concept of afterlife and the actual purpose of satore moreover the whole story being told through the perspective of the protagonist gives rise to several mysteries especially the involvement of neil remains a mystery but the ones who have watched the movie closely will know who this neil really is second great thing about this movie is the cinematography the whole time reversal action sequences is a delight to watch in the very beginning when the lead character is at the verge of being killed we see two trains passing simultaneously one in forward and the other one in backward direction which was a hint what is going to happen in the film in many of the action movies when we watch car flipping we watch it on pov shot or through distorted shots but here nolan uses a steady wide angle shot in a whole car flip scene which i must say is very very rare the editing of the movie is abrupt in few cases that is another good thing regarding this film now the negatives i personally didn apost find any negatives regarding the film but there are few concepts regarding the movie which you should be familiar with not the time reversal concept but the whole occurrence of the pincher movement is the main key factor if you are the ones who hasn apost seen a sci fi thriller or doesn apost know about nolan aposs filmography or style please don apost watch this film at first go for his previous films first in order to understand this one and if you want to develop a complete perception regarding this you need to watch each and every minute details and still if you cant you can refer to different blogs there is nothing shame in referring to a blog in order to understand this movie i personally referred to some them in order to find answers to my queries to me this movie another masterpiece by nolan and yes do watch it on a big screen in full hd otherwise you wont be able to experience the stunning visuals and slow motions throughout the film

BODY: dorohedoro type tvsource mangastatus finished airinggenres action comedy horror magic fantasy seinenepisodes 12duration 23 min per epscore 8 23studio s mappapremiered winter 2020rating r 17 violence profanity hole a dark decrepit and disorderly district where the strong prey on the weak and death is an ordinary occurrence is all but befitting of the name given to it a realm separated from law and ethics it is a testing ground to the magic users who dominate it as a race occupying the highest rungs of their society the magic users think of the denizens of hole as no more than insects murdered mutilated and made experiments without a second thought the powerless hole dwellers litter the halls of hole s hospital on a daily basis possessing free access to and from the cesspool and with little challenge to their authority the magic users appear indomitable to most aside for a few kaiman more reptile than man is one such individual he hunts them on a heedless quest for answers with only a trusted pair of bayonets and his immunity to magic cursed by his appearance and tormented by nightmares magic users are his only clue to restoring his life to normal with his biggest obstacle being his stomach his female companion nikaidou who runs the restaurant hungry bug is his greatest ally set in a gritty world of hellish design dorohedoro manages a healthy blend of comedy and lightheartedness with death and carnage taking plenty of twists and turns while following the lives of hole s residents it weaves a unique world of unearthly origin and dreary appearance not for the squeamish or easily disturbed written by mal rewrite

BODY: review animereview 1 death notesynopsis a shinigami as a god of death can kill any person provided they see their victim s face and write their victim s name in a notebook called a death note one day ryuk bored by the shinigami lifestyle and interested in seeing how a human would use a death note drops one into the human realm high school student and prodigy light yagami stumbles upon the death note and since he deplores the state of the world tests the deadly notebook by writing a criminal s name in it when the criminal dies immediately following his experiment with the death note light is greatly surprised and quickly recognizes how devastating the power that has fallen into his hands could be with this divine capability light decides to extinguish all criminals in order to build a new world where crime does not exist and people worship him as a god police however quickly discover that a serial killer is targeting criminals and consequently try to apprehend the culprit to do this the japanese investigators count on the assistance of the best detective in the world a young and eccentric man known only by the name of l verdict according to me it is one of the best psychological thriller i have ever seen the writer of the story tsugumi ohba had done a great job of questioning morality and the story stands to its point of what is justice and that it is referential he has also done a great job of portraying and building the characters in the story the story has many twists and turns that will make your mind boggle the world building in this story is also quite good the pacing of the story is good though you may feel the pacing of the story slow in the middle but over all the pacing of the story is really good illustrator takeshi obata had done a great job in drawing the manga comics and it was marvelously adapted into anime by studio madhouse in to an series consisting of 37 episodes each of 20 24 mins the series has really good sound effects ost original soundtrack though the animation is old but it is really good the series is available on youtube even on telegram in english hope you like it thank you p s the name of the episodes of the series are as follows 1 rebirth 2 confrontation3 dealings4 pursuit5 tactics6 unraveling7 overcast8 glare9 encounter10 doubt11 assault12 love13 confession14 friend15 wager16 decision17 execution18 ally19 matsuda20 makeshift21 performance22 guidance23 frenzy24 revival25 silence26 renewal27 abduction28 impatience29 father30 justice31 transfer32 selection33 scorn34 vigilance35 malice36 1 2837 new e tc telecom communication or mca candidate should have passed out qualifying course in 2018 19 without any backlog candidate passing out in 2020 and meeting the criteria also stand eligible should have scored min of 60 in scc 10th hsc 12th diploma in case done and be b tech mca not more than 1 year gap since ssc and that too not after joining a course means no loss of academic year after joining a course other details selection process candidates shortlisted from the registered list will be called for an aptitude test english essay story tech test technical and hr interview with each of these acting as filter for next stage on selection process candidate holding certifications like ocp mcp aws rpa sap coursera in credit mode edx in credit mode etc would be given preference note the entire selection process may be completed on the same day in exceptional circumstances for reasons beyond our control part of the selection process may happen on subsequent days you may be prepared for such eventuality test and interview schedule eligible candidates will be communicated the test and interview schedule over mail minimum 1 week prior to the date of test and interview bond and compensation on selection candidate will be on probation for 6 months with a ctc of inr 2 6 l annum on completion of probation candidate will be offered a ctc of inr 3 25 l annum candidate will read happy2share diary volume 1 clicking here escape velocity founder happy2share review animereview 1 death notesynopsis a shinigami as a god of death can kill any person provided they see their victim s face and write their victim s name in a notebook called a death note one day ryuk bored by the shinigami lifestyle and interested in seeing how a human would use a death note drops one into the human realm high school student and prodigy light yagami stumbles upon the death note and since he deplores the state of the world tests the deadly notebook by writing a criminal s name in it when the criminal dies immediately following his experiment with the death note light is greatly surprised and quickly recognizes how devastating the power that has fallen into his hands could be with this divine capability light decides to extinguish all criminals in order to build a new world where crime does not exist and people worship him as a god police however quickly discover that a serial killer is targeting criminals and consequently try to apprehend the culprit to do this the japanese investigators count on the assistance of the best detective in the world a young and eccentric man known only by the name of l verdict according to me it is one of the best psychological thriller i have ever seen the writer of the story tsugumi ohba had done a great job of questioning morality and BODY: press release21 10 2020in 1922 a bengali freedom fighter satindranath sen started a hunger strike movement in the barisal prison of the erstwhile undivided bengal in protest against the oppression of the british jailor he demanded that the political prisoners had to be treated separately from the ordinary prisoners satindranath aposs 61 day long hunger strike was the first historic movement in the colonial india which demanded the status of political prisoners in 1929 jatindranath das also started a hunger strike in the lahore central jail with the same demand his heroic strike ended in 13th september 1929 when he breathed his last after 63 days of fasting but history repeats itself and we see this when even after 73years of independence political prisoners like prof g n saibaba has had to go for the same hunger strike to protest against the ill treatment of the nagpur jail authority according to his family and the committee set up for his defence release saibaba is being denied of the books letters sent regularly by his family citing covid 19 outbreak he is also being denied of regular newspapers and phone calls to either his family or the lawyer not only that his family complained that the jail authority has not even provided the medical assistance prescribed by his doctor at the same time even after repeated request saibaba who is a 90 percent disabled wheelchair bound person has not been provided with a permanent trained helper equipped to deal with his medical needs as prescribed by the doctors at the government medical college nagpur on the other hand revolutionary poet vara vara rao who is at his 80s and is severely ill has fallen prey to the continuous negligence of the taloja jail hospital authority his family has complained that v v has been denied of necessary medical tests due to his critical condition he is presently kept on urinary catheterization but his family complained that since his urinary bag has not been changed for long he has got infected also because of the continuous neglect of his neurological problems he is totally in an incoherent state and talked about the deadbody of his wife kept in the morgue when she is very much alive we think these incidents cannot be seen simply as negligence but are a part of the cruel vindictive attitude of the indian state towards its political prisoners which can only have resemblance to our colonial past it is utterly shameful that even after the india government being a signatory of the international mandela rules the jail authorities regularly flout the basic rights of the political prisoners of our country so quite obviously political prisoners like saibaba has to take resort to a hunger strike to fight the oppressive rules of the present day indian state we see his fight for the dignity of the political prisoners as the ones which follows the legacy of our beloved freedom fighters so we stand in complete solidarity with prof saibaba and demand immidiate provision of all the necessary items as well as requisite medical assistance to him so that his life as a political prisoner is not threatened crpp w b

gores were just unputdownable the camera is awesome there are very beautiful wide shots of everywhere even from the indoor ones the editing is just apt specially the fight scenes near the climax the editing techniques soothe our eyes and lastly i want to mention the role of richard jenkins as the over aged chief deputy officer who stole all the scenes specially eating soup promising avenge etc BODY: every few decades there is a drastic change in how we view important societal and scientific problems what used to be a ridiculous idea yesterday can become the predominant opinion today only to turn into an obsolete notion tomorrow in the history of human beliefs change is the only constant most people living in 1921 shared views that today are considered quaint at best and dangerous at worst the chances that our present day convictions will remain relevant by 2121 are slim in fact we won t even have to wait 100 years as the speed of change is accelerating a good example is how quickly humanity changed its mind over the origins of covid just a year ago the idea that the virus originated from a wuhan lab was dismissed as a conspiracy theory facebook twitter and other social media platforms blocked posts promoting the lab leak theory today however this theory is on its way to becoming the mainstream scientific view of how the virus originated such instances make combating fake news and misinformation particularly challenging they can also fundamentally undermine people s trust in the neutrality of social media platforms and jeopardize future efforts to fight misinformation telegram never blocked posts discussing the lab leak theory because we didn t think it s our role to decide for our users what they should believe at the same time we felt that our users had the right to be informed about covid by official sources that reflected scientific consensus that s why we worked with 19 governments to help them reach out to every telegram user in their countries with up to date information on the pandemic today we call upon more governments to join the telegram anti covid initiative to make sure more people around the world get access critical knowledge that can save lives in my 20 years of managing discussion platforms i noticed that conspiracy theories only strengthen each time their content is removed by moderators instead of putting an end to wrong ideas censorship often makes it harder to fight them that s why spreading the truth will always be a more efficient strategy than engaging in censorship

BODY: this month we have verified and promoted 17 official news sources representing ministries of health in 17 countries the constantly growing list is available in corona we did this as part of our anti covid19 initiative announced in early april while telegram is not exactly famous for cooperating with government officials we decided to make one exception globally to help spread information about the virus the current pandemic is a threat to our entire species when it ends the world will not return to normal we may witness a civilizational shift that will ripple through generations it is up to all of us to ensure that the new world about to be born is a better place than the one we aposre leaving behind this is a chance for people to use their time in isolation to create a better version of themselves and a chance for technology to prove its worth for humanity i believe we at telegram should do all we can not only to help contain the pandemic and combat the spread of unverified information but also to find new ways of moving forwards for this reason in addition to providing informational support we ll try to contribute to tackling the problem of education under lockdown we also have several other anti covid19 projects in the works at telegram i will announce more details in the next few days on the telegram blog stay tuned and stay safe 40 4 1 40 4 3 750 7 500

BODY: tech mahindra off campus for 2018 19 batch registrations would remain open till 10th marchacademic eligibility qualifying courses be b tech comp science comp engineering it e c e tc telecom communication or mca candidate should have passed out qualifying course in 2018 19 without any backlog candidate passing out in 2020 and meeting the criteria also stand eligible should have scored min of 60 in scc 10th hsc 12th diploma in case done and be b tech mca not more than 1 year gap since ssc and that too not after joining a course means no loss of academic year after joining a course other details selection process candidates shortlisted from the registered list will be called for an aptitude test english essay story tech test technical and hr interview with each of these acting as filter for next stage on selection process candidate holding certifications like ocp mcp aws rpa sap coursera in credit mode edx in credit mode etc would be given preference note the entire selection process may be completed on the same day in exceptional circumstances for reasons beyond our control part of the selection process may happen on subsequent days you may be prepared for such eventuality test and interview schedule eligible candidates will be communicated the test and interview schedule over mail minimum 1 week prior to the date of test and interview bond and compensation on selection candidate will be on probation for 6 months with a ctc of inr 2 6 l annum on completion of probation candidate will be offered a ctc of inr 3 25 l annum candidate will have to sign an indemnity bond for inr 1 l for a mandatory period of service of 2 years from date of joining the companynote during probation candidate may undergo unit specific classroom training on the job training shadowing all as per the business requirement work place timings candidate should be willing to work at any of the techm development center or client locations spread across country globe in any projects including development application support and maintenance testing managed services etc as per the company specified work timings including shift working joining location anywhere in india apply here https registration techmahindra com

BODY: film review logan 2017 spoiler alert synopsis the movie starts with an advanced era in 2029 few old x men like wolverine huge jackman freind caliban stephen merchant and prof x patrick steward are still living thogh they are struggling for existing and adapting in advanced world meanwhile scientific experiments are going on illegally to form genetically mutant children gabriela lopez a former nurse managed to escape from there with laura dafine keen an 11 year old girl after 1st meeting gabriela offered logan aka wolverine and introduced the girl to be her child though after first invasion with donald pierce boyd holbrook and his team the girl was shown to be a similar power as wolverine with higher healing later it was revealed that she was actually made through the dna of wolverine and charles reminded him also and told him to look care of charles is attacked by the gang of pierce but saved by paralyzing temporarily when logan and laura killed those imposter rushing from the hotel they met a family in the way the three finally reached in their home for safe abode but this time charles is attcked again by x 24 a clone of logan and expired a skirmish is experienced between logan and his clone and logan abled to escaped being wonded severly after checked up from a doctor laura urges first time to lgan to drive toward north dacota after a little dilemma lagan agrees to move there to prove that place is not eden as written in comic after reaching there laura finally met with her mutant friends who takes care wonded logan but pierce and his team finds the place also the final encounter occures between logan and little mutant with team pierce finally those mutantant children able to abolish pierce through their special enhanced power though logan was severly wonded in the hand of x 24 laura uses adamantium bullet to finish x 24 finally near death logan can just told to laura not to uses weapon in life better try to piece all around and dies piecefully in her arm with her tearful eyes reviewfirst of all the factor makes difference from other x men movies though i have watched 3 4 of them is the approach this is not hero adoration movie or not only showing the power of some advanced people over the commonman rather it enlightens the pain of being supernatural the everydays fight of them of being normal its very dark approched movie it consists barely any laughter incident though the plots and storytelling engaged the spectetors every moment the movie shows advanced ara of 2029 but shows society with slow but considerable changes with todays world the diractor james mangold shows it with perfect tone but the main gem is the acting department hugh jackman was outstanding in one word to his character none other can be imagined as the charcter the way he potrays his pain his anger and his feeling is just inpackable patrick also shows justice as an old tired dependend x man who always believes in better world the main attract of the movie is dafine as laura she did truely a magneficent job in almost 2 3 rd of the film she did not talk a single world when she did we all shocked her expression towards her rage was expressed in remarkable way last but not the least the movie tells an inner tone according to me the people advances to his age is always resistanced by his society the way they deals with make the difference feeling towards a man is the biggest weapon logan s last word toward his daughter reminds us again not an war only peace can make a better society a better world p s thanks to another asgardian for providing the goldmine and also thanks team happy2share to suggest me to write a review this is my first review of a film it may contain some error please ignore it

BODY: dorohedoro type tvsource mangastatus finished airinggenres action comedy horror magic fantasy seinenepisodes 12duration 23 min per epscore 8 23studio s mappapremiered winter 2020rating r 17 violence profanity hole a dark decrepit and disorderly district where the strong prey on the weak and death is an ordinary occurrence is all but befitting of the name given to it a realm separated from law and ethics it is a testing ground to the magic users who dominate it as a race occupying the highest rungs of their society the magic users think of the denizens of hole as no more than insects murdered mutilated and made experiments without a second thought the powerless hole dwellers litter the halls of hole aposs hospital on a daily basis possessing free access to and from the cesspool and with little challenge to their authority the magic users appear indomitable to most aside for a few kaiman more reptile than man is one such individual he hunts them on a heedless quest for answers with only a trusted pair of bayonets and his immunity to magic cursed by his appearance and tormented by nightmares magic users are his only clue to restoring his life to normal with his biggest obstacle being his stomach his female companion nikaidou who runs the restaurant hungry bug is his greatest ally set in a gritty world of hellish design dorohedoro manages a healthy blend of comedy and lightheartedness with death and carnage taking plenty of twists and turns while following the lives of hole aposs residents it weaves a unique world of unearthly origin and dreary appearance not for the squeamish or easily disturbed written by mal rewrite

BODY: if you think you know about humanity you don t know humanity in 1974 yugoslavian performance artist marina abramovic dared to conduct a terrifying experiment to examine how people think many people have hailed abramovic as the grandmother of performance art after all she has been staging thought provoking interactive installations for more than 40 years indeed it can t be denied that her performances have a lasting impact in fact one of her earliest performances is still being talked about today abramovic staged a performance piece called rhythm 0 at studio morra in naples italy the premise of rhythm 0 was deceptively simple abramovic would stand still for six hours straight while the people who came to see her were urged to do whatever they wanted to her using one of 72 objects that she had placed on a table abramovic stood in the middle of the room with a notice board containing these words instructions there are 72 objects on the table that one can use on me as desired performance i am the object during this period i take full responsibility duration 6 hours 8 pm 2 am what happened in the next six hours was horrifying to say the least it began tamely someone turned her around someone thrust her arms into the air someone touched her somewhat intimately in the third hour all her clothes were cut from her with razor blades in the fourth hour the same blades began to explore her skin various minor sexual assaults were carried out on her body she was so committed to the piece that she would not have resisted rape or murder it just got worse in the last two hours abramovic s own account of what the people did to her was even more heartbreaking she recalled i felt raped they cut off the clothes they stuck me with thorns of rose in the stomach aimed the gun to my head another came apart when the six hours were over abramovic started to walk among the people they couldn t look her in the face abramovic observed that people didn t want any sort of confrontation with her they didn t want to be held accountable or judged for what they did it seemed as if they wanted to forget how they relished hurting her this work reveals something terrible about humanity it shows how fast a person can hurt you under favorable circumstances it shows that if he provides the stage the majority of normal people apparently can become truly violent that is the grammar of anarchy

BODY: the new york times uncovered that apple is involved in large scale surveillance and censorship at the behest of china it is sad but not surprising big tech companies often choose profits over freedoms apple is very efficient at pursuing their business model which is based on selling overpriced obsolete hardware to customers locked in their ecosystem every time i have to use an iphone to test our ios app i feel like i m thrown back into the middle ages the iphone s 60hz displays can t compete with the 120hz displays of modern android phones that support much smoother animations the worst part of apple s tech though is not clunkier devices or outdated hardware owning an iphone makes you a digital slave of apple you are only allowed to use apps that apple lets you install via their app store and you can only use apple s icloud to natively back up your data it s no wonder that apple s totalitarian approach is so appreciated by the communist party of china which thanks to apple now has complete control over the apps and data of all its citizens who rely on iphones

BODY: reviewbook karna s wife the outcast s queenauthor kavita kanewhile mahabharata itself is an intriguing read i have to admit that the character of karna has always been the most intriguing one while on one hand we feel attached to him and his journey and on the other hand we can t help questioning him well this is just the book while making a journey through the pages we live with karna we get to understand him in a much deeper level and most importantly we get to put up the questions uruvi though a fictional character actually represents us she is karna s conscience keeper but i personally feel she represents us readers throughout the book there had been so many instances where i felt uruvi was able to read my mind and was putting forward all the questions and seeking justification for all the injustice rendered to karna there is a beautiful instance in the book where uruvi seeks justification from bhishma pitamah about the injustice he had subjected karna to for years even after knowing that he was the rightful heir of kuru clan to which bhishma replied that he had no right in claiming him as his grandson until his mother kunti recongnized him as his son in front of the society especially when the society can question her character but this yet again gives rise to the question how long shall you stay indifferent is it actually right to silently give rise to kurukshetra we also see uruvi questioning karna about his blind friendship and oath of loyalty towards duryodhana while their friendship had grown only stronger over the years yet it was this very friendship which caused the demise of karna even though he proved his loyalty till the end but could he really be a great friend what is friendship if not stopping them going to the wrong path and then again we get to a point where uruvi herself is questioned about her judgements towards karna how could she judge him when she hadn t been through a lifetime of humiliation and abandonment and a constant search of acceptance and dignity when once questioned by uruvi why do you want to fight arjuna what do you want to prove that you are a great warrior to which karna replies no a loser who wants to fight for his dignity he knew he was going towards his death a death whose dentiny was determined by the curses abandonment humiliations and his daanveerta a man with his flaws and strenghts this book is a perfect read for those who want to see the insight of karna you will feel your existence throughout the journey because uruvi isn t fictional it s the reader s voice please do give this book a try you sure will enjoy it

is a musk deer known for its strong perfumed smell the core of the message is this metaphor of the heart as a musk deer the deer keeps looking for the source of the fragrance without realizing that it originates from its own body from within itself another allegory to be mindful of is that of the river ganges which passes through some of the oldest cities of india intersecting lives across many languages and religions rivers are of central importance to all civilizations both ancient and contemporary they have been an immense source of inspiration to people objects of mythic fables a muse for poets and artists across cultures the ganges has a sacrosanct status for those who live around it the originator of life the washer of sins the carrier of death the poetry of this song is imbued with many facets of the human condition growing up growing old finding meaning finding hope shifting perspective and achieving enlightenment managing to self reflect on the medium of poetry itself the escalation of words mirrors the steps of strings culminating in a whirling dervish of a crescendo i hope you find this composition as helpful as i do here are the lyrics and interpretations adapted BODY: i had left calcutta in 1976 never went back to settle down for various reasons yes when i left calcutta it was dreadful i had to waste one year to get into college in madras because my final school result were delayed by 6 months but emotionally i love my calcutta many says calcutta has much less oppertunity than other metro i worked with abp and hence i really never lost roots and kept visiting i always saw changes during my visits since last few years many malls new restaurants huge gated community but still whenever i see paiteins in bangalore or hyderabad or madras they complain about inadequacy my friends in calcutta keeps asking about schools and colleges in south i wonder why is it other side of river always green or something else i always wanted to go back to calcutta to settle down but my kids prevented it then one of childhood friend who had settled in canada spoken bitterly about calcutta he wanted to come back but was harassed and now looking to purchase property in south then i understood one point those of us who prefer the city are always emotionally attached to it but i all practical purpose our dear state had gone back or self destroyed since 1967 what we look at the infrastructure progress which otherwise is happening everywhere and except real estate and other developments which is natural keeping with the time we lost the practical development politics is calcutta never grew from 1970 chaos every state mechinary is corrupt south is the most but they are preferred destination simply because they had been working despite being the machinery being corrupt in calcutta it is not only machinery but willingness to take it forward also got corrupted i cry in my inner sense when someone innocently ask me what actor dev got to do with davos meeting or why is that they go on rampages still in hospitals or in universities or why is that nandigram happened if we really love bengal we need to address this there are people who started business and doing well in calcutta but compare the percentage and it is only trading and service i love to settle down there as i am now retired but not before that as city of joy has long way to go to become city of opportunity like once the glorified villages like hyderabad and bangalore has become now
