BODY: guidelinefor the first timers in prelims first attempt is the golden attempt my favourite line some of the things which i would like to share with you1 fear of forgetting everything is quite normal even for senior players don t worry about this 2 fear of not able to see any questions from what you have read till now is classic first attempt trap it happens because you are new to the preparation and your coverage of syllabus is definitely less than senior players but trust me around 60 70 questions will come from what you have read till now rest you will be able to solve with your knowledge of solving mock test 3 confusion between two options it is also faced by all whether first attempt or last pin pointed knowledge is the key here where you have pin pointed knowledge even about any single option don t change it for anything if you are confused then please try the elimination method elimination method doesn t mean some god level trick which you have learned on some youtube or telegram channel upsc is hundred steps ahead of those tricks it s the mix of wide knowledge which you have acquired during this process and basic human instinct for this i want all of you to go through previous year questions 4 chronology of revision first is the basic books then current affairs from wherever you have done it and then previous year questions and lastly test series most of the questions you will find from the basic text books then current affairs and then test series and pyq please don t rely only and only on test papers many test series will claim 70 80 90 questions but if you will check their questions you will like i am not fool test papers might help you in polity geography and history but not in other sections 5 now you must have the balanced confidence of clearing the prelims irrespective of your marks in mock or any test this is the key to get into prelims under and over confidence both can ruin your chance of prelims 6 you can t judge whether paper is simple or tough you are not having that much experience therefore please don t limit your attempt or exceed on the basis of paper attempt according to your pre decided plan 7 increase your reading speed toughness of the paper since 2018 also accompany with increased length of the papers it takes time to read full paper therefore you must solve mock test in 1 5 hrs instead of 2 hrs 8 one famous movie 3 idiots had one famous character chaturramalingam free mock in the last week is golden trap and they re using that funda of churan students how to remove competition either by increasing the performance of your team or make others feel demotivated this is what many institute do especially two big institute they resort to second option because first require efforts i know this from personal experience toppers will get 178 180 marks and you struggle for even 100 marks your marks are like 42 52 52 72 etc if you go for deep analysis then you will find questions were framed for not to get corrected avoid giving any free free mock now please depend on pyq for next week

BODY: press release21 10 2020in 1922 a bengali freedom fighter satindranath sen started a hunger strike movement in the barisal prison of the erstwhile undivided bengal in protest against the oppression of the british jailor he demanded that the political prisoners had to be treated separately from the ordinary prisoners satindranath s 61 day long hunger strike was the first historic movement in the colonial india which demanded the status of political prisoners in 1929 jatindranath das also started a hunger strike in the lahore central jail with the same demand his heroic strike ended in 13th september 1929 when he breathed his last after 63 days of fasting but history repeats itself and we see this when even after 73years of independence political prisoners like prof g n saibaba has had to go for the same hunger strike to protest against the ill treatment of the nagpur jail authority according to his family and the committee set up for his defence release saibaba is being denied of the books letters sent regularly by his family citing covid 19 outbreak he is also being denied of regular newspapers and phone calls to either his family or the lawyer not only that his family complained that the jail authority has not even provided the medical assistance prescribed by his doctor at the same time even after repeated request saibaba who is a 90 percent disabled wheelchair bound person has not been provided with a permanent trained helper equipped to deal with his medical needs as prescribed by the doctors at the government medical college nagpur on the other hand revolutionary poet vara vara rao who is at his 80s and is severely ill has fallen prey to the continuous negligence of the taloja jail hospital authority his family has complained that v v has been denied of necessary medical tests due to his critical condition he is presently kept on urinary catheterization but his family complained that since his urinary bag has not been changed for long he has got infected also because of the continuous neglect of his neurological problems he is totally in an incoherent state and talked about the deadbody of his wife kept in the morgue when she is very much alive we think these incidents cannot be seen simply as negligence but are a part of the cruel vindictive attitude of the indian state towards its political prisoners which can only have resemblance to our colonial past it is utterly shameful that even after the india government being a signatory of the international mandela rules the jail authorities regularly flout the basic rights of the political prisoners of our country so quite obviously political prisoners like saibaba has to take resort to a hunger strike to fight the oppressive rules of the present day indian state we see his fight for the dignity of the political prisoners as the ones which follows the legacy of our beloved freedom fighters so we stand in complete solidarity with prof saibaba and demand immidiate provision of all the necessary items as well as requisite medical assistance to him so that his life as a political prisoner is not threatened crpp w b

BODY: storyher last visit one day my grandmother was sharing some of my great grandfather s experiences about some paranormal activities one of them seemed really horrifying and mysterious ghost story i don t know whether it was a real story or not but it is really interesting i will share the story with you all my great grandfather s name is manishankar mukhopadhaya but everyone in the village used to call him mani in short he was known for his bravery in his village this story revolves around 1878 when bengal witnessed a massive flood at earlier times kirtans and bhajans devotional songs used to be sung in the zamindar s resident that lasted for 7 8 days one night of the 4th day a woman who was called sarada told the landlady that she would return home as her son is alone at home and he had to leave for work tomorrow at dawn so the landlady gave sarada a plate where all kinds of bengali food were there it is often believed that if someone carries any non veg food with them at night alone then ghosts with capture them still sarada went towards home she didn t take the usual road but she unconsciously took the other way now let s come to another scene it is about my great grandfather at his time child marriage was very prevalent at those times people were not aware of the outcomes of child marriage so considering child marriage as a ritual my great grandfather married a girl of 12 years soon she was pregnant and the delivery date came after 10 months 10 days but unfortunately while delivering she and also the child who was to be born passed away so my great grandfather had to fulfill the last rites for her so that her soul can rest in peace it was that day when sarada was returning home it was also the last day of my great grandfather maintaining his wife s last rites in older times as there was no arrangement for defecating in a covered place people had to go to fields so that night he went to the fields and that time was the time when bengal faced a massive threat to life due to the disastrous flood that place was at a higher level so it didn t face any problem the only ankle dipped water level was present there during the flood he went to the place where water was present after finishing his work when he was about to head towards home he heard something he turned and saw that something was disturbing the tranquility of the standing paddy crops he thought it was some animal but the humming sound that came from didn t seem like an animal so he decided to check what it was he followed the direction in which the crops were moving the humming sound was making the eerier but whenever he headed towards the moving object in no time it changed its direction it was happening again and again so he showed his bravery and ran to block the way of the moving object suddenly the moving object stopped and stood up it was a human figure suddenly with the dim light of the moon he recognized the person and yelled the name of sarada she was all wet and was half undressed then great grandfather properly put her sari and asked what had happened suddenly sarada caught hold of him and told amake bachao baba amake bachao baba save me son save me son my great grandfather asked what had happened but she continuously asked him to save her from what from whom all remained unknown forever he took her home and handed her over to her son on asking what had happened her son just got a reply to take care of her as it was too late to explain to him great grandfather reached home and his mother enquired about him being late he told that on his way he met his friend confused that what on earth his friend was doing late night told great grandfather to wash his feet in the pond he went there and while he was washing his feet in the water he saw one girl in bengali attire was standing on the opposite side of the pond and was watching him he shouted who s there but she ran away at home when great grandfather was about to sleep and was trying to sleep

they are pushing myth 1 telegram s code is not open source in reality all telegram client apps have been open source since 2013 2 our encryption and api are fully documented and have been reviewed by security experts thousands of times moreover telegram is the only messaging app in the world that has verifiable builds both for ios and android 3 as for whatsapp they intentionally obfuscate their code making it impossible to verify their encryption and privacy myth 2 telegram is russian in fact telegram has no servers or offices in russia and was blocked there from 2018 to 2020 4 telegram is still blocked in some authoritarian countries such as iran while whatsapp and other supposedly secure apps have never had any issue in these places myth 3 telegram is not encrypted every chat on encryption for a few years and then adopted an encryption protocol funded by the us government 6 even if we assume that the whatsapp encryption is solid it s invalidated via multiple backdoors and reliance on backups 7 in 2019 alone facebook spent almost 10 billion dollars on marketing 8 i guess this includes paid bots on wikipedia and other sites unlike facebook telegram doesn apost spend any BODY: story your father s preyanuj had gone on a holiday for one month and when he returns he turned the key in the lock and opens the door to his horror he finds someone staring at him and then suddenly there was a loud crack of thunder he saw that one boy who looked exactly the same as anuj jumped out of the balcony before we move further let us start from the beginning anuj is a college student who is the second boy of his college in calcutta he stayed in the hostel of that college he had a small vacation of durga puja so he went to his home to spend some time with his loved ones and end his boredom but unfortunately his father who was the professor of anuj s college died of a strange disease that could not be cured by any medicines or therapy he was already not mentally peaceful and this incident happened when he returned to the hostel he turned the key to his room it was a stormy night there was a load shedding so he took a torch in his hand his roommate and his best friend rony who was the first boy the college didn t come yet so he had to stay alone for some days when he entered the room he saw a boy who looked like him jumped out of the balcony he was horrified he didn t enter his room rather he rushed to the security guard anand but when anand examined the room balcony he saw everything was at their places then anuj calmed down his mind and entered the room he thought it was his hallucination after his mournful holidays he always had suffocation in that room after that incident he couldn t sleep he was losing his concentration on studies and was gradually attacked by insomnia so he asked his hostel s superintendent ajay to shift his room ajay said yes that s a big problem but you should try to overcome it there is one room vacant but you know that it is locked by your father before his death and it should not be opened as instructed by him but anuj refused to listen he asked ajay to give him the keys and took his belongings to that room the slowly settled in that room and could now sleep peacefully one hectic day he came to his room and threw his body on the bed and slowly went to sleep he had a dreadful dream and woke up he saw all his belongings scattered here and there he closed his eyes and thought maybe he himself had done it and now he will have to keep the things at their proper places he didn t want to get up he wished if rony was there when anuj opened his eyes and saw two human feet in front of him he stood up and what he saw was really horrifying a boy was hanging from the fan seeing this his voice choked he couldn t keep himself standing and fainted when he opened his eyes he saw he was in the hospital ajay was the first man to meet him he said see what happened to you i told you not to stay in that room anuj asked why that incident took place with him why he saw all this and why his father forbidden anyone to stay in that room ajay said your father wanted you to be the first student of this college so he made rony stay here for some days and he was promised that he get extra holidays but who knew his holidays will be forever your father murdered rony and hanged him in that room so that everyone thinks that he committed suicide saying so he broke into tears anuj didn t say a single word he called the police and the police arrested ajay anuj s face became red with anger and grief with tears he asked his friend to forgive him and prayed so that his soul rest in peace after recovering he decided to leave the hostel his things were shifted so he went to the room to see if anything is left or not soon he found a note on the table it said anuj your father got the punishment for his wrong deed now you have to focus on your aim and proceed towards it remember your father did this to see you as a topper don t disrespect his wish this will let your father s soul stay peacefully and mine too take care farewell your father s prey ronyayantika rakshit

BODY: press release21 10 2020in 1922 a bengali freedom fighter satindranath sen started a hunger strike movement in the barisal prison of the erstwhile undivided bengal in protest against the oppression of the british jailor he demanded that the political prisoners had to be treated separately from the ordinary prisoners satindranath aposs 61 day long hunger strike was the first historic movement in the colonial india which demanded the status of political prisoners in 1929 jatindranath das also started a hunger strike in the lahore central jail with the same demand his heroic strike ended in 13th september 1929 when he breathed his last after 63 days of fasting but history repeats itself and we see this when even after 73years of independence political prisoners like prof g n saibaba has had to go for the same hunger strike to protest against the ill treatment of the nagpur jail authority according to his family and the committee set up for his defence release saibaba is being denied of the books letters sent regularly by his family citing covid 19 outbreak he is also being denied of regular newspapers and phone calls to either his family or the lawyer not only that his family complained that the jail authority has not even provided the medical assistance prescribed by his doctor at the same time even after repeated request saibaba who is a 90 percent disabled wheelchair bound person has not been provided with a permanent trained helper equipped to deal with his medical needs as prescribed by the doctors at the government medical college nagpur on the other hand revolutionary poet vara vara rao who is at his 80s and is severely ill has fallen prey to the continuous negligence of the taloja jail hospital authority his family has complained that v v has been denied of necessary medical tests due to his critical condition he is presently kept on urinary catheterization but his family complained that since his urinary bag has not been changed for long he has got infected also because of the continuous neglect of his neurological problems he is totally in an incoherent state and talked about the deadbody of his wife kept in the morgue when she is very much alive we think these incidents cannot be seen simply as negligence but are a part of the cruel vindictive attitude of the indian state towards its political prisoners which can only have resemblance to our colonial past it is utterly shameful that even after the india government being a signatory of the international mandela rules the jail authorities regularly flout the basic rights of the political prisoners of our country so quite obviously political prisoners like saibaba has to take resort to a hunger strike to fight the oppressive rules of the present day indian state we see his fight for the dignity of the political prisoners as the ones which follows the legacy of our beloved freedom fighters so we stand in complete solidarity with prof saibaba and demand immidiate BODY: i hear facebook has an entire department devoted to figuring out why telegram is so popular imagine dozens of employees working on just that full time i am happy to save facebook tens of millions of dollars and give away our secret for free respect your users millions of people are outraged by the latest change in whatsapp terms which now say users must feed all their private data to facebook s ad engine it s no surprise that the flight of users from whatsapp to telegram already ongoing for a few years has accelerated at about 500 million users and growing telegram has become a major problem for the facebook corporation unable to compete with telegram in quality and privacy facebook s whatsapp seems to have switched to covert marketing wikipedia editors have recently exposed multiple paid bots adding biased information into the whatsapp wikipedia article 1 we have also detected bots which spread inaccurate information about telegram on social media here are the 3 myths they are pushing myth 1 telegram s code is not open source in reality all telegram client apps have been open source since 2013 2 our encryption and api are fully documented and have been reviewed by security experts thousands of times moreover telegram is the only messaging app in the world that has verifiable builds both for ios and android 3 as for whatsapp they intentionally obfuscate their code making it impossible to verify their encryption and privacy myth 2 telegram is russian in fact telegram has no servers or offices in russia and was blocked there from 2018 to 2020 4 telegram is still blocked in some authoritarian countries such as iran while whatsapp and other supposedly secure apps have never had any issue in these places myth 3 telegram is not encrypted every chat on telegram has been encrypted since launch we have secret chats that are end to end and cloud chats that also offer real time secure and distributed cloud storage 5 whatsapp on the other hand had zero encryption for a few years and then adopted an encryption protocol funded by the us government 6 even if we assume that the whatsapp encryption is solid it s invalidated via multiple backdoors and reliance on backups 7 in 2019 alone facebook spent almost 10 billion dollars on marketing 8 i guess this includes paid bots on wikipedia and other sites unlike facebook telegram doesn t spend any money let alone billions of dollars on marketing we believe that people are smart enough to choose what is best for them and judging by the half a billion people using telegram this belief is BODY: a huge asteroid that is estimated to be three times larger than the empire state building is expected to fly by earth tonight according to nasa the asteroid is traveling at a speed of seven miles per second and will be coming very close to earth but is still expected to safely pass our planet without incident however the agency said that they are keeping a close eye on the asteroid and have classified it as potentially hazardous because it would certainly cause some damage if it struck the earth somewhere luckily all projections have indicated that the rock will pass within 3 8 million miles of earth this may sound like a long distance but considering the vastness of space this is a little bit too close for comfort according to nasa any space object that comes within 120 million miles of earth is considered a near earth object according to nasa s neo tracker site which tracks space objects the asteroid that is scheduled to pass by the planet named 1997 bq will make its approach to our planet at 9 45 pm bst on may 21 these types of objects come close to our orbit more often than people believe in fact space is filled with asteroids and similar objects and they pass by us on a routine basis there are even many asteroids that do enter our atmosphere but either disintegrate before they hit the ground or are so small that they don t do any serious damage

facebook s ad engine 1 it s no surprise that the flight of users from whatsapp to telegram already ongoing for a few years has accelerated at about 500 million users and growing telegram has become a major problem for the facebook corporation unable to compete with telegram in quality and privacy facebook s whatsapp seems to have switched to covert marketing wikipedia editors have recently exposed multiple paid bots adding biased information into the whatsapp wikipedia article 2 we have also detected bots which spread inaccurate information about telegram on social media here are the 3 myths they are pushing myth 1 telegram s code is not open source in reality all telegram client apps have been open source since 2013 3 our encryption and api are fully documented and have been reviewed by security experts thousands of times moreover telegram is the only messaging app in the world that has verifiable builds both for ios and android 4 as for whatsapp they intentionally obfuscate their code making it impossible to verify their encryption and privacy myth 2 telegram is russian in fact telegram has no servers or offices in russia and was blocked there from 2018 to 2020 5 telegram is still blocked in some authoritarian countries such as iran while whatsapp and other supposedly secure apps have never had any issue in these places myth 3 telegram is not encrypted every chat on telegram has been encrypted since launch we have secret chats that are end to end and cloud chats that also offer real time secure and distributed cloud storage 6 whatsapp on the other hand had zero encryption for a few years and then adopted an encryption protocol funded by the us government 7 even if we assume that the whatsapp encryption is solid it s invalidated via multiple backdoors and reliance on backups 8 in 2019 alone facebook spent almost 10 billion dollars on marketing 9 i guess this includes paid bots on wikipedia and other sites unlike facebook telegram doesn apost spend any BODY: story your father s preyanuj had gone on a holiday for one month and when he returns he turned the key in the lock and opens the door to his horror he finds someone staring at him and then suddenly there was a loud crack of thunder he saw that one boy who looked exactly the same as anuj jumped out of the balcony before we move further let us start from the beginning anuj is a college student who is the second boy of his college in calcutta he stayed in the hostel of that college he had a small vacation of durga puja so he went to his home to spend some time with his loved ones and end his boredom but unfortunately his father who was the professor of anuj s college died of a strange disease that could not be cured by any medicines or therapy he was already not mentally peaceful and this incident happened when he returned to the hostel he turned the key to his room it was a stormy night there was a load shedding so he took a torch in his hand his roommate and his best friend rony who was the first boy the college didn t come yet so he had to stay alone for some days when he entered the room he saw a boy who looked like him jumped out of the balcony he was horrified he didn t enter his room rather he rushed to the security guard anand but when anand examined the room balcony he saw everything was at their places then anuj calmed down his mind and entered the room he thought it was his hallucination after his mournful holidays he always had suffocation in that room after that incident he couldn t sleep he was losing his concentration on studies and was gradually attacked by insomnia so he asked his hostel s superintendent ajay to shift his room ajay said yes that s a big problem but you should try to overcome it there is one room vacant but you know that it is locked by your father before his death and it should not be opened as instructed by him but anuj refused to listen he asked ajay to give him the keys and took his belongings to that room the slowly settled in that room and could now sleep peacefully one hectic day he came to his room and threw his body on the bed and slowly went to sleep he had a dreadful dream and woke up he saw all his belongings scattered here and there he closed his eyes and thought maybe he himself had done it and now he will have to keep the things at their proper places he didn t want to get up he wished if rony was there when anuj opened his eyes and saw two human feet in front of him he stood up and what he saw was really horrifying a boy was hanging from the fan seeing this his voice choked he couldn t keep himself standing and fainted when he opened his eyes he saw he was in the hospital ajay was the first man to meet him he said see what happened to you i told you not to stay in that room anuj asked why that incident took place with him why he saw all this and why his father forbidden anyone to stay in that room ajay said your father wanted you to be the first student of this college so he made rony stay here for some days and he was promised that he get extra holidays but who knew his holidays will be forever your father murdered rony and hanged him in that room so that everyone thinks that he committed suicide saying so he broke into tears anuj didn t say a single word he called the police and the police arrested ajay anuj s face became red with anger and grief with tears he asked his friend to forgive him and prayed so that his soul rest in peace after recovering he decided to leave the hostel his things were shifted so he went to the room to see if anything is left or not soon he found a note on the table it said anuj your father got the punishment for his wrong deed now you have to focus on your aim and proceed towards it remember your father did this to see you as a topper don t disrespect his wish this will let your father s soul stay peacefully and mine too take care farewell your father s prey ronyayantika rakshitei story ta ekdom amar imagination diye lekha

BODY: i hear facebook has an entire department devoted to figuring out why telegram is so popular imagine dozens of employees working on just that full time i am happy to save facebook tens of millions of dollars and give away our secret for free respect your users millions of people are outraged by the latest change in whatsapp terms which now say users must feed all their private data to facebook s ad engine 1 it s no surprise that the flight of users from whatsapp to telegram already ongoing for a few years has accelerated at about 500 million users and growing telegram has become a major problem for the facebook corporation unable to compete with telegram in quality and privacy facebook s whatsapp seems to have switched to covert marketing wikipedia editors have recently exposed multiple paid bots adding biased information into the whatsapp wikipedia article 2 we have also detected bots which spread inaccurate information about telegram on social media here are the 3 myths they are pushing myth 1 telegram s code is not open source in reality all telegram client apps have been open source since 2013 3 our encryption and api are fully documented and have been reviewed by security experts thousands of times moreover telegram is the only messaging app in the world that has verifiable builds both for ios and android 4 as for whatsapp they intentionally obfuscate their code making it impossible to verify their encryption and privacy myth 2 telegram is russian in fact telegram has no servers or offices in russia and was blocked there from 2018 to 2020 5 telegram is still blocked in some authoritarian countries such as iran while whatsapp and other supposedly secure apps have never had any issue in these places myth 3 telegram is not encrypted every chat on telegram has been encrypted since launch we have secret chats that are end to end and cloud chats that also offer real time secure and distributed cloud storage 6 whatsapp on the other hand had zero encryption for a few years and then adopted an encryption protocol funded by the us government 7 even if we assume that the whatsapp encryption is solid it s invalidated via multiple backdoors and reliance on backups 8 in 2019 alone facebook spent almost 10 billion dollars on marketing 9 i guess this includes paid bots on wikipedia and other sites unlike facebook telegram doesn t spend any money let alone billions of dollars on marketing we believe that people are smart enough to choose what is best for them and judging by the half a billion people using telegram this belief is BODY: review movie spoilerfreetenet don t try to understand it feel it year 2020writer director christopher nolan cinematography hoyte van hoyetemamusic ludwig g ranssoncast john david washington robert pattinson elizabeth debicki kenneth branagh dimple kapadia michael caine and many more this quoted line is from the most awaited movie of christopher nolan tenet this one line was said by a character named laura for the lead character and the audience who were just about experience the absurdness of the film and yes at first i watched the movie at one go without giving a pause just to take that experience and the second time i rewatched few parts of the movie in order to understand it and i would say i tried my best to understand the movie though that is kind of impossible yet i developed my own perception of the entire film the plot is based on an unnamed guy who is referred as the protagonist played by j d washington is recruited by a secret organisation in his afterlife which is engaged in cold war with an unknown enemy he is advised by his senior to go after andrei sator played by kenneth branagh a russian arms dealer who is involved with some rare kind of ammunition that moves backwards through his journey he is assisted by neil robert pattinson and sator s wife katharine elizabeth debicki the first positive point in this movie is the writing probably in every nolan s movie we get an overview of something absurd or beyond our imagination thing is taking place without knowing its source or the cause of why its happening like in inception we never get to know what the whole dream machine is about but we see a detailed procedure of how they get involved in each others dream in interstellar we see the lead character communicating with his daughter through the 5 dimension world but we never get an overview how this is happening but in tenet he gave the explanation of the absurdities occurring though not all but he explains the exact reason behind time reversal concept and the pincher movement but he didn t explain the concept of afterlife and the actual purpose of satore moreover the whole story being told through the perspective of the protagonist gives rise to several mysteries especially the involvement of neil remains a mystery but the ones who have watched the movie closely will know who this neil really is second great thing about this movie is the cinematography the whole time reversal action sequences is a delight to watch in the very beginning when the lead character is at the verge of being killed we see two trains passing simultaneously one in forward and the other one in backward direction which was a hint what is going to happen in the film in many of the action movies when we watch car flipping we watch it on pov shot or through distorted shots but here nolan uses a steady wide angle shot in a whole car flip scene which i must say is very very rare the editing of the movie is abrupt in few cases that is another good thing regarding this film now the negatives i personally didn t find any negatives regarding the film but there are few concepts regarding the movie which you should be familiar with not the time reversal concept but the whole occurrence of the pincher movement is the main key factor if you are the ones who hasn t seen a sci fi thriller or doesn t know about nolan s filmography or style please don t watch this film at first go for his previous films first in order to understand this one and if you want to develop a complete perception regarding this you need to watch each and every minute details and still if you cant you can refer to different blogs there is nothing shame in referring to a blog in order to understand this movie i personally referred to some them in order to find answers to my queries to me this movie another masterpiece by nolan and yes do watch it on a big screen in full hd otherwise you wont be able to experience the stunning visuals and slow motions throughout the film

BODY: souravsourav in bengali means a damn good scent it s pronounced showw rauve when properly pronounced it brings out the hidden and deepest of baritones in a man and the sheer sweetness of voice in the woman and when you reach the second syllable you love it because it sounds so sensual and you know that you are in love with your own voice that s just the start but imagine if you love yourself when you say the name how can you not continue try saying it before reading a common name i admit but each person is unique a burning rage inside and kindness in his eyes form such a dynamic balance that you might want to be there and see his both sides he know one thing thats respect and he fears none at a date he ll probably stare at you in such a way that you d feel blessed a bit flirty for sure he is not your average chump he is old fashioned the scent his name personifies might be that damp musky scent with more than a hint of sweat after a hard day s work women die for or the smell of old vinyls classic barbershops or sawdust a sourav cares for his family but he is a bit hot headed at times he is eternally curious and helpful to the t he is a keeper but on the hindsight once gone he is hard to get a rare breed i tell youin bengali they say golaper sourav bhenshe asche kemon matano ekta gondho it translates to i am getting drunk in that beautiful scent of the rose you may or may not date a sourav in your life but if you find one hold him close

BODY: as telegram approaches 500 million active users many of you are asking the question who is going to pay to support this growth after all more users mean more expenses for traffic and servers a project of our size needs at least a few hundred million dollars per year to keep going for most of telegram s history i paid for the expenses of the company from my personal savings however with its current growth telegram is on track to reach billions of users and to require appropriate funding when a tech project reaches this scale typically there are two options start earning money to cover the costs or sell the company hence the question which path will telegram take i d like to make a few points to clarify our plan 1 we are not going to sell the company like the founders of whatsapp the world needs telegram to stay independent as a place where users are respected and high quality service is ensured telegram must continue to serve the world as an example of a tech company that strives for perfection and integrity and as the sad examples of our predecessors show that is impossible if you become part of a corporation 2 telegram is here to stay for a long time we began developing our apps for our personal use over 8 years ago and have come a long way since then in the process telegram changed the way people communicate in several aspects encryption functionality simplicity design speed this journey has just started there s much more we can and will bring to the world 3 in order to make points 1 and 2 possible telegram will begin to generate revenue starting next year we will do it in accordance with our values and the pledges we have made over the last 7 years thanks to our current scale we will be able to do it in a non intrusive way most users will hardly notice any change 4 all the features that are currently free will stay free we will add some new features for business teams or power users some of these features will require more resources and will be paid for by these premium users regular users will be able to keep enjoying telegram for free forever 5 all parts of telegram devoted to messaging will remain ad free we think that displaying ads in private 1 to 1 chats or group chats is a bad idea communication between people should be free of advertising of any sort 6 in addition to its messaging component telegram has a social networking dimension our massive public one to many channels can have millions of subscribers each and are more like twitter feeds in many markets the owners of such channels display ads to earn money sometimes using third party ad platforms the ads they post look like regular messages and are often intrusive we will fix this by introducing our own ad platform for public one to many channels one that is user friendly respects privacy and allows us to cover the costs of servers and traffic 7 if telegram starts earning money the community should also benefit for example if we monetize large public one to many channels via the ad platform the owners of these channels will receive free traffic in proportion to their size or if telegram introduces premium stickers with additional expressive features the artists who make stickers of this new type will also get a part of the profit we want millions of telegram based creators and small businesses to thrive enriching the experience of all our users this is the telegram way it will allow us to keep innovating and keep growing for decades to come we will be able to launch countless new features and welcome billions of new users while doing that we will remain independent and stay true to our values redefining how a tech company should operate

BODY: reviewbook karna s wife the outcast s queenauthor kavita kanewhile mahabharata itself is an intriguing read i have to admit that the character of karna has always been the most intriguing one while on one hand we feel attached to him and his journey and on the other hand we can t help questioning him well this is just the book while making a journey through the pages we live with karna we get to understand him in a much deeper level and most importantly we get to put up the questions uruvi though a fictional character actually represents us she is karna s conscience keeper but i personally feel she represents us readers throughout the book there had been so many instances where i felt uruvi was able to read my mind and was putting forward all the questions and seeking justification for all the injustice rendered to karna there is a beautiful instance in the book where uruvi seeks justification from bhishma pitamah about the injustice he had subjected karna to for years even after knowing that he was the rightful heir of kuru clan to which bhishma replied that he had no right in claiming him as his grandson until his mother kunti recongnized him as his son in front of the society especially when the society can question her character but this yet again gives rise to the question how long shall you stay indifferent is it actually right to silently give rise to kurukshetra we also see uruvi questioning karna about his blind friendship and oath of loyalty towards duryodhana while their friendship had grown only stronger over the years yet it was this very friendship which caused the demise of karna even though he proved his loyalty till the end but could he really be a great friend what is friendship if not stopping them going to the wrong path and then again we get to a point where uruvi herself is questioned about her judgements towards karna how could she judge him when she hadn t been through a lifetime of humiliation and abandonment and a constant search of acceptance and dignity when once questioned by uruvi why do you want to fight arjuna what do you want to prove that you are a great warrior to which karna replies no a loser who wants to fight for his dignity he knew he was going towards his death a death whose dentiny was determined by the curses abandonment humiliations and his daanveerta a man with his flaws and strenghts this book is a perfect read for those who want to see the insight of karna you will feel your existence throughout the journey because uruvi isn t fictional it s the reader s voice please do give this book a try you sure will enjoy it

BODY: souravsourav in bengali means a damn good scent it aposs pronounced showw rauve when properly pronounced it brings out the hidden and deepest of baritones in a man and the sheer sweetness of voice in the woman and when you reach the second syllable you love it because it sounds so sensual and you know that you are in love with your own voice that aposs just the start but imagine if you love yourself when you say the name how can you not continue try saying it before reading a common name i admit but each person is unique a burning rage inside and kindness in his eyes form such a dynamic balance that you might want to be there and see his both sides he know one thing thats respect and he fears none at a date he aposll probably stare at you in such a way that you aposd feel blessed a bit flirty for sure he is not your average chump he is old fashioned the scent his name personifies might be that damp musky scent with more than a hint of sweat after a hard day aposs work women die for or the smell of old vinyls classic barbershops or sawdust a sourav cares for his family but he is a bit hot headed at times he is eternally curious and helpful to the t he is a keeper but on the hindsight once gone he is hard to get a rare breed i tell youin bengali they say golaper sourav bhenshe asche kemon matano ekta gondho it translates to i am getting drunk in that beautiful scent of the rose you may or may not date a sourav in your life but if you find one hold him close

BODY: review movie spoilerfreedisciple indian film winning the golden lion at venice film festival after 19 years year 2020writer director chaitanya tamhaneproducer vivek gombarcinematography michal soboci skimusic aneesh pradhancast aditya modak sushmita bhave ashwini kulkarni kiran yadnyopavit arun dravid and many more there are few films which can show you the reality of your boring life in a very interesting manner this film is one of them this film won the golden lion award for the best screenplay and the best film critics choice at the prestigious venice film festival which is considered as the oldest and the most prestigious among all other film festivals last film from india which won this award was mira nair aposs monsoon wedding long back in 2000 the plot revolves around a guy named sharad nerulkar who is very passionate and wants to make a career in indian classical music the film focuses more on his journey dilemma struggle regarding various instances in his life the plot may seem very much simple and yet it manages to entangle you in the story due to magnificent cinematography movement of the camera zooming into the lead character as he sings will show how much determination he has for his dreams this shot has been used time and time again in the movie second thing which will attract you is the slow motion shots as our lead character is riding a bike and is listening to the tap recordings of maai this particular camera work shows how much blindly and passionately he listens and follows maai aposs philosophy this particular one shot is trump card of the whole film the frames taken are exceptional and will enhance your visual experience after the cinematography the other positive point is the metaphorical writing in many of the shows and films we get an overview of the traditions regarding classical music but here we get that but not that much and there is a reason for it in the whole movie classical music has been used as a metaphor to anything that we are dedicated to so it is basically a life oriented movie and music has been used only as a metaphor thats why if you closely listen to maai aposs philosophy regarding music they are actually techniques of leading life and lastly the most important point is the sound designing in the whole movie you will get a perfect blend of digentic and non digentic sound the tanpura starts immediately when our lead character is listening to maai aposs philosophy and rest of the part you will hear normal and sounds now the negatives i didn apost find any negatives throughout the movie but this film more about visual storytelling and very less dialogues so if you are not into that then this movie is not for you according to me this movie is more than a masterpiece and i will request each and every individual to watch this film

BODY: review nospoiler book the girl in room 105 an unlove storyauthor chetan bhagatpublisher westland ltd genre fictionpublishing year 2018language englishisbn 978 1542040464pages 304when you re slumping and lazily browsing through your bookshelf for a quick read a chetan bhagat book serves almost similar flavour what a smaranjit book is meant for in terms of bengali however this time he tries his hand with somewhat he loves to call fun thriller needless to say proving himself wrong in my opinion if not in mass opinion the story unfolds a rajasthani man keshav rajpurohit to fall in one sided love with a kashmiri muslim girl called zara lone the mystery sets in when one night in room 105 keshav finds her dead then the hunt for murderer begins with a juxtaposed outcome the pages are quite full with desi dialogues with a pinch of vulgar swear words random in bhagat ji novels nowadays kashmir sensitive topics terorism hint and army thing are clearly added for more promotional hype than storytelling or for the sake of plot twist i honestly think bhagat misuses his potential by writing his pieces only eying to make these spicey plot for upcoming bollywood masala flicks this one too not devoid of stock characters randomised taken for granted girl characters cheap punchlines and predictable ending thrill part is wasted while comedy part still manages to stand seriously would love something more credible coming out from him in future time alternative choice to consider rahasya samagra by shirshendu mukhopadhyaytumbaad dekhechi nirvana inn tao dekhechi ebar fobiya ta dekhte hobe review reaction review review review movie h2s team review wanda vision just finished the first 2 episodes and i can t wait for more i will never be tired from seeing elizabeth olsen and paul bettany on screen together they have a fantastic chemistry that brings their characters to life kathryn hahn also does her role well wandavision is weird and wonderful there is a strong sense of mystery and even danger by the end of each episode i ve been on the edge of my seat i crave more i really do wish that they released all the episodes together but i will not allow that to tarnish the greatness of this show after having such a long break between marvel content this is exactly what i needed to kickstart my love for the franchise again can t wait for more episodes reaction wandavision na dekhe thakle akhuni dekhun jodi apni marvel fan hon marvel fan non kintu marvel er cinema gulo dakha taholeo dekhun because mcu is going to explode puro universe ta ke onno matray niye gachhe beshi kotha bolle spoiler dewa hoye jabe tobe ajker episode tar por uttejona aro bere galo marvel er ei bold move experimentation korar amar darun lagchhe ar sitcom er sathe sci fi mystery thriller er blending ta osadharon review movie i watched dc s aquaman today and to be honest this movie doesn t deserve to be treated like this by the critics especially aquaman is dc s one of the beautiful and finest creation and above all this movie has proved what dceu can give common movie lovers this movie is outstanding most common thing in the movie was the tone of the movie as it should be dark in story but the story telling is beautifully managed and exceed all our expectation and visuals were simply jaw dropping as a story aquaman is run of the mill mixing bits of national treasure thor black panther ormwasright and green lantern in a good way into an entertaining stew but the devil is in the details and the screen is filled with delightful details easter eggs and visual gags from beginning to end save for a reference to steppenwolf this is an entirely self contained movie and even the mid credit cookie is entirely in the service of this specific franchise it is colorful funny swashbuckling ly violent big screen entertainment with a simple story providing a framework for charming characters and top notch spectacle the third act soars accordingly delivering the promised absurdist lord of the rings but underwater action and by that time we like the characters enough to give a damn momoa s arc as aquaman is solid and includes some especially thoughtful intelligent self awareness and self criticism nicole kidman s atlanna is a wonderfully developed role and the one with the strongest emotional presentation she packs so much into a relatively small number of scenes but it s such a full story and kidman brings it all to life perfectly yahya abdul mateen ii as black manta is aquaman s most hated enemy and the film really sets up their conflict perfectly giving manta a singular understandable drive also he s simply one of the coolest looking villains in comics and now he s become one of the absolutely coolest looking villains in movies patrick wilson s ocean master has a few different motives and goals and it all works well even though i d like to have seen more passionate emphasis on his sense of righteousness regarding the threat posed by the surface world dolph lundgren plays king nereus and willem dafoe plays nuidis vulko both actors delivering smart restrained performances as dignified royalty who must choose sides in an increasingly brutal and complicated conflict aquaman is more similar to wonder woman than it is to batman v superman or man of steel so yeah i got my aquaman movie i mean i got my aquaman movie the one that lived in my heart the one i yearned to see yet never really believed would ever be made aquaman is an amazing achievement in superhero cinema filled with pulse pounding action and dazzling visual effects it s indiana jones black panther avatar and pirates of the caribbean rolled into one blockbuster ball of holiday cinema thanks a lot to happy2share and mystic phoenix for sharing this movie with me my rating for this movie would be9 8 10 for character development and supporting characters 10 10 for fantastic visual effects and great imaginations9 2 10 for story and sub plotsoverall BODY: guidelinefor the first timers in prelims first attempt is the golden attempt my favourite line some of the things which i would like to share with you1 fear of forgetting everything is quite normal even for senior players don t worry about this 2 fear of not able to see any questions from what you have read till now is classic first attempt trap it happens because you are new to the preparation and your coverage of syllabus is definitely less than senior players but trust me around 60 70 questions will come from what you have read till now rest you will be able to solve with your knowledge of solving mock test 3 confusion between two options it is also faced by all whether first attempt or last pin pointed knowledge is the key here where you have pin pointed knowledge even about any single option don t change it for anything if you are confused then please try the elimination method elimination method doesn t mean some god level trick which you have learned on some youtube or telegram channel upsc is hundred steps ahead of those tricks it s the mix of wide knowledge which you have acquired during this process and basic human instinct for this i want all of you to go through previous year questions 4 chronology of revision first is the basic books then current affairs from wherever you have done it and then previous year questions and lastly test series most of the questions you will find from the basic text books then current affairs and then test series and pyq please don t rely only and only on test papers many test series will claim 70 80 90 questions but if you will check their questions you will like i am not fool test papers might help you in polity geography and history but not in other sections 5 now you must have the balanced confidence of clearing the prelims irrespective of your marks in mock or any test this is the key to get into prelims under and over confidence both can ruin your chance of prelims 6 you can t judge whether paper is simple or tough you are not having that much experience therefore please don t limit your attempt or exceed on the basis of paper attempt according to your pre decided plan 7 increase your reading speed toughness of the paper since 2018 also accompany with increased length of the papers it takes time to read full paper therefore you must solve mock test in 1 5 hrs instead of 2 hrs 8 one famous movie 3 idiots had one famous character chaturramalingam free mock in the last week is golden trap and they re using that funda of churan students how to remove competition either by increasing the performance of your team or make others feel demotivated this is what many institute do especially two big institute they resort to second option because first require efforts i know this from personal experience toppers will get 178 180 marks and you struggle for even 100 marks your marks are like 42 52 52 72 etc if you go for deep analysis then you will find questions were framed for not to get corrected avoid giving any free free mock now please depend on pyq for next week

intriguing one while on one hand we feel attached to him and his journey and on the other hand we can apost help questioning him well this is just the book while making a journey through the pages we live with karna we get to understand him in a much deeper level and most importantly we get to put up the questions uruvi though a fictional character actually represents us she is karna aposs conscience keeper but i personally feel she represents us readers throughout the book there had been so many instances where i felt uruvi was able to read my mind and was putting forward all the questions and seeking justification for all the injustice rendered to karna there is a beautiful instance in the book where uruvi seeks justification from bhishma pitamah about the injustice he had subjected karna to for years even after knowing that he was the rightful heir of kuru clan to which bhishma replied that he had no right in claiming him as his grandson until his mother kunti recongnized him as his son in front of the society especially when the society can question her character but this yet again gives rise to the question how long shall you stay indifferent is it actually right to silently give rise to kurukshetra we also see uruvi questioning karna about his blind friendship and oath of loyalty towards duryodhana while their friendship had grown only stronger over the years yet it was this very friendship which caused the demise of karna even though he proved his loyalty till the end but could he really be a great friend what is friendship if not stopping them going to the wrong path and then again we get to a point where uruvi herself is questioned about her judgements towards karna how could she judge him when she hadn apost been through a lifetime BODY: i hear facebook has an entire department devoted to figuring out why telegram is so popular imagine dozens of employees working on just that full time i am happy to save facebook tens of millions of dollars and give away our secret for free respect your users millions of people are outraged by the latest change in whatsapp terms which now say users must feed all their private data to facebook s ad engine it s no surprise that the flight of users from whatsapp to telegram already ongoing for a few years has accelerated at about 500 million users and growing telegram has become a major problem for the facebook corporation unable to compete with telegram in quality and privacy facebook s whatsapp seems to have switched to covert marketing wikipedia editors have recently exposed multiple paid bots adding biased information into the whatsapp wikipedia article 1 we have also detected bots which spread inaccurate information about telegram on social media here are the 3 myths they are pushing myth 1 telegram s code is not open source in reality all telegram client apps have been open source since 2013 2 our encryption and api are fully documented and have been reviewed by security experts thousands of times moreover telegram is the only messaging app in the world that has verifiable builds both for ios and android 3 as for whatsapp they intentionally obfuscate their code making it impossible to verify their encryption and privacy myth 2 telegram is russian in fact telegram has no servers or offices in russia and was blocked there from 2018 to 2020 4 telegram is still blocked in some authoritarian countries such as iran while whatsapp and other supposedly secure apps have never had any issue in these places myth 3 telegram is not encrypted every chat on BODY: review movie spoilerfreetenet don apost try to understand it feel it year 2020writer director christopher nolan cinematography hoyte van hoyetemamusic ludwig g ranssoncast john david washington robert pattinson elizabeth debicki kenneth branagh dimple kapadia michael caine and many more this quoted line is from the most awaited movie of christopher nolan tenet this one line was said by a character named laura for the lead character and the audience who were just about experience the absurdness of the film and yes at first i watched the movie at one go without giving a pause just to take that experience and the second time i rewatched few parts of the movie in order to understand it and i would say i tried my best to understand the movie though that is kind of impossible yet i developed my own perception of the entire film the plot is based on an unnamed guy who is referred as the protagonist played by j d washington is recruited by a secret organisation in his afterlife which is engaged in cold war with an unknown enemy he is advised by his senior to go after andrei sator played by kenneth branagh a russian arms dealer who is involved with some rare kind of ammunition that moves backwards through his journey he is assisted by neil robert pattinson and sator aposs wife katharine elizabeth debicki the first positive point in this movie is the writing probably in every nolan aposs movie we get an overview of something absurd or beyond our imagination thing is taking place without knowing its source or the cause of why its happening like in inception we never get to know what the whole dream machine is about but we see a detailed procedure of how they get involved in each others dream in interstellar we see the lead character communicating with his daughter through the 5 dimension world but we never get an overview how this is happening but in tenet he gave the explanation of the absurdities occurring though not all but he explains the exact reason behind time reversal concept and the pincher movement but he didn apost explain the concept of afterlife and the actual purpose of satore moreover the whole story being told through the perspective of the protagonist gives rise to several mysteries especially the involvement of neil remains a mystery but the ones who have watched the movie closely will know who this neil really is second great thing about this movie is the cinematography the whole time reversal action sequences is a delight to watch in the very beginning when the lead character is at the verge of being killed we see two trains passing simultaneously one in forward and the other one in backward direction which was a hint what is going to happen in the film in many of the action movies when we watch car flipping we watch it on pov shot or through distorted shots but here nolan uses a steady wide angle shot in a whole car flip scene which i must say is very very rare the editing of the movie is abrupt in few cases that is another good thing regarding this film now the negatives i personally didn apost find any negatives regarding the film but there are few concepts regarding the movie which you should be familiar with not the time reversal concept but the whole occurrence of the pincher movement is the main key factor if you are the ones who hasn apost seen a sci fi thriller or doesn apost know about nolan aposs filmography or style please don apost watch this film at first go for his previous films first in order to understand this one and if you want to develop a complete perception regarding this you need to watch each and every minute details and still if you cant you can refer to different blogs there is nothing shame in referring to a blog in order to understand this movie i personally referred to some them in order to find answers to my queries to me this movie another masterpiece by nolan and yes do watch it on a big screen in full hd otherwise you wont be able to experience the stunning visuals and slow motions throughout the film

the human realm high school student and prodigy light yagami stumbles upon the death note and since he deplores the state of the world tests the deadly notebook by writing a criminal s name in it when the criminal dies immediately following his experiment with the death note light is greatly surprised and quickly recognizes how devastating the power that has fallen into his hands could be with this divine capability light decides to extinguish all criminals in order to build a new world where crime does not exist and people worship him as a god police however quickly discover that a serial killer is targeting criminals and consequently try to apprehend the culprit to do this the japanese investigators count on the assistance of the best detective in the world a young and eccentric man millions of dollars and give away our secret for free respect your users millions of people are outraged by the latest change in whatsapp terms which now say users must feed all their private data to facebook s ad engine it s no surprise that the flight of users from whatsapp to telegram already ongoing for a few years has accelerated at about 500 million users and growing telegram has become a major problem for the facebook corporation unable to compete with telegram in quality and privacy facebook s whatsapp seems to have switched to covert marketing wikipedia editors have recently exposed multiple paid bots adding biased information into the whatsapp wikipedia article 1 we have also detected bots which spread inaccurate information about telegram on social media here are the 3 myths they are pushing myth 1 telegram s code is not open source in reality all telegram client apps have been open source since 2013 2 our encryption and api are fully documented and have been reviewed by security experts thousands of times moreover telegram is the only messaging app in the world that has verifiable builds both for ios and android 3 as for whatsapp they intentionally obfuscate their code making it impossible to verify their encryption and privacy myth 2 telegram is russian in fact telegram has no servers or offices in russia and was blocked there from 2018 to 2020 4 telegram is still blocked in some authoritarian countries such as iran while whatsapp and other supposedly secure apps have never had any issue in these places myth 3 telegram is not encrypted every chat on telegram has been encrypted since launch we have secret chats that are end to end and cloud chats that also offer real time secure and distributed cloud storage 5 whatsapp on the other hand had zero encryption for a few years and then adopted an encryption protocol funded by the us government 6 even if we assume that the whatsapp encryption is solid it s invalidated via multiple backdoors and BODY: review ramprasad ki tehrvi 2020 realistic black comedy drama hits the right notefirst of all my first film in theaters after almost a year and the feeling was great although whole hall was empty except me and gandhi to watch a film on big screen again now coming to the movie directed by debutante seema pahwa known for her roles in chintu ka birthday shubh mangal saavdhan was a balanced act of satire melancholy lifted by brilliant acting camerawork screenplay positives the realism from the conversations between siblings united after a long time to the depiction of feud among neucleur family director wrote the screenplay with proper sense of reality the film is an acting masterclass no need or intention to identify a single one as everyone in the cast is mind blowing from konkona to vikrant massey parambrata from deepika amin to vinay pathak to supriya pathak brajendra kala manoj pahwa everyone poured their heart out direction screenplay as a debutantee seema pahwa does an excellent job at handling a common well known topic and still making her own voice being heard in it screenplay and dialogue writing is done with utmost care camerawork have to mention sudip sengupta because without his stupendous and dedicated cinematography the feeling of the film is half lost he follows the emotions of characters very well with great use of lighting average negativesthere aposs not really anything negative in this film just that some aspects could have been better the music is just fine and suits the film brilliantly but fails to stay with the audience that much editing could have been better like 1 2 sequences could have been cut or shortened maybe conclusionoverall i would say it aposs a great and relatable tragicomedy that can be seen with friends family both this is a film that shows u both light darkness of life in same frame hand to hand without dismissing the other and the core theme stays with you after leaving the theater so go and watch it in theater if u love slice of life and black comedy dramas with realistic setting recommended7 4 7 5 10

BODY: review movie spoilerfreedisciple indian film winning the golden lion at venice film festival after 19 years year 2020writer director chaitanya tamhaneproducer vivek gombarcinematography michal soboci skimusic aneesh pradhancast aditya modak sushmita bhave ashwini kulkarni kiran yadnyopavit arun dravid and many more there are few films which can show you the reality of your boring life in a very interesting manner this film is one of them this film won the golden lion award for the best screenplay and the best film critics choice at the prestigious venice film festival which is considered as the oldest and the most prestigious among all other film festivals last film from india which won this award was mira nair s monsoon wedding long back in 2000 the plot revolves around a guy named sharad nerulkar who is very passionate and wants to make a career in indian classical music the film focuses more on his journey dilemma struggle regarding various instances in his life the plot may seem very much simple and yet it manages to entangle you in the story due to magnificent cinematography movement of the camera zooming into the lead character as he sings will show how much determination he has for his dreams this shot has been used time and time again in the movie second thing which will attract you is the slow motion shots as our lead character is riding a bike and is listening to the tap recordings of maai this particular camera work shows how much blindly and passionately he listens and follows maai s philosophy this particular one shot is trump card of the whole film the frames taken are exceptional and will enhance your visual experience after the cinematography the other positive point is the metaphorical writing in many of the shows and films we get an overview of the traditions regarding classical music but here we get that but not that much and there is a reason for it in the whole movie classical music has been used as a metaphor to anything that we are dedicated to so it is basically a life oriented movie and music has been used only as a metaphor thats why if you closely listen to maai s philosophy regarding music they are actually techniques of leading life and lastly the most important point is the sound designing in the whole movie you will get a perfect blend of digentic and non digentic sound the tanpura starts immediately when our lead character is listening to maai s philosophy and rest of the part you will hear normal and sounds now the negatives i didn t find any negatives throughout the movie but this film more about visual storytelling and very less dialogues so if you are not into that then this movie is not for you according to me this movie is more than a masterpiece and i will request each and every individual to watch this film

BODY: this month we have verified and promoted 17 official news sources representing ministries of health in 17 countries the constantly growing list is available in corona we did this as part of our anti covid19 initiative announced in early april while telegram is not exactly famous for cooperating with government officials we decided to make one exception globally to help spread information about the virus the current pandemic is a threat to our entire species when it ends the world will not return to normal we may witness a civilizational shift that will ripple through generations it is up to all of us to ensure that the new world about to be born is a better place than the one we aposre leaving behind this is a chance for people to use their time in isolation to create a better version of themselves and a chance for technology to prove its worth for humanity i believe we at telegram should do all we can not only to help contain the pandemic and combat the spread of unverified information but also to find new ways of moving forwards for this reason in addition to providing informational support we ll try to contribute to tackling the problem of education under lockdown we also have several other anti covid19 projects in the works at telegram i will announce more details in the next few days on the telegram blog stay tuned and stay safe

facebook s ad engine 1 it s no surprise that the flight of users from whatsapp to telegram already ongoing for a few years has accelerated at about 500 million users and growing telegram has become a major problem for the facebook corporation unable to compete with telegram in quality and privacy facebook s whatsapp seems to have switched to covert marketing wikipedia editors have recently exposed multiple paid bots adding biased information into the whatsapp wikipedia article 2 we have also detected bots which spread inaccurate information about telegram on social media here are the 3 myths they are pushing myth 1 telegram s code is not open source in reality all telegram client apps have been open source since 2013 3 our encryption and api are fully documented and have been reviewed by security experts thousands of times moreover telegram is the only messaging app in the world that has verifiable builds both for ios and android 4 as for whatsapp they intentionally obfuscate their code making it impossible to verify their encryption and privacy myth 2 telegram is russian in fact telegram has no servers or offices in russia and was blocked there from 2018 to 2020 5 telegram is still blocked in some authoritarian countries such as iran while whatsapp and other supposedly secure apps have never had any issue in these places myth 3 telegram is not encrypted every chat on telegram has been encrypted since launch we have secret chats that are end to end and cloud chats that also offer real time secure and distributed cloud storage 6 whatsapp on the other hand had zero encryption for a few years and then adopted an encryption protocol funded by the us government 7 even if we assume that the whatsapp encryption is solid it s invalidated via multiple backdoors and reliance on backups 8 in 2019 alone facebook spent almost 10 billion dollars on marketing 9 i guess this includes paid bots on wikipedia and other sites unlike facebook telegram doesn apost spend any BODY: this month we have verified and promoted 17 official news sources representing ministries of health in 17 countries the constantly growing list is available in corona we did this as part of our anti covid19 initiative announced in early april while telegram is not exactly famous for cooperating with government officials we decided to make one exception globally to help spread information about the virus the current pandemic is a threat to our entire species when it ends the world will not return to normal we may witness a civilizational shift that will ripple through generations it is up to all of us to ensure that the new world about to be born is a better place than the one we re leaving behind this is a chance for people to use their time in isolation to create a better version of themselves and a chance for technology to prove its worth for humanity i believe we at telegram should do all we can not only to help contain the pandemic and combat the spread of unverified information but also to find new ways of moving forwards for this reason in addition to providing informational support we ll try to contribute to tackling the problem of education under lockdown we also have several other anti covid19 projects in the works at telegram i will announce more details in the next few days on the telegram blog stay tuned and stay safe

BODY: nice review keep it up excellent what u give rating out of 10 review hiroshima mon amour alain resnais review movie silence can you hear it the movie silence can you hear it is a thriller film it stars the legend manoj bajpayee prachi desai and arjun mathur the way the movie starts makes the audience stay connected since the starting manoj sir s performance is asusual legendary and the way he abuses will surely make you laugh xd and the movie also contains funny scenes and dialogues the other co actors also gave their best the storyline is also very good as in the movie a judge s daughter is killed mysteriously and manoj bajpayee as an acp officer investigates the mystery the suspense in the end is the best part of the movie and you will surely be shocked it is a must watch one time movie the only thing i didn t liked is the runtime of the movie as it is too long straight 2 hr and 16 min which for the movies nowadays is a long itme it s a mystery packed a must watch movie i willl give 7 10 sardar ka grandson movie review before i start my review please expect some unrealistic things in this movie arjun kapoor is settled in los angeles and is staying as a live in with rakulpreet singh due to some reasons they have some differences and she leaves the house arjun kapoor gets a call from his dad that his grandmother played by neena gupta is unwell in amritsar and wants her last wish of visiting her home in lahore to be fulfilled now will arjun kapoor be able to live up to her expectations and what all hurdles will he face is something you have to watch out for arjun kapoor has played his role well but needs to improve upon his comic and emotional timings where he gets a bit loud rakulpreet singh is good and has done a good job john abraham and aditi rao hydari are in brief roles and are decent kumud mishra returns after a long time in a negative role and has done good the main focus is neena gupta who has played her path well but she doesn t look 90 years even after she getting an old womans make up which too is not up to the mark the movie overall is a time pass one time watch with some things being unbelievable my rating 2 5 stars streaming on netflix run time 2 hrs 19 min reaction reviewsandeep aur pinky faraarso guys i was waiting for sandeep aur pinky faraar to come on a streaming platform for a long time now it s available on amazon prime i watched it yesterday and this is how i feel about the movie a lot of people will see arjun kapoor on the poster and will simply avoid the film but this film will break the stereotypes in your mind as this is the best work of parineeti chopra as far as i have seen watching jaydeep ahlawat act is just a delight to eyes raghubir yadav and neena gupta pradhan ji and his wife from panchayat are always brilliant arjun kapoor too has done a good job but the best part about the film is the script dibakar banerjee and varun grover came together to write this and the result is worth your time this film exposes the indian society on several fronts but it never feels like it s trying to be woke the film starts as a chase thriller but halfway through you understand that it s much bigger than that in every thriller the character arc of whether the antagonist or the protagonist is fixed but this film is layered it s a social drama cum chase thriller cum dark zoned movie when i finished this movie last night there was a smile on my face the smile you generally have after watching a really good movie i don t just recommend rather request everybody to watch this movie invite link expired
