BODY: review ramprasad ki tehrvi 2020 realistic black comedy drama hits the right notefirst of all my first film in theaters after almost a year and the feeling was great although whole hall was empty except me and gandhi to watch a film on big screen again now coming to the movie directed by debutante seema pahwa known for her roles in chintu ka birthday shubh mangal saavdhan was a balanced act of satire melancholy lifted by brilliant acting camerawork screenplay positives the realism from the conversations between siblings united after a long time to the depiction of feud among neucleur family director wrote the screenplay with proper sense of reality the film is an acting masterclass no need or intention to identify a single one as everyone in the cast is mind blowing from konkona to vikrant massey parambrata from deepika amin to vinay pathak to supriya pathak brajendra kala manoj pahwa everyone poured their heart out direction screenplay as a debutantee seema pahwa does an excellent job at handling a common well known topic and still making her own voice being heard in it screenplay and dialogue writing is done with utmost care camerawork have to mention sudip sengupta because without his stupendous and dedicated cinematography the feeling of the film is half lost he follows the emotions of characters very well with great use of lighting average negativesthere s not really anything negative in this film just that some aspects could have been better the music is just fine and suits the film brilliantly but fails to stay with the audience that much editing could have been better like 1 2 sequences could have been cut or shortened maybe conclusionoverall i would say it s a great and relatable tragicomedy that can be seen with friends family both this is a film that shows u both light darkness of life in same frame hand to hand without dismissing the other and the core theme stays with you after leaving the theater so go and watch it in theater if u love slice of life and black comedy dramas with realistic setting recommended7 4 7 5 10

BODY: silvat the best performance of kartik aryaan that nobody saw year 2016length 42 minutesplatform zee5director tanuja chandrascreenplay faraz ansaricast meher mistry kartik aryaan maamon memon the most important work of a director is to utilize an actor in a such a way that he or shegives their best in order to enact a scene kartik aryaan who is a rising star in bollywood and is stereotyped in various manner once gave a stellar stellar performance in a low budget short film which i think didn apost get its recognition and tanuja chandra the director of this film is also the director of another amazing film from the 90 aposs called sangharsh which is famous for the iconic character of lajja shankar pandey played by ashutosh rana timeline is set during the 1997 where many people from india moved to the gulf countries in order to earn money noor played by meher mistry whose husband was one of them whose husband went away just after 2 days of their marriage the movie revolves around how a lonely housewife falls in love with a tailor anwar played by kartik aryaan and what happens next the first positive point is the cinematography and the minute detailing on screen minute detailing regarding the concept of love is a treat to watch second thing the music the music partly sufi and the sarangi tune that comes up everytime is another great point of the film last but not the least performances meher mistry did a very good job with her expressions she had the maximum number of scenes and in each scene she performed brilliantly but kartik aryaan aposs performance was kind of surprise package for me because have never seen him in an out and out complete serious film with no comedy especially i was amazed by the outburst scene where lets his anger out with completely no dialogues now the negatives the music of the movie was good as i mentioned earlier but what i found a little bit odd was the utilisation of the sound in few places especially when a realistic scene is going then i guess the sound should be real too and not an additional sarangi tune playing in the background anyway i will request all the kartik aryaan fans and non fans to give it a watch i bet you will notice a completely different kartik aryaan different from all the characters he has played till now

BODY: reviewbook karna s wife the outcast s queenauthor kavita kanewhile mahabharata itself is an intriguing read i have to admit that the character of karna has always been the most intriguing one while on one hand we feel attached to him and his journey and on the other hand we can t help questioning him well this is just the book while making a journey through the pages we live with karna we get to understand him in a much deeper level and most importantly we get to put up the questions uruvi though a fictional character actually represents us she is karna s conscience keeper but i personally feel she represents us readers throughout the book there had been so many instances where i felt uruvi was able to read my mind and was putting forward all the questions and seeking justification for all the injustice rendered to karna there is a beautiful instance in the book where uruvi seeks justification from bhishma pitamah about the injustice he had subjected karna to for years even after knowing that he was the rightful heir of kuru clan to which bhishma replied that he had no right in claiming him as his grandson until his mother kunti recongnized him as his son in front of the society especially when the society can question her character but this yet again gives rise to the question how long shall you stay indifferent is it actually right to silently give rise to kurukshetra we also see uruvi questioning karna about his blind friendship and oath of loyalty towards duryodhana while their friendship had grown only stronger over the years yet it was this very friendship which caused the demise of karna even though he proved his loyalty till the end but could he really be a great friend what is friendship if not stopping them going to the wrong path and then again we get to a point where uruvi herself is questioned about her judgements towards karna how could she judge him when she hadn t been through a lifetime of humiliation and abandonment and a constant search of acceptance and dignity when once questioned by uruvi why do you want to fight arjuna what do you want to prove that you are a great warrior to which karna replies no a loser who wants to fight for his dignity he knew he was going towards his death a death whose dentiny was determined by the curses abandonment humiliations and his daanveerta a man with his flaws and strenghts this book is a perfect read for those who want to see the insight of karna you will feel your existence throughout the journey because uruvi isn t fictional it s the reader s voice please do give this book a try you sure will enjoy it

BODY: i had left calcutta in 1976 never went back to settle down for various reasons yes when i left calcutta it was dreadful i had to waste one year to get into college in madras because my final school result were delayed by 6 months but emotionally i love my calcutta many says calcutta has much less oppertunity than other metro i worked with abp and hence i really never lost roots and kept visiting i always saw changes during my visits since last few years many malls new restaurants huge gated community but still whenever i see paiteins in bangalore or hyderabad or madras they complain about inadequacy my friends in calcutta keeps asking about schools and colleges in south i wonder why is it other side of river always green or something else i always wanted to go back to calcutta to settle down but my kids prevented it then one of childhood friend who had settled in canada spoken bitterly about calcutta he wanted to come back but was harassed and now looking to purchase property in south then i understood one point those of us who prefer the city are always emotionally attached to it but i all practical purpose our dear state had gone back or self destroyed since 1967 what we look at the infrastructure progress which otherwise is happening everywhere and except real estate and other developments which is natural keeping with the time we lost the practical development politics is calcutta never grew from 1970 chaos every state mechinary is corrupt south is the most but they are preferred destination simply because they had been working despite being the machinery being corrupt in calcutta it is not only machinery but willingness to take it forward also got corrupted i cry in my inner sense when someone innocently ask me what actor dev got to do with davos meeting or why is that they go on rampages still in hospitals or in universities or why is that nandigram happened if we really love bengal we need to address this there are people who started business and doing well in calcutta but compare the percentage and it is only trading and service i love to settle down there as i am now retired but not before that as city of joy has long way to go to become city of opportunity like once the glorified villages like hyderabad and bangalore has become now

slumping and lazily browsing through your bookshelf for a quick read a chetan bhagat book serves almost similar flavour what a smaranjit book is meant for in terms of bengali however this time he tries his hand with somewhat he loves to call fun thriller needless to say proving himself wrong in my opinion if not in mass opinion the story unfolds a rajasthani man keshav rajpurohit to fall in one sided love with a kashmiri muslim girl called zara lone the mystery sets in when one night in room 105 keshav finds her dead then the hunt for murderer begins with a juxtaposed outcome the pages are quite full with desi dialogues with a pinch of vulgar swear words random in bhagat ji novels nowadays kashmir sensitive topics terorism hint and army thing are clearly added for more promotional hype than storytelling or for the sake of plot twist i honestly think bhagat misuses his potential by writing his pieces only eying to make these spicey plot for upcoming bollywood masala flicks this one too not devoid of stock characters randomised taken for granted girl characters cheap punchlines and predictable ending thrill part is wasted while comedy part still manages to stand seriously would love something more credible coming out from him in future time alternative choice to consider rahasya samagra by shirshendu mukhopadhyaytumbaad dekhechi nirvana inn tao dekhechi ebar fobiya ta mystery and even danger by the end of each episode i ve been on the edge of my seat i crave more i really do wish that they released all the episodes together but i will not allow that to tarnish the greatness of this show after having such a long break between marvel content this is exactly what i needed to kickstart my love for the franchise again can t wait for more episodes reaction thriller er blending ta osadharon review movie i watched dc s aquaman today and to be honest this movie doesn t deserve to be treated like this by the critics especially aquaman is dc s one of the beautiful and finest creation and above all this movie has proved what dceu can give common movie lovers this movie is outstanding most common thing in the movie was the tone of the movie as it should be dark in story but the story telling is beautifully managed and exceed all our expectation and visuals were simply jaw dropping as a story aquaman is run of the mill mixing bits of national treasure thor black panther ormwasright and green lantern in a good way into an entertaining stew but the devil is in the details and the screen is filled with delightful details easter eggs and visual gags from beginning to end save for a reference to steppenwolf this is an entirely self contained movie and even the mid credit cookie is entirely in the service of this specific franchise it is colorful funny swashbuckling ly violent big screen entertainment with a simple story providing a framework for charming characters and top notch spectacle the third act soars accordingly delivering the promised absurdist lord of the rings but underwater action and by that time we like the characters enough to give a damn momoa s arc as aquaman is solid and includes some especially thoughtful intelligent self awareness and self criticism nicole kidman s atlanna is a wonderfully developed role and the one with the strongest emotional presentation she packs so much into a relatively small number of scenes but it s such a full story and kidman brings it all to life perfectly yahya abdul mateen ii as black manta is aquaman s most hated enemy and the film really sets up their conflict perfectly giving manta a singular understandable drive also he s simply one of the coolest looking villains in comics and now he s become one of the absolutely coolest looking villains in movies patrick wilson s ocean master has a few different motives and goals and it all works well even though i d like to have seen more passionate emphasis on his sense of righteousness regarding the threat posed by the surface world dolph lundgren plays king nereus and willem dafoe plays nuidis vulko both actors delivering smart restrained performances as dignified royalty who must choose sides in an increasingly brutal and complicated conflict aquaman is more similar to wonder woman than it is to batman v superman or man of steel so yeah i got my aquaman movie i mean i got my aquaman movie the one that lived in my heart the one i yearned to see yet never really believed would ever be made aquaman is an amazing achievement in superhero cinema filled with pulse pounding action and dazzling visual effects it s indiana jones black panther avatar and pirates of the caribbean rolled into one blockbuster ball of holiday cinema thanks a lot to happy2share and mystic phoenix for sharing this knowledge of solving mock test 3 confusion between two options it is also faced by all whether first attempt or last pin pointed knowledge is the key here where you have pin pointed knowledge even about any single option don t change it for anything if you are confused then please try the elimination method elimination method doesn t mean some god level trick which you have learned on some youtube or telegram channel upsc is hundred steps ahead of those tricks it s the mix of wide knowledge which you have acquired during this process and basic human instinct for this i want all of you to go through previous year questions 4 chronology of revision first is the basic books then current affairs from wherever you have done it and then previous year questions and lastly test series most clearing the prelims irrespective of your marks in mock or any test this is the key to get into prelims under and over confidence both can ruin your chance of prelims 6 you can t judge whether paper BODY: the capitalism socialism opposition seems outdated i prefer to think in terms of centralization vs decentralization humans have evolved to perform best in small groups of less than 150 people that s why wherever there s centralization and excessive heirarchy there s inefficiency and underutilized human potential capitalist monopolies and socialist dictatorships are equally bad in a natural environment every small community is able to produce an outstanding leader and an independent thinker in today s world of trillion dollar monopolies and bloated governments the potential of hundreds of millions of people is suppressed by the limitations imposed by our artificial societal structures that is the reason why tens of thousands of people working at big corporations such as facebook have failed to keep up with what our small team at telegram has been implementing that s also the reason why countries like russia fail to generate and retain global brands in their jurisdictions genuine creativity is rare in organizations and societies built on excessive hierarchies and lack of personal autonomy

BODY: story words speak louder than actionswe have often heard people saying that actions speak louder than words but words can in some cases speak louder than actions this story tells us that we can also say the latter in mexico city there lived a boy named ethan he had an indian origin and had traveled almost every place in the world due to his father s transferrable job he was a very jolly and happy boy he was strong in both academics and athletics his mother had her own home business of bakery and he grew up watching his father go to work every morning before anyone woke up and returned after everyone slept he only knew that his father did a very reputed job on sundays he loved to spend time with his father playing games or by going on a small trip with the family life for him was very much similar every day except the fact that he met a lot of new people almost every year as he grew up he had many friends too they wanted to know about him and what his father and mother did and BODY: story words speak louder than actionswe have often heard people saying that actions speak louder than words but words can in some cases speak louder than actions this story tells us that we can also say the latter in mexico city there lived a boy named ethan he had an indian origin and had traveled almost every place in the world due to his father s transferrable job he was a very jolly and happy boy he was strong in both academics and athletics his mother had her own home business of bakery and he grew up watching his father go to work every morning before anyone woke up and returned after everyone slept he only knew that his father did a very reputed job on sundays he loved to spend time with his father playing games or by going on a small trip with the family life for him was very much similar every day except the fact that he met a lot of new people almost every year as he grew up he had many friends too they wanted to know about him and what his father and mother did and every time he ended saying that he did not know his father s occupation properly he felt very ashamed of himself and it was then he was determined to ask his father about it likewise he asked his father about his job his father replied that he worked in a call center despite getting the answer ethan was not satisfied with it he knew that at call centers there were shifts but one stay in one place for a long time moreover his job was transferrable that means talking to different peoples in different countries almost every year is impossible but he had no other option than to believe the same now ethan became mature and they shifted to pennsylvania the day was similar to another day but that day his father didn t come back home to the work he and his mother were extremely worried they informed the local police and filed a missing diary as well they hoped that he would return soon but days passed by and he did not return even after a week ethan and his mother searched him like mad persons then ethan decided to search for everything very minutely so he asked for the cctv footage and found his father in a very remote part of pennsylvania when they went there his father was not there ethan and his mother lost all their hopes as they also couldn t find any clues after three weeks and two days later his father came and without answering their questions he told them that now they had to go to india as soon as possible they followed his words went to the place where they actually belonged to when they reached india he revealed the biggest secret of his life he was actually a secret agent from the indian government he went to different countries to accomplish small missions but this time they had to deal with the biggest criminal of all time dudley he also told them that the mission was really hard and it took them two weeks to identify dudley s actual location but they succeeded in their mission both of the listeners were shocked they could not believe their ears they understood why some people say words speak louder than actions instead of saying actions speak louder than words ayantika rakshit

BODY: just finished watching deliver us from evil 2020 korean film a very engaging tale one that attempts to get as real as it can whilst yet maintaining the fabric of fictional reality in a film dominated by psychopaths of various degrees painting anyone with any moral obligation goes out of the window yet the protagonist is intrinsically imbued with a modicum of morality and is stricken with a gust of hope especially at a juncture in his life when he absolutely has no utility of hope the film being designed as a high octane action thriller obviously delivers on that front to a large extent but what it also exhibits is the story writers carefully placed bread crumbs of hope placed all along the journey of the protagonist thus it also gives us as an audience the chance to see the protagonist s frantic attempt and yearning for redemption as he keeps taking those bread crumbs desperately to have some meaning to his life i might be exaggerating with the moral aspect of the film perhaps eulogising too to a certain extent the reality or the lack of it thereof is again beautifully done its been done before it s been done almost neatly in here too nothing of major importance action choreography is as expected of korean gangster films although fight cinematography of hong kyung po employs the ever so known jittery camera technique but its not bad infact the shaky camera work at least lets us see the punches land and the knives disembowel the participants so yeah not bad but not good too the film boasts of a stellar pair of lead actors especially the leads this marks the reunion of hwang jung min and lee jung jae after new world 2013 another gem of a film apart from them no one was that significant in conclusion its a regular action flick and no more doesn t intend to be preachy where violence is made commonplace and justifications for bloodshed are hardly essential my rating 7 10 review

BODY: review movie spoilerfreetenet don t try to understand it feel it year 2020writer director christopher nolan cinematography hoyte van hoyetemamusic ludwig g ranssoncast john david washington robert pattinson elizabeth debicki kenneth branagh dimple kapadia michael caine and many more this quoted line is from the most awaited movie of christopher nolan tenet this one line was said by a character named laura for the lead character and the audience who were just about experience the absurdness of the film and yes at first i watched the movie at one go without giving a pause just to take that experience and the second time i rewatched few parts of the movie in order to understand it and i would say i tried my best to understand the movie though that is kind of impossible yet i developed my own perception of the entire film the plot is based on an unnamed guy who is referred as the protagonist played by j d washington is recruited by a secret organisation in his afterlife which is engaged in cold war with an unknown enemy he is advised by his senior to go after andrei sator played by kenneth branagh a russian arms dealer who is involved with some rare kind of ammunition that moves backwards through his journey he is assisted by neil robert pattinson and sator s wife katharine elizabeth debicki the first positive point in this movie is the writing probably in every nolan s movie we get an overview of something absurd or beyond our imagination thing is taking place without knowing its source or the cause of why its happening like in inception we never get to know what the whole dream machine is about but we see a detailed procedure of how they get involved in each others dream in interstellar we see the lead character communicating with his daughter through the 5 dimension world but we never get an overview how this is happening but in tenet he gave the explanation of the absurdities occurring though not all but he explains the exact reason behind time reversal concept and the pincher movement but he didn t explain the concept of afterlife and the actual purpose of satore moreover the whole story being told through the perspective of the protagonist gives rise to several mysteries especially the involvement of neil remains a mystery but the ones who have watched the movie closely will know who this neil really is second great thing about this movie is the cinematography the whole time reversal action sequences is a delight to watch in the very beginning when the lead character is at the verge of being killed we see two trains passing simultaneously one in forward and the other one in backward direction which was a hint what is going to happen in the film in many of the action movies when we watch car flipping we watch it on pov shot or through distorted shots but here nolan uses a steady wide angle shot in a whole car flip scene which i must say is very very rare the editing of the movie is abrupt in few cases that is another good thing regarding this film now the negatives i personally didn t find any negatives regarding the film but there are few concepts regarding the movie which you should be familiar with not the time reversal concept but the whole occurrence of the pincher movement is the main key factor if you are the ones who hasn t seen a sci fi thriller or doesn t know about nolan s filmography or style please don t watch this film at first go for his previous films first in order to understand this one and if you want to develop a complete perception regarding this you need to watch each and every minute details and still if you cant you can refer to different blogs there is nothing shame in referring to a blog in order to understand this movie i personally referred to some them in order to find answers to my queries to me this movie another masterpiece by nolan and yes do watch it on a big screen in full hd otherwise you wont be able to experience the stunning visuals and slow motions throughout the film

BODY: reviewbook karna s wife the outcast s queenauthor kavita kanewhile mahabharata itself is an intriguing read i have to admit that the character of karna has always been the most intriguing one while on one hand we feel attached to him and his journey and on the other hand we can t help questioning him well this is just the book while making a journey through the pages we live with karna we get to understand him in a much deeper level and most importantly we get to put up the questions uruvi though a fictional character actually represents us she is karna s conscience keeper but i personally feel she represents us readers throughout the book there had been so many instances where i felt uruvi was able to read my mind and was putting forward all the questions and seeking justification for all the injustice rendered to karna there is a beautiful instance in the book where uruvi seeks justification from bhishma pitamah about the injustice he had subjected karna to for years even after knowing that he was the rightful heir of kuru clan to which bhishma replied that he had no right in claiming him as his grandson until his mother kunti recongnized him as his son in front of the society especially when the society can question her character but this yet again gives rise to the question how long shall you stay indifferent is it actually right to silently give rise to kurukshetra we also see uruvi questioning karna about his blind friendship and oath of loyalty towards duryodhana while their friendship had grown only stronger over the years yet it was this very friendship which caused the demise of karna even though he proved his loyalty till the end but could he really be a great friend what is friendship if not stopping them going to the wrong path and then again we get to a point where uruvi herself is questioned about her judgements towards karna how could she judge him when she hadn t been through a lifetime of humiliation and abandonment and a constant search of acceptance and dignity when once questioned by uruvi why do you want to fight arjuna what do you want to prove that you are a great warrior to which karna replies no a loser who wants to fight for his dignity he knew he was going towards his death a death whose dentiny was determined by the curses abandonment humiliations and his daanveerta a man with his flaws and strenghts this book is a perfect read for those who want to see the insight of karna you will feel your existence throughout the journey because uruvi isn t fictional it s the reader s voice please do give this book a try you sure will enjoy it

BODY: i had left calcutta in 1976 never went back to settle down for various reasons yes when i left calcutta it was dreadful i had to waste one year to get into college in madras because my final school result were delayed by 6 months but emotionally i love my calcutta many says calcutta has much less oppertunity than other metro i worked with abp and hence i really never lost roots and kept visiting i always saw changes during my visits since last few years many malls new restaurants huge gated community but still whenever i see paiteins in bangalore or hyderabad or madras they complain about inadequacy my friends in calcutta keeps asking about schools and colleges in south i wonder why is it other side of river always green or something else i always wanted to go back to calcutta to settle down but my kids prevented it then one of childhood friend who had settled in canada spoken bitterly about calcutta he wanted to come back but was harassed and now looking to purchase property in south then i understood one point those of us who prefer the city are always emotionally attached to it but i all practical purpose our dear state had gone back or self destroyed since 1967 what we look at the infrastructure progress which otherwise is happening everywhere and except real estate and other developments which is natural keeping with the time we lost the practical development politics is calcutta never grew from 1970 chaos every state mechinary is corrupt south is the most but they are preferred destination simply because they had been working despite being the machinery being corrupt in calcutta it is not only machinery but willingness to take it forward also got corrupted i cry in my inner sense when someone innocently ask me what actor dev got to do with davos BODY: review movie spoilerfreedisciple indian film winning the golden lion at venice film festival after 19 years year 2020writer director chaitanya tamhaneproducer vivek gombarcinematography michal soboci skimusic aneesh pradhancast aditya modak sushmita bhave ashwini kulkarni kiran yadnyopavit arun dravid and many more there are few films which can show you the reality of your boring life in a very interesting manner this film is one of them this film won the golden lion award for the best screenplay and the best film critics choice at the prestigious venice film festival which is considered as the oldest and the most prestigious among all other film festivals last film from india which won this award was mira nair aposs monsoon wedding long back in 2000 the plot revolves around a guy named sharad nerulkar who is very passionate and wants to make a career in indian classical music the film focuses more on his journey dilemma struggle regarding various instances in his life the plot may seem very much simple and yet it manages to entangle you in the story due to magnificent cinematography movement of the camera zooming into the lead character as he sings will show how much determination he has for his dreams this shot has been used time and time again in the movie second thing which will attract you is the slow motion shots as our lead character is riding a bike and is listening to the tap recordings of maai this particular camera work shows how much blindly and passionately he listens and follows maai aposs philosophy this particular one shot is trump card of the whole film the frames taken are exceptional and will enhance your visual experience after the cinematography the other positive point is the metaphorical writing in many of the shows and films we get an overview of the traditions regarding classical music but here we get that but not that much and there is a reason for it in the whole movie classical music has been used as a metaphor to anything that we are dedicated to so it is basically a life oriented movie and music has been used only as a metaphor thats why if you closely listen to maai aposs philosophy regarding music they are actually techniques of leading life and lastly the most important point is the sound designing in the whole movie you will get a perfect blend of digentic and non digentic sound the tanpura starts immediately when our lead character is listening to maai aposs philosophy and rest of the part you will hear normal and sounds now the negatives i didn apost find any negatives throughout the movie but this film more about visual storytelling and very less dialogues so if you are not into that then this movie is not for you according to me this movie is more than a masterpiece and i will request each and every individual to watch this film

slumping and lazily browsing through your bookshelf for a quick read a chetan bhagat book serves almost similar flavour what a smaranjit book is meant for in terms of bengali however this time he tries his hand with somewhat he loves to call fun thriller needless to say proving himself wrong in my opinion if not in mass opinion the story unfolds a rajasthani man keshav rajpurohit to fall in one sided love with a kashmiri muslim girl called zara lone the mystery sets in when one night in room 105 keshav finds her dead then the hunt for murderer begins with a juxtaposed outcome the pages are quite full with desi dialogues with a pinch of vulgar swear words random in bhagat ji novels nowadays kashmir sensitive topics terorism hint and army thing are clearly added for more promotional hype than storytelling or for the sake of plot twist i honestly think bhagat misuses his potential by writing his pieces only eying to make these spicey plot for upcoming bollywood masala flicks this one too not devoid of stock characters randomised taken for granted girl characters cheap punchlines and predictable ending thrill part is wasted while comedy part still manages to stand seriously would love something more credible coming out from him in future time alternative choice to consider rahasya samagra by shirshendu mukhopadhyaytumbaad dekhechi nirvana inn tao dekhechi ebar fobiya ta paul bettany on screen together they have a fantastic chemistry that brings their characters to life kathryn hahn also does her role well wandavision is weird and wonderful there is a strong sense of mystery and even danger by the end of each episode i ve been on the edge of my seat i crave more i really do wish that they released all the episodes together but i will not allow that to tarnish the greatness of this show after having such a long break between marvel content this is exactly what i needed to kickstart my love for the franchise again can t wait for more episodes reaction gachhe beshi kotha bolle spoiler dewa hoye jabe tobe ajker episode tar por uttejona aro bere galo marvel er ei bold move experimentation korar amar darun lagchhe ar sitcom er sathe sci fi mystery thriller er blending ta osadharon review movie i watched dc s aquaman today and to be honest this movie doesn t deserve to be treated like this by the critics especially aquaman is dc s one of the beautiful and finest creation and above all this movie has proved what dceu can give common movie lovers this movie is outstanding most common thing in the movie was the tone of the movie as it should be dark in story but the story telling is beautifully managed and exceed all our expectation and visuals were simply jaw dropping as a story aquaman is run of the mill mixing bits of national treasure thor black panther ormwasright and green lantern in a good way into an entertaining stew but the devil is in the details and the screen is filled with delightful details easter eggs and visual gags from beginning to end save for a reference to steppenwolf this is an entirely self contained movie and even the mid credit cookie is entirely in the service of this specific franchise it is colorful funny swashbuckling ly violent big screen entertainment with a simple story providing a framework for charming characters and top notch spectacle the third act soars accordingly delivering the promised absurdist lord of the rings but underwater action and by that time we like the characters enough to give a damn momoa s arc as aquaman is solid and includes some especially thoughtful intelligent self awareness and self criticism nicole kidman s atlanna is a wonderfully developed role and the one with the strongest emotional presentation she packs so much into a relatively small number of scenes but it s such a full story and kidman brings it all to life perfectly yahya abdul mateen ii as black manta is aquaman s most hated enemy and the film really sets up their conflict perfectly giving manta a singular understandable drive also he s simply one of the coolest looking villains in comics and now he s become one of the absolutely coolest looking villains in movies patrick wilson s ocean master has a few different motives and goals and it all works well even though i d like to have seen more passionate emphasis on his sense of righteousness regarding the threat posed by the surface world dolph lundgren plays king nereus and willem dafoe plays nuidis vulko both actors delivering smart restrained performances as dignified royalty who must choose sides in an increasingly brutal and complicated conflict aquaman is more similar to wonder woman than it is to batman v superman or man of steel so yeah i got my aquaman movie i mean i got my aquaman movie the one that lived in my heart the one i yearned to see yet never really believed would ever be made aquaman is an amazing achievement in superhero cinema filled with pulse pounding action and dazzling visual effects it s indiana jones black panther avatar and pirates of the caribbean rolled into one blockbuster ball of holiday cinema thanks a lot to happy2share and mystic phoenix for sharing this BODY: sharinganthe sharingan is a special type of dojutsu pupil technique that naturally occurs in all members of the uchiha clan though not all of them gain the ability to utilize it the sharingan is thought to be descended from the byakugan but grants the user different abilities and a different insight the sharingan aposs first and most well known ability is to memorize any technique that it is a witness to it can memorize ninjutsu ninja techniques genjutsu illusionary techniques and taijutsu hand to hand techniques with perfect accuracy and allow the user to use the techniques so long as they have the necessary resources to do so second it has the ability to predict an opponent aposs movement as well as allowing to track fast moving objects with great clarity third it is capable of a unique brand of hypnosis that involves suggesting actions and thoughts to the opponent fourth it can see through genjutsu the level of which is possibly dependent on the user aposs skill in order to copy a jutsu one has to have the physical ability to perform the technique for example they have to have the needed amount of chakra stamina agility and or strength in order to perform said technique in addition to physical skill the sharingan cannot copy any other bloodline abilities or summon a creature the user has not made a contract with because the user of the sharingan has to have the same blood as the other user the sharingan does not automatically appear from birth in a user instead it will usually appear when the user is in a life threatening situation where the power of the sharingan could save the user after this first appearance the user can then call up the sharingan any time he or she pleases due to its unique nature kakashi aposs sharingan is permanently on and thus he covers it except during heated battles to conserve chakra the power of the sharingan is judged through the number of tomoe in the person aposs eye it is not unheard of for a sharingan user to have different amounts of tomoe in each eye for example sasuke aposs sharingan initially had two tomoe in one eye and one in the other eventually his sharingan evolved to two tomoe in each eye then three a fully matured sharingan has three tomoe in each eye interestingly enough it is possible to transplant sharingan eyes from one person to another as occurred with kakashi and his deceased comrade obito however transplanted eyes do not work as well in a non uchiha body causing much more strain on the user as is the case with kakashi extended use of his sharingan will cause him to collapse uchiha clan members are not burdened with this weakness while activation of the sharingan does consume chakra the drain is so small as to be almost insignificant uchiha itachi in particular seems to have no trouble in keeping his sharingan activated near constantly characters who currently possess the sharingan include uchiha sasuke uchiha itachi and hatake kakashi kakashi aposs eye was given to him by uchiha obito one of his teammates in his original three man ninja team obito developed it in battle against rival rock shinobi and during this battle kakashi lost his left eye when he was attacked which is also the reason for his scar there near the end of the battle obito aposs right side is crushed under a giant rock and as his last act obito has rin a medical ninja remove his left eye and implant it in kakashi aposs left eye thus allowing kakashi to use the sharingan even though he does not have uchiha blood this is also why only his left eye is a sharingan eye sharingan is the pupil condition of the uchiha clan in the manga anime naruto

BODY: if you think you know about humanity you don t know humanity in 1974 yugoslavian performance artist marina abramovic dared to conduct a terrifying experiment to examine how people think many people have hailed abramovic as the grandmother of performance art after all she has been staging thought provoking interactive installations for more than 40 years indeed it can t be denied that her performances have a lasting impact in fact one of her earliest performances is still being talked about today abramovic staged a performance piece called rhythm 0 at studio morra in naples italy the premise of rhythm 0 was deceptively simple abramovic would stand still for six hours straight while the people who came to see her were urged to do whatever they wanted to her using one of 72 objects that she had placed on a table abramovic stood in the middle of the room with a notice board containing these words instructions there are 72 objects on the table that one can use on me as desired performance i am the object during this period i take full responsibility duration 6 hours 8 pm 2 am what happened in the next six hours was horrifying to say the least it began tamely someone turned her around someone thrust her arms into the air someone touched her somewhat intimately in the third hour all her clothes were cut from her with razor blades in the fourth hour the same blades began to explore her skin various minor sexual assaults were carried out on her body she was so committed to the piece that she would not have resisted rape or murder it just got worse in the last two hours abramovic s own account of what the people did to her was even more heartbreaking she recalled i felt raped they cut off the clothes they stuck me with thorns of rose in the stomach aimed the gun to my head another came apart when the six hours were over abramovic started to walk among the people they couldn t look her in the face abramovic observed that people didn t want any sort of confrontation with her they didn t want to be held accountable or judged for what they did it seemed as if they wanted to forget how they relished hurting her this work reveals something terrible about humanity it shows how fast a person can hurt you under favorable circumstances it shows that if he provides the stage the majority of normal people apparently can become truly violent that is the grammar of anarchy collected

robert pattinson elizabeth debicki kenneth branagh dimple kapadia michael caine and many more this quoted line is from the most awaited movie of christopher nolan tenet this one line was said by a character named laura for the lead character and the audience who were just about experience the absurdness of the film and yes at first i watched the movie at one go without giving a pause just to take that experience and the second time i rewatched few parts of the movie in order to understand it and i would say i tried my best to understand the movie though that is kind of impossible yet i developed my own perception of the entire film the plot is based on an unnamed guy who is referred as the protagonist played by j d washington is recruited by a secret organisation in his afterlife which is engaged in cold war with an unknown enemy he is advised by his senior to go after andrei sator played by kenneth branagh a russian arms dealer who is involved with some rare kind of ammunition that moves backwards through his journey he is assisted by neil robert pattinson and sator aposs wife katharine elizabeth debicki the first positive point in this movie is the writing probably in every nolan aposs movie we get an overview of something absurd or beyond our imagination thing is taking place without knowing its source or the cause of why its happening like in inception we never get to know what the whole dream machine is about but we see a detailed procedure of how they get involved in each others dream in interstellar we see the lead character communicating with his daughter through the 5 dimension world but we never get an overview how this is happening but in tenet he gave the explanation of the absurdities occurring though not all but he explains the exact reason behind time reversal concept and the pincher movement but he didn apost explain the concept of afterlife and the actual purpose of satore moreover the whole story being told through the perspective of the protagonist gives rise to several mysteries especially the involvement of neil remains a mystery but the ones who have watched the movie closely will know who this neil really is second great thing about this movie is the cinematography the whole time reversal action sequences is a delight to watch in the very beginning when the lead character is at the verge of being killed we see two trains passing simultaneously one in forward and the other one in backward direction which was a hint what is going to happen in the film in many of the action movies when we watch car flipping we watch it on pov shot or through distorted shots but here nolan uses a steady wide angle shot in a whole car flip scene which i must say is very very rare the editing of the movie is abrupt in few cases that is another good thing regarding this film now the negatives i personally didn apost find any negatives regarding the film but there are few concepts regarding the movie which you should be familiar with not the time reversal concept but the whole occurrence of the pincher movement is the main key factor if you are the ones who hasn apost seen a sci fi thriller or doesn apost know about nolan aposs filmography or style please don apost watch this film at first go for his previous films first in order to understand this one and if you want to develop a complete perception regarding this you need to watch each and every minute details and still if you cant you can refer to different blogs there is nothing shame in referring to a blog in order to understand BODY: review movie i watched dc s aquaman today and to be honest this movie doesn t deserve to be treated like this by the critics especially aquaman is dc s one of the beautiful and finest creation and above all this movie has proved what dceu can give common movie lovers this movie is outstanding most common thing in the movie was the tone of the movie as it should be dark in story but the story telling is beautifully managed and exceed all our expectation and visuals were simply jaw dropping as a story aquaman is run of the mill mixing bits of national treasure thor black panther ormwasright and green lantern in a good way into an entertaining stew but the devil is in the details and the screen is filled with delightful details easter eggs and visual gags from beginning to end save for a reference to steppenwolf this is an entirely self contained movie and even the mid credit cookie is entirely in the service of this specific franchise it is colorful funny swashbuckling ly violent big screen entertainment with a simple story providing a framework for charming characters and top notch spectacle the third act soars accordingly delivering the promised absurdist lord of the rings but underwater action and by that time we like the characters enough to give a damn momoa s arc as aquaman is solid and includes some especially thoughtful intelligent self awareness and self criticism nicole kidman s atlanna is a wonderfully developed role and the one with the strongest emotional presentation she packs so much into a relatively small number of scenes but it s such a full story and kidman brings it all to life perfectly yahya abdul mateen ii as black manta is aquaman s most hated enemy and the film really sets up their conflict perfectly giving manta a singular understandable drive also he s simply one of the coolest looking villains in comics and now he s become one of the absolutely coolest looking villains in movies patrick wilson s ocean master has a few different motives and goals and it all works well even though i d like to have seen more passionate emphasis on his sense of righteousness regarding the threat posed by the surface world dolph lundgren plays king nereus and willem dafoe plays nuidis vulko both actors delivering smart restrained performances as dignified royalty who must choose sides in an increasingly brutal and complicated conflict aquaman is more similar to wonder woman than it is to batman v superman or man of steel so yeah i got my aquaman movie i mean i got my aquaman movie the one that lived in my heart the one i yearned to see yet never really believed would ever be made aquaman is an amazing achievement in superhero cinema filled with pulse pounding action and dazzling visual effects it s indiana jones black panther avatar and pirates of the caribbean rolled into one blockbuster ball of holiday cinema thanks a lot to happy2share and mystic phoenix for sharing this movie with me my rating for this movie would be9 8 10 for character development and supporting characters 10 10 for fantastic visual effects and great imaginations9 2 10 for story and sub plotsoverall rating 9 7 10

BODY: life of an artist while rehearsing a scene from no land s man nawazuddin siddiqui became slightly emotional but since he is extremely professional he quickly regained his composure later on i came to know the reason the scene i mentioned was between him and his sister whose reel name was saima he asked me if i knew his sister s name is saima too i answered negative as my script was written five years ago and i had no idea about his sister he then told me his sister saima has been suffering from cancer for eight years and he has been trying everything he could to help her in this battle so whenever he had scenes phone conversations with saima he was feeling extremely emotional i didn t know how to respond to this strange connection i forgot this quickly as i had other things to deal with two days ago while we were shooting a scene he received a call we had no idea what was going on he completed the scene brilliantly after we packed up i came to know he lost his sister while we were shooting that scene i have recently developed some idea about this man s attachment to his family as someone who is strongly connected to family i could completely understand how he was feeling i didn t know how to deal with this situation but he knew while coordinating everything back home he continued his shoot and made sure our new york shoot is completed he will fly home today maybe he will be standing silently in front of her grave maybe they will speak thousand words in silence maybe fiction and reality will merge into each other nolandsmanfilm

BODY: every few decades there is a drastic change in how we view important societal and scientific problems what used to be a ridiculous idea yesterday can become the predominant opinion today only to turn into an obsolete notion tomorrow in the history of human beliefs change is the only constant most people living in 1921 shared views that today are considered quaint at best and dangerous at worst the chances that our present day convictions will remain relevant by 2121 are slim in fact we won t even have to wait 100 years as the speed of change is accelerating a good example is how quickly humanity changed its mind over the origins of covid just a year ago the idea that the virus originated from a wuhan lab was dismissed as a conspiracy theory facebook twitter and other social media platforms blocked posts promoting the lab leak theory today however this theory is on its way to becoming the mainstream scientific view of how the virus originated such instances make combating fake news and misinformation particularly challenging they can also fundamentally undermine people s trust in the neutrality of social media platforms and jeopardize future efforts to fight misinformation telegram never blocked posts discussing the lab leak theory because we didn t think it s our role to decide for our users what they should believe at the same time we felt that our users had the right to be informed about covid by official sources that reflected scientific consensus that s why we worked with 19 governments to help them reach out to every telegram user in their countries with up to date information on the pandemic today we call upon more governments to join the telegram anti covid initiative to make sure more people around the world get access critical knowledge that can save lives in my 20 years of managing discussion platforms i noticed that conspiracy theories only strengthen each time their content is removed by moderators instead of putting an end to wrong ideas censorship often makes it harder to fight them that s why spreading the truth will always be a more efficient strategy than engaging in censorship

BODY: review movie spoilerfreedisciple indian film winning the golden lion at venice film festival after 19 years year 2020writer director chaitanya tamhaneproducer vivek gombarcinematography michal soboci skimusic aneesh pradhancast aditya modak sushmita bhave ashwini kulkarni kiran yadnyopavit arun dravid and many more there are few films which can show you the reality of your boring life in a very interesting manner this film is one of them this film won the golden lion award for the best screenplay and the best film critics choice at the prestigious venice film festival which is considered as the oldest and the most prestigious among all other film festivals last film from india which won this award was mira nair s monsoon wedding long back in 2000 the plot revolves around a guy named sharad nerulkar who is very passionate and wants to make a career in indian classical music the film focuses more on his journey dilemma struggle regarding various instances in his life the plot may seem very much simple and yet it manages to entangle you in the story due to magnificent cinematography movement of the camera zooming into the lead character as he sings will show how much determination he has for his dreams this shot has been used time and time again in the movie second thing which will attract you is the slow motion shots as our lead character is riding a bike and is listening to the tap recordings of maai this particular camera work shows how much blindly and passionately he listens and follows maai s philosophy this particular one shot is trump card of the whole film the frames taken are exceptional and will enhance your visual experience after the cinematography the other positive point is the metaphorical writing in many of the shows and films we get an overview of the traditions regarding classical music but here we get that but not that much and there is a reason for it in the whole movie classical music has been used as a metaphor to anything that we are dedicated to so it is basically a life oriented movie and music has been used only as a metaphor thats why if you closely listen to maai s philosophy regarding music they are actually techniques of leading life and lastly the most important point is the sound designing in the whole movie you will get a perfect blend of digentic and non digentic sound the tanpura starts immediately when our lead character is listening to maai s philosophy and rest of the part you will hear normal and sounds now the negatives i didn t find any negatives throughout the movie but this film more about visual storytelling and very less dialogues so if you are not into that then this movie is not for you according to me this movie is more than a masterpiece and i will request each and every individual to watch this film

BODY: the phones of 50 000 individuals including human rights activists and journalists have been targeted by surveillance tools that were used by numerous governments these tools can hack any ios and android phone and there is no way to protect your device from it it doesn t matter which apps you use because the system is breached on a deeper level according to the snowden revelations from 2013 both apple and google are part of the global surveillance program that implies that these companies have to among other things implement backdoors into their mobile operating systems these backdoors usually disguised as security bugs allow us agencies to access information on any smartphone in the world the problem with such backdoors is that they are never exclusive to just one party anybody can exploit them so if a us security agency can hack an ios or android phone any other organization that uncovers the backdoors can do the same unsurprisingly this is exactly what has been taking place an israeli company called nso group has been selling access to the spying tools that allowed third parties to hack tens of thousands of phones since at least 2018 i have been aware that one of my phone numbers was included in a list of potential targets of such surveillance tools although a source from the nso group denies it personally i wasn t worried since 2011 when i was still living in russia i ve got used to assuming that all my phones were compromised anyone who gains access to my private data will be utterly disappointed they will have to go through thousands of concept designs for telegram features and millions of messages related to our product development process they won t find any important information there however these surveillance tools are also used against people far more prominent than me for example they were employed to spy on 14 heads of state the existence of backdoors in crucial infrastructure and software creates a huge challenge for humanity that s why i have been calling upon the governments of the world to start acting against the apple google duopoly in the smartphone market and to force them to open their closed ecosystems and allow for more competition so far even though the current market monopolization increases costs and impedes privacy and freedom of speech of billions government officials have been very slow to act i hope the news that they themselves have been targeted by these surveillance tools will prompt politicians to change their minds

witness to it can memorize ninjutsu ninja techniques genjutsu illusionary techniques and taijutsu hand to hand techniques with perfect accuracy and allow the user to use the techniques so long as they brand of hypnosis that involves suggesting actions and thoughts to the opponent fourth it can see through genjutsu the level of which is possibly dependent on the user s skill in order to copy a jutsu one has to have the physical ability to perform the technique for example they have to have the needed amount of chakra stamina agility and or strength in order to perform said technique in addition to physical skill the sharingan cannot copy any other bloodline abilities or summon a creature the user has not made a contract with because the user of the sharingan has to have the same blood as the other user the sharingan does not automatically appear from birth in a user instead it will usually appear when the user is in a life threatening situation where the power of the sharingan could save BODY: review movie i watched dc aposs aquaman today and to be honest this movie doesn apost deserve to be treated like this by the critics especially aquaman is dc aposs one of the beautiful and finest creation and above all this movie has proved what dceu can give common movie lovers this movie is outstanding most common thing in the movie was the tone of the movie as it should be dark in story but the story telling is beautifully managed and exceed all our expectation and visuals were simply jaw dropping as a story aquaman is run of the mill mixing bits of national treasure thor black panther ormwasright and green lantern in a good way into an entertaining stew but the devil is in the details and the screen is filled with delightful details easter eggs and visual gags from beginning to end save for a reference to steppenwolf this is an entirely self contained movie and even the mid credit cookie is entirely in the service of this specific franchise it is colorful funny swashbuckling ly violent big screen entertainment with a simple story providing a framework for charming characters and top notch spectacle the third act soars accordingly delivering the promised absurdist lord of the rings but underwater action and by that time we like the characters enough to give a damn momoa s arc as aquaman is solid and includes some especially thoughtful intelligent self awareness and self criticism nicole kidman s atlanna is a wonderfully developed role and the one with the strongest emotional presentation she packs so much into a relatively small number of scenes but it s such a full story and kidman brings it all to life perfectly yahya abdul mateen ii as black manta is aquaman s most hated enemy and the film really sets up their conflict perfectly giving manta a singular understandable drive also he s simply one of the coolest looking villains in comics and now he s become one of the absolutely coolest looking villains in movies patrick wilson s ocean master has a few different motives and goals and it all works well even though i d like to have seen more passionate emphasis on his sense of righteousness regarding the threat posed by the surface world dolph lundgren plays king nereus and willem dafoe plays nuidis vulko both actors delivering smart restrained performances as dignified royalty who must choose sides in an increasingly brutal and complicated conflict aquaman is more similar to wonder woman than it is to batman v superman or man of steel so yeah i got my aquaman movie i mean i got my aquaman movie the one that lived in my heart the one i yearned to see yet never really believed would ever be made aquaman is an amazing achievement in superhero cinema filled with pulse pounding action and dazzling visual effects it s indiana jones black panther avatar and pirates of the caribbean rolled into one blockbuster ball of holiday cinema thanks a lot to happy2share and mystic phoenix for sharing this movie with me my rating for this movie would be9 8 10 for character development and supporting characters 10 10 for fantastic visual effects and great imaginations9 2 10 for story and sub plotsoverall rating 9 7 10

BODY: if you think you know about humanity you don t know humanity in 1974 yugoslavian performance artist marina abramovic dared to conduct a terrifying experiment to examine how people think many people have hailed abramovic as the grandmother of performance art after all she has been staging thought provoking interactive installations for more than 40 years indeed it can t be denied that her performances have a lasting impact in fact one of her earliest performances is still being talked about today abramovic staged a performance piece called rhythm 0 at studio morra in naples italy the premise of rhythm 0 was deceptively simple abramovic would stand still for six hours straight while the people who came to see her were urged to do whatever they wanted to her using one of 72 objects that she had placed on a table abramovic stood in the middle of the room with a notice board containing these words instructions there are 72 objects on the table that one can use on me as desired performance i am the object during this period i take full responsibility duration 6 hours 8 pm 2 am what happened in the next six hours was horrifying to say the least it began tamely someone turned her around someone thrust her arms into the air someone touched her somewhat intimately in the third hour all her clothes were cut from her with razor blades in the fourth hour the same blades began to explore her skin various minor sexual assaults were carried out on her body she was so committed to the piece that she would not have resisted rape or murder it just got worse in the last two hours abramovic s own account of what the people did to her was even more heartbreaking she recalled i felt raped they cut off the clothes they stuck me with thorns of rose in the stomach aimed the gun to my head another came apart when the six hours were over abramovic started to walk among the people they couldn t look her in the face abramovic observed that people didn t want any sort of confrontation with her they didn t want to be held accountable or judged for what they did it seemed as if they wanted to forget how they relished hurting her this work reveals something terrible about humanity it shows how fast a person can hurt you under favorable circumstances it shows that if he provides the stage the majority of normal people apparently can become truly violent that is the grammar of anarchy

BODY: review movie spoilerfreeak vs ak there is some serious problm with netflix india year 2020streaming platform netflixscreenplay and direction vikramaditya motwanecinematography swapnil sonawanecast anil kapoor anurag kashyap sonam kapoor harshvardhan kapoor bony kapoor and many more i was really excited about this film when i watched the trailer since motwane is one of my favourite directors from bollywood the plot goes like this anurag kashyap wants to make a film using real life characters where sonam kapoor gets kidnapped and anil kapoor has to find her first i want to clarify a small thing i see a lot of people complaining that here anurag kashyap and anil kapoor are playing the characters which are not relevant to them actually they are playing the character in which the audience perceive them like anurag kashyap makes very dark films so naturally the many of the people may think that he himself is a sociopath where as anil kapoor is the mainstream star so the masses may think he in real life is also like that the first positive thing about this film is this approach which belongs to the metacinema genre vikramaditya motwane a man who loves to experiment did with this one too and to a certain extent it worked also the way the long shots are taken man handedly those are amazing few shots reminded me of dibakar banerjee directorial venture lsd which is one of my favourites the second positive point about this film is the screenplay which is way more satirical in one sequence harshvardhan kapoor tells anurag motwane fucked me with bhavesh joshi you will revive me and on another sequence anil kapoor gets hit by a car and anurag kashyap says daniel ka day lewis ho gaya there is blood there is blood and one another shot we see a girl pointing to anurag kashyap and say anurag basu which is often mistaken by people if you can get these lines you will get the amount of humour in it but none of the aks are mocked the one who is mocked are the people or the audience who create a dismantle hype with any of the news articles the film also showcases how much hardship a star goes through when he needs help from the common people now this whole thing gets messed up at the climax my reaction way exactly like tauba tauba sara mood kharab kar diya the climax is way more cliche than one could ever imagine i think netflix india may have pressurised the makers for this ending since people are liking thrillers nowadays and i dont expect this type of ending from a man who has made a film like bhavesh joshi superhero this is where the problm lies if this whole thing was produced independently under the phantom banner motwane would have given a better ending because this type of twists is justified for a classic age old srijit mukherjee thriller not today that too from a man like motwane so according to me the attempt and the presentation was kickass but the whole thing got messed up at the climax
